90 static CGCXXABI *createCXXABI(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
91  switch (CGM.getContext().getCXXABIKind()) {
92  case TargetCXXABI::AppleARM64:
93  case TargetCXXABI::Fuchsia:
94  case TargetCXXABI::GenericAArch64:
95  case TargetCXXABI::GenericARM:
96  case TargetCXXABI::iOS:
97  case TargetCXXABI::WatchOS:
98  case TargetCXXABI::GenericMIPS:
99  case TargetCXXABI::GenericItanium:
100  case TargetCXXABI::WebAssembly:
101  case TargetCXXABI::XL:
102  return CreateItaniumCXXABI(CGM);
103  case TargetCXXABI::Microsoft:
104  return CreateMicrosoftCXXABI(CGM);
105  }
106 
107  llvm_unreachable("invalid C++ ABI kind");
108 }
109 
110 static bool SYCLCUDAIsHost(const clang::LangOptions &LangOpts) {
111  // Return true for the host compilation of SYCL CUDA sources.
112  return LangOpts.SYCLIsHost && LangOpts.CUDA && !LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice;
113 }
114 static bool SYCLCUDAIsSYCLDevice(const clang::LangOptions &LangOpts) {
115  // Return true for the SYCL device compilation of SYCL CUDA sources.
116  return LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && LangOpts.CUDA && !LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice;
117 }

119 static std::unique_ptr<TargetCodeGenInfo>
120 createTargetCodeGenInfo(CodeGenModule &CGM) {
121  const TargetInfo &Target = CGM.getTarget();
122  const llvm::Triple &Triple = Target.getTriple();
123  const CodeGenOptions &CodeGenOpts = CGM.getCodeGenOpts();
124 
125  switch (Triple.getArch()) {
126  default:
127  return createDefaultTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
128 
129  case llvm::Triple::le32:
130  return createPNaClTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
131  case llvm::Triple::m68k:
132  return createM68kTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
133  case llvm::Triple::mips:
134  case llvm::Triple::mipsel:
135  if (Triple.getOS() == llvm::Triple::NaCl)
136  return createPNaClTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
137  return createMIPSTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, /*IsOS32=*/true);
138 
139  case llvm::Triple::mips64:
140  case llvm::Triple::mips64el:
141  return createMIPSTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, /*IsOS32=*/false);
142 
143  case llvm::Triple::avr: {
144  // For passing parameters, R8~R25 are used on avr, and R18~R25 are used
145  // on avrtiny. For passing return value, R18~R25 are used on avr, and
146  // R22~R25 are used on avrtiny.
147  unsigned NPR = Target.getABI() == "avrtiny" ? 6 : 18;
148  unsigned NRR = Target.getABI() == "avrtiny" ? 4 : 8;
149  return createAVRTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, NPR, NRR);
150  }
151 
152  case llvm::Triple::aarch64:
153  case llvm::Triple::aarch64_32:
154  case llvm::Triple::aarch64_be: {
155  AArch64ABIKind Kind = AArch64ABIKind::AAPCS;
156  if (Target.getABI() == "darwinpcs")
157  Kind = AArch64ABIKind::DarwinPCS;
158  else if (Triple.isOSWindows())
159  return createWindowsAArch64TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, AArch64ABIKind::Win64);
160  else if (Target.getABI() == "aapcs-soft")
161  Kind = AArch64ABIKind::AAPCSSoft;
162 
163  return createAArch64TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, Kind);
164  }
165 
166  case llvm::Triple::wasm32:
167  case llvm::Triple::wasm64: {
168  WebAssemblyABIKind Kind = WebAssemblyABIKind::MVP;
169  if (Target.getABI() == "experimental-mv")
170  Kind = WebAssemblyABIKind::ExperimentalMV;
171  return createWebAssemblyTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, Kind);
172  }
173 
174  case llvm::Triple::arm:
175  case llvm::Triple::armeb:
176  case llvm::Triple::thumb:
177  case llvm::Triple::thumbeb: {
178  if (Triple.getOS() == llvm::Triple::Win32)
179  return createWindowsARMTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, ARMABIKind::AAPCS_VFP);
180 
181  ARMABIKind Kind = ARMABIKind::AAPCS;
182  StringRef ABIStr = Target.getABI();
183  if (ABIStr == "apcs-gnu")
184  Kind = ARMABIKind::APCS;
185  else if (ABIStr == "aapcs16")
186  Kind = ARMABIKind::AAPCS16_VFP;
187  else if (CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "hard" ||
188  (CodeGenOpts.FloatABI != "soft" &&
189  (Triple.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::GNUEABIHF ||
190  Triple.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::MuslEABIHF ||
191  Triple.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::EABIHF)))
192  Kind = ARMABIKind::AAPCS_VFP;
193 
194  return createARMTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, Kind);
195  }
196 
197  case llvm::Triple::ppc: {
198  if (Triple.isOSAIX())
199  return createAIXTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, /*Is64Bit=*/false);
200 
201  bool IsSoftFloat =
202  CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft" || Target.hasFeature("spe");
203  return createPPC32TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, IsSoftFloat);
204  }
205  case llvm::Triple::ppcle: {
206  bool IsSoftFloat = CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft";
207  return createPPC32TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, IsSoftFloat);
208  }
209  case llvm::Triple::ppc64:
210  if (Triple.isOSAIX())
211  return createAIXTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, /*Is64Bit=*/true);
212 
213  if (Triple.isOSBinFormatELF()) {
214  PPC64_SVR4_ABIKind Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIKind::ELFv1;
215  if (Target.getABI() == "elfv2")
216  Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIKind::ELFv2;
217  bool IsSoftFloat = CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft";
218 
219  return createPPC64_SVR4_TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, Kind, IsSoftFloat);
220  }
221  return createPPC64TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
222  case llvm::Triple::ppc64le: {
223  assert(Triple.isOSBinFormatELF() && "PPC64 LE non-ELF not supported!");
224  PPC64_SVR4_ABIKind Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIKind::ELFv2;
225  if (Target.getABI() == "elfv1")
226  Kind = PPC64_SVR4_ABIKind::ELFv1;
227  bool IsSoftFloat = CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft";
228 
229  return createPPC64_SVR4_TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, Kind, IsSoftFloat);
230  }
231 
232  case llvm::Triple::nvptx:
233  case llvm::Triple::nvptx64:
234  return createNVPTXTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
235 
236  case llvm::Triple::msp430:
237  return createMSP430TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
238 
239  case llvm::Triple::riscv32:
240  case llvm::Triple::riscv64: {
241  StringRef ABIStr = Target.getABI();
242  unsigned XLen = Target.getPointerWidth(LangAS::Default);
243  unsigned ABIFLen = 0;
244  if (ABIStr.ends_with("f"))
245  ABIFLen = 32;
246  else if (ABIStr.ends_with("d"))
247  ABIFLen = 64;
248  bool EABI = ABIStr.ends_with("e");
249  return createRISCVTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, XLen, ABIFLen, EABI);
250  }
251 
252  case llvm::Triple::systemz: {
253  bool SoftFloat = CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft";
254  bool HasVector = !SoftFloat && Target.getABI() == "vector";
255  return createSystemZTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, HasVector, SoftFloat);
256  }
257 
258  case llvm::Triple::tce:
259  case llvm::Triple::tcele:
260  return createTCETargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
261 
262  case llvm::Triple::x86: {
263  bool IsDarwinVectorABI = Triple.isOSDarwin();
264  bool IsWin32FloatStructABI = Triple.isOSWindows() && !Triple.isOSCygMing();
265 
266  if (Triple.getOS() == llvm::Triple::Win32) {
267  return createWinX86_32TargetCodeGenInfo(
268  CGM, IsDarwinVectorABI, IsWin32FloatStructABI,
269  CodeGenOpts.NumRegisterParameters);
270  }
271  return createX86_32TargetCodeGenInfo(
272  CGM, IsDarwinVectorABI, IsWin32FloatStructABI,
273  CodeGenOpts.NumRegisterParameters, CodeGenOpts.FloatABI == "soft");
274  }
275 
276  case llvm::Triple::x86_64: {
277  StringRef ABI = Target.getABI();
278  X86AVXABILevel AVXLevel = (ABI == "avx512" ? X86AVXABILevel::AVX512
279  : ABI == "avx" ? X86AVXABILevel::AVX
280  : X86AVXABILevel::None);
281 
282  switch (Triple.getOS()) {
283  case llvm::Triple::Win32:
284  return createWinX86_64TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, AVXLevel);
285  default:
286  return createX86_64TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, AVXLevel);
287  }
288  }
289  case llvm::Triple::hexagon:
290  return createHexagonTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
291  case llvm::Triple::lanai:
292  return createLanaiTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
293  case llvm::Triple::r600:
294  return createAMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
295  case llvm::Triple::amdgcn:
296  return createAMDGPUTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
297  case llvm::Triple::sparc:
298  return createSparcV8TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
299  case llvm::Triple::sparcv9:
300  return createSparcV9TargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
301  case llvm::Triple::xcore:
302  return createXCoreTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
303  case llvm::Triple::arc:
304  return createARCTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
305  case llvm::Triple::spir:
306  case llvm::Triple::spir64:
307  return createCommonSPIRTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
308  case llvm::Triple::spirv32:
309  case llvm::Triple::spirv64:
310  return createSPIRVTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
311  case llvm::Triple::ve:
312  return createVETargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
313  case llvm::Triple::csky: {
314  bool IsSoftFloat = !Target.hasFeature("hard-float-abi");
315  bool hasFP64 =
316  Target.hasFeature("fpuv2_df") || Target.hasFeature("fpuv3_df");
317  return createCSKYTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM, IsSoftFloat ? 0
318  : hasFP64 ? 64
319  : 32);
320  }
321  case llvm::Triple::bpfeb:
322  case llvm::Triple::bpfel:
323  return createBPFTargetCodeGenInfo(CGM);
324  case llvm::Triple::loongarch32:
325  case llvm::Triple::loongarch64: {
326  StringRef ABIStr = Target.getABI();
327  unsigned ABIFRLen = 0;
328  if (ABIStr.ends_with("f"))
329  ABIFRLen = 32;
330  else if (ABIStr.ends_with("d"))
331  ABIFRLen = 64;
332  return createLoongArchTargetCodeGenInfo(
333  CGM, Target.getPointerWidth(LangAS::Default), ABIFRLen);
334  }
335  }
336 }
337 
338 const TargetCodeGenInfo &CodeGenModule::getTargetCodeGenInfo() {
339  if (!TheTargetCodeGenInfo)
340  TheTargetCodeGenInfo = createTargetCodeGenInfo(*this);
341  return *TheTargetCodeGenInfo;
342 }
343 
344 CodeGenModule::CodeGenModule(ASTContext &C,
345  IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem> FS,
346  const HeaderSearchOptions &HSO,
347  const PreprocessorOptions &PPO,
348  const CodeGenOptions &CGO, llvm::Module &M,
349  DiagnosticsEngine &diags,
350  CoverageSourceInfo *CoverageInfo)
351  : Context(C), LangOpts(C.getLangOpts()), FS(FS), HeaderSearchOpts(HSO),
352  PreprocessorOpts(PPO), CodeGenOpts(CGO), TheModule(M), Diags(diags),
353  Target(C.getTargetInfo()), ABI(createCXXABI(*this)),
354  VMContext(M.getContext()), Types(*this), VTables(*this),
355  SanitizerMD(new SanitizerMetadata(*this)) {
356 
357  // Initialize the type cache.
358  llvm::LLVMContext &LLVMContext = M.getContext();
359  VoidTy = llvm::Type::getVoidTy(LLVMContext);
360  Int8Ty = llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(LLVMContext);
361  Int16Ty = llvm::Type::getInt16Ty(LLVMContext);
362  Int32Ty = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(LLVMContext);
363  Int64Ty = llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(LLVMContext);
364  HalfTy = llvm::Type::getHalfTy(LLVMContext);
365  BFloatTy = llvm::Type::getBFloatTy(LLVMContext);
366  FloatTy = llvm::Type::getFloatTy(LLVMContext);
367  DoubleTy = llvm::Type::getDoubleTy(LLVMContext);
368  PointerWidthInBits = C.getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(LangAS::Default);
369  PointerAlignInBytes =
370  C.toCharUnitsFromBits(C.getTargetInfo().getPointerAlign(LangAS::Default))
371  .getQuantity();
372  SizeSizeInBytes =
373  C.toCharUnitsFromBits(C.getTargetInfo().getMaxPointerWidth()).getQuantity();
374  IntAlignInBytes =
375  C.toCharUnitsFromBits(C.getTargetInfo().getIntAlign()).getQuantity();
376  CharTy =
377  llvm::IntegerType::get(LLVMContext, C.getTargetInfo().getCharWidth());
378  IntTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(LLVMContext, C.getTargetInfo().getIntWidth());
379  IntPtrTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(LLVMContext,
380  C.getTargetInfo().getMaxPointerWidth());
381  Int8PtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(LLVMContext, 0);
382  const llvm::DataLayout &DL = M.getDataLayout();
383  AllocaInt8PtrTy =
384  llvm::PointerType::get(LLVMContext, DL.getAllocaAddrSpace());
385  GlobalsInt8PtrTy =
386  llvm::PointerType::get(LLVMContext, DL.getDefaultGlobalsAddressSpace());
387  DefaultInt8PtrTy =
388  Int8Ty->getPointerTo(getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default));
389  ConstGlobalsPtrTy = llvm::PointerType::get(
390  LLVMContext, C.getTargetAddressSpace(GetGlobalConstantAddressSpace()));
391  ASTAllocaAddressSpace = getTargetCodeGenInfo().getASTAllocaAddressSpace();
392 
393  // Build C++20 Module initializers.
394  // TODO: Add Microsoft here once we know the mangling required for the
395  // initializers.
396  CXX20ModuleInits =
397  LangOpts.CPlusPlusModules && getCXXABI().getMangleContext().getKind() ==
398  ItaniumMangleContext::MK_Itanium;
399 
400  RuntimeCC = getTargetCodeGenInfo().getABIInfo().getRuntimeCC();
401 
402  if (LangOpts.ObjC)
403  createObjCRuntime();
404  if (LangOpts.OpenCL || LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
405  createOpenCLRuntime();
406  if (LangOpts.OpenMP)
407  createOpenMPRuntime();
408  if (LangOpts.CUDA)
409  createCUDARuntime();
410  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
411  createSYCLRuntime();
412  if (LangOpts.HLSL)
413  createHLSLRuntime();
414 
415  // Enable TBAA unless it's suppressed. ThreadSanitizer needs TBAA even at O0.
416  if (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Thread) ||
417  (!CodeGenOpts.RelaxedAliasing && CodeGenOpts.OptimizationLevel > 0))
418  TBAA.reset(new CodeGenTBAA(Context, getTypes(), TheModule, CodeGenOpts,
419  getLangOpts(), getCXXABI().getMangleContext()));
420 
421  // If debug info or coverage generation is enabled, create the CGDebugInfo
422  // object.
423  if (CodeGenOpts.getDebugInfo() != llvm::codegenoptions::NoDebugInfo ||
424  CodeGenOpts.CoverageNotesFile.size() ||
425  CodeGenOpts.CoverageDataFile.size())
426  DebugInfo.reset(new CGDebugInfo(*this));
427 
428  Block.GlobalUniqueCount = 0;
429 
430  if (C.getLangOpts().ObjC)
431  ObjCData.reset(new ObjCEntrypoints());
432 
433  if (CodeGenOpts.hasProfileClangUse()) {
434  auto ReaderOrErr = llvm::IndexedInstrProfReader::create(
435  CodeGenOpts.ProfileInstrumentUsePath, *FS,
436  CodeGenOpts.ProfileRemappingFile);
437  // We're checking for profile read errors in CompilerInvocation, so if
438  // there was an error it should've already been caught. If it hasn't been
439  // somehow, trip an assertion.
440  assert(ReaderOrErr);
441  PGOReader = std::move(ReaderOrErr.get());
442  }
443 
444  // If coverage mapping generation is enabled, create the
445  // CoverageMappingModuleGen object.
446  if (CodeGenOpts.CoverageMapping)
447  CoverageMapping.reset(new CoverageMappingModuleGen(*this, *CoverageInfo));
448 
449  // Generate the module name hash here if needed.
450  if (CodeGenOpts.UniqueInternalLinkageNames &&
451  !getModule().getSourceFileName().empty()) {
452  std::string Path = getModule().getSourceFileName();
453  // Check if a path substitution is needed from the MacroPrefixMap.
454  for (const auto &Entry : LangOpts.MacroPrefixMap)
455  if (Path.rfind(Entry.first, 0) != std::string::npos) {
456  Path = Entry.second + Path.substr(Entry.first.size());
457  break;
458  }
459  ModuleNameHash = llvm::getUniqueInternalLinkagePostfix(Path);
460  }
461 }
462 
463 CodeGenModule::~CodeGenModule() {}
464 
465 void CodeGenModule::createObjCRuntime() {
466  // This is just isGNUFamily(), but we want to force implementors of
467  // new ABIs to decide how best to do this.
468  switch (LangOpts.ObjCRuntime.getKind()) {
469  case ObjCRuntime::GNUstep:
470  case ObjCRuntime::GCC:
471  case ObjCRuntime::ObjFW:
472  ObjCRuntime.reset(CreateGNUObjCRuntime(*this));
473  return;
474 
475  case ObjCRuntime::FragileMacOSX:
476  case ObjCRuntime::MacOSX:
477  case ObjCRuntime::iOS:
478  case ObjCRuntime::WatchOS:
479  ObjCRuntime.reset(CreateMacObjCRuntime(*this));
480  return;
481  }
482  llvm_unreachable("bad runtime kind");
483 }
484 
485 void CodeGenModule::createOpenCLRuntime() {
486  OpenCLRuntime.reset(new CGOpenCLRuntime(*this));
487 }
488 
489 void CodeGenModule::createOpenMPRuntime() {
490  // Select a specialized code generation class based on the target, if any.
491  // If it does not exist use the default implementation.
492  switch (getTriple().getArch()) {
493  case llvm::Triple::nvptx:
494  case llvm::Triple::nvptx64:
495  case llvm::Triple::amdgcn:
496  assert(getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice &&
497  "OpenMP AMDGPU/NVPTX is only prepared to deal with device code.");
498  OpenMPRuntime.reset(new CGOpenMPRuntimeGPU(*this));
499  break;
500  default:
501  if (LangOpts.OpenMPSimd)
502  OpenMPRuntime.reset(new CGOpenMPSIMDRuntime(*this));
503  else
504  OpenMPRuntime.reset(new CGOpenMPRuntime(*this));
505  break;
506  }
507 }
508 
509 void CodeGenModule::createCUDARuntime() {
510  CUDARuntime.reset(CreateNVCUDARuntime(*this));
511 }
512 
513 void CodeGenModule::createSYCLRuntime() {
514  SYCLRuntime.reset(new CGSYCLRuntime(*this));
515 }

517 void CodeGenModule::createHLSLRuntime() {
518  HLSLRuntime.reset(new CGHLSLRuntime(*this));
519 }

521 void CodeGenModule::addReplacement(StringRef Name, llvm::Constant *C) {
522  Replacements[Name] = C;
523 }
524 
525 void CodeGenModule::applyReplacements() {
526  for (auto &I : Replacements) {
527  StringRef MangledName = I.first;
528  llvm::Constant *Replacement = I.second;
529  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
530  if (!Entry)
531  continue;
532  auto *OldF = cast<llvm::Function>(Entry);
533  auto *NewF = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Replacement);
534  if (!NewF) {
535  if (auto *Alias = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(Replacement)) {
536  NewF = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Alias->getAliasee());
537  } else {
538  auto *CE = cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(Replacement);
539  assert(CE->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::BitCast ||
540  CE->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::GetElementPtr);
541  NewF = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(CE->getOperand(0));
542  }
543  }
544 
545  // Replace old with new, but keep the old order.
546  OldF->replaceAllUsesWith(Replacement);
547  if (NewF) {
548  NewF->removeFromParent();
549  OldF->getParent()->getFunctionList().insertAfter(OldF->getIterator(),
550  NewF);
551  }
552  OldF->eraseFromParent();
553  }
554 }
555 
556 void CodeGenModule::addGlobalValReplacement(llvm::GlobalValue *GV, llvm::Constant *C) {
557  GlobalValReplacements.push_back(std::make_pair(GV, C));
558 }
559 
560 void CodeGenModule::applyGlobalValReplacements() {
561  for (auto &I : GlobalValReplacements) {
562  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = I.first;
563  llvm::Constant *C = I.second;
564 
565  GV->replaceAllUsesWith(C);
566  GV->eraseFromParent();
567  }
568 }
569 
570 // This is only used in aliases that we created and we know they have a
571 // linear structure.
572 static const llvm::GlobalValue *getAliasedGlobal(const llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
573  const llvm::Constant *C;
574  if (auto *GA = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(GV))
575  C = GA->getAliasee();
576  else if (auto *GI = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(GV))
577  C = GI->getResolver();
578  else
579  return GV;
580 
581  const auto *AliaseeGV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(C->stripPointerCasts());
582  if (!AliaseeGV)
583  return nullptr;
584 
585  const llvm::GlobalValue *FinalGV = AliaseeGV->getAliaseeObject();
586  if (FinalGV == GV)
587  return nullptr;
588 
589  return FinalGV;
590 }
591 
592 static bool checkAliasedGlobal(
593  const ASTContext &Context, DiagnosticsEngine &Diags, SourceLocation Location,
594  bool IsIFunc, const llvm::GlobalValue *Alias, const llvm::GlobalValue *&GV,
595  const llvm::MapVector<GlobalDecl, StringRef> &MangledDeclNames,
596  SourceRange AliasRange) {
597  GV = getAliasedGlobal(Alias);
598  if (!GV) {
599  Diags.Report(Location, diag::err_cyclic_alias) << IsIFunc;
600  return false;
601  }
602 
603  if (GV->hasCommonLinkage()) {
604  const llvm::Triple &Triple = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple();
605  if (Triple.getObjectFormat() == llvm::Triple::XCOFF) {
606  Diags.Report(Location, diag::err_alias_to_common);
607  return false;
608  }
609  }
610 
611  if (GV->isDeclaration()) {
612  Diags.Report(Location, diag::err_alias_to_undefined) << IsIFunc << IsIFunc;
613  Diags.Report(Location, diag::note_alias_requires_mangled_name)
614  << IsIFunc << IsIFunc;
615  // Provide a note if the given function is not found and exists as a
616  // mangled name.
617  for (const auto &[Decl, Name] : MangledDeclNames) {
618  if (const auto *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(Decl.getDecl())) {
619  if (ND->getName() == GV->getName()) {
620  Diags.Report(Location, diag::note_alias_mangled_name_alternative)
621  << Name
622  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(
623  AliasRange,
624  (Twine(IsIFunc ? "ifunc" : "alias") + "(\"" + Name + "\")")
625  .str());
626  }
627  }
628  }
629  return false;
630  }
631 
632  if (IsIFunc) {
633  // Check resolver function type.
634  const auto *F = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
635  if (!F) {
636  Diags.Report(Location, diag::err_alias_to_undefined)
637  << IsIFunc << IsIFunc;
638  return false;
639  }
640 
641  llvm::FunctionType *FTy = F->getFunctionType();
642  if (!FTy->getReturnType()->isPointerTy()) {
643  Diags.Report(Location, diag::err_ifunc_resolver_return);
644  return false;
645  }
646  }
647 
648  return true;
649 }
650 
651 // Emit a warning if toc-data attribute is requested for global variables that
652 // have aliases and remove the toc-data attribute.
653 static void checkAliasForTocData(llvm::GlobalVariable *GVar,
654  const CodeGenOptions &CodeGenOpts,
655  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
656  SourceLocation Location) {
657  if (GVar->hasAttribute("toc-data")) {
658  auto GVId = GVar->getName();
659  // Is this a global variable specified by the user as local?
660  if ((llvm::binary_search(CodeGenOpts.TocDataVarsUserSpecified, GVId))) {
661  Diags.Report(Location, diag::warn_toc_unsupported_type)
662  << GVId << "the variable has an alias";
663  }
664  llvm::AttributeSet CurrAttributes = GVar->getAttributes();
665  llvm::AttributeSet NewAttributes =
666  CurrAttributes.removeAttribute(GVar->getContext(), "toc-data");
667  GVar->setAttributes(NewAttributes);
668  }
669 }
670 
671 void CodeGenModule::checkAliases() {
672  // Check if the constructed aliases are well formed. It is really unfortunate
673  // that we have to do this in CodeGen, but we only construct mangled names
674  // and aliases during codegen.
675  bool Error = false;
676  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags = getDiags();
677  for (const GlobalDecl &GD : Aliases) {
678  const auto *D = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
679  SourceLocation Location;
680  SourceRange Range;
681  bool IsIFunc = D->hasAttr<IFuncAttr>();
682  if (const Attr *A = D->getDefiningAttr()) {
683  Location = A->getLocation();
684  Range = A->getRange();
685  } else
686  llvm_unreachable("Not an alias or ifunc?");
687 
688  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
689  llvm::GlobalValue *Alias = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
690  const llvm::GlobalValue *GV = nullptr;
691  if (!checkAliasedGlobal(getContext(), Diags, Location, IsIFunc, Alias, GV,
692  MangledDeclNames, Range)) {
693  Error = true;
694  continue;
695  }
696 
697  if (getContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSAIX())
698  if (const llvm::GlobalVariable *GVar =
699  dyn_cast<const llvm::GlobalVariable>(GV))
700  checkAliasForTocData(const_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable *>(GVar),
701  getCodeGenOpts(), Diags, Location);
702 
703  llvm::Constant *Aliasee =
704  IsIFunc ? cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(Alias)->getResolver()
705  : cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(Alias)->getAliasee();
706 
707  llvm::GlobalValue *AliaseeGV;
708  if (auto CE = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(Aliasee))
709  AliaseeGV = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(CE->getOperand(0));
710  else
711  AliaseeGV = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Aliasee);
712 
713  if (const SectionAttr *SA = D->getAttr<SectionAttr>()) {
714  StringRef AliasSection = SA->getName();
715  if (AliasSection != AliaseeGV->getSection())
716  Diags.Report(SA->getLocation(), diag::warn_alias_with_section)
717  << AliasSection << IsIFunc << IsIFunc;
718  }
719 
720  // We have to handle alias to weak aliases in here. LLVM itself disallows
721  // this since the object semantics would not match the IL one. For
722  // compatibility with gcc we implement it by just pointing the alias
723  // to its aliasee's aliasee. We also warn, since the user is probably
724  // expecting the link to be weak.
725  if (auto *GA = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(AliaseeGV)) {
726  if (GA->isInterposable()) {
727  Diags.Report(Location, diag::warn_alias_to_weak_alias)
728  << GV->getName() << GA->getName() << IsIFunc;
729  Aliasee = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
730  GA->getAliasee(), Alias->getType());
731 
732  if (IsIFunc)
733  cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(Alias)->setResolver(Aliasee);
734  else
735  cast<llvm::GlobalAlias>(Alias)->setAliasee(Aliasee);
736  }
737  }
738  }
739  if (!Error)
740  return;
741 
742  for (const GlobalDecl &GD : Aliases) {
743  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
744  llvm::GlobalValue *Alias = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
745  Alias->replaceAllUsesWith(llvm::UndefValue::get(Alias->getType()));
746  Alias->eraseFromParent();
747  }
748 }
749 
750 void CodeGenModule::clear() {
751  DeferredDeclsToEmit.clear();
752  EmittedDeferredDecls.clear();
753  DeferredAnnotations.clear();
754  if (OpenMPRuntime)
755  OpenMPRuntime->clear();
756 }
757 
758 void InstrProfStats::reportDiagnostics(DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
759  StringRef MainFile) {
760  if (!hasDiagnostics())
761  return;
762  if (VisitedInMainFile > 0 && VisitedInMainFile == MissingInMainFile) {
763  if (MainFile.empty())
764  MainFile = "<stdin>";
765  Diags.Report(diag::warn_profile_data_unprofiled) << MainFile;
766  } else {
767  if (Mismatched > 0)
768  Diags.Report(diag::warn_profile_data_out_of_date) << Visited << Mismatched;
769 
770  if (Missing > 0)
771  Diags.Report(diag::warn_profile_data_missing) << Visited << Missing;
772  }
773 }
774 
775 static std::optional<llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes>
776 getLLVMVisibility(clang::LangOptions::VisibilityFromDLLStorageClassKinds K) {
777  // Map to LLVM visibility.
778  switch (K) {
779  case clang::LangOptions::VisibilityFromDLLStorageClassKinds::Keep:
780  return std::nullopt;
781  case clang::LangOptions::VisibilityFromDLLStorageClassKinds::Default:
782  return llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility;
783  case clang::LangOptions::VisibilityFromDLLStorageClassKinds::Hidden:
784  return llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility;
785  case clang::LangOptions::VisibilityFromDLLStorageClassKinds::Protected:
786  return llvm::GlobalValue::ProtectedVisibility;
787  }
788  llvm_unreachable("unknown option value!");
789 }
790 
791 void setLLVMVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue &GV,
792  std::optional<llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes> V) {
793  if (!V)
794  return;
795 
796  // Reset DSO locality before setting the visibility. This removes
797  // any effects that visibility options and annotations may have
798  // had on the DSO locality. Setting the visibility will implicitly set
799  // appropriate globals to DSO Local; however, this will be pessimistic
800  // w.r.t. to the normal compiler IRGen.
801  GV.setDSOLocal(false);
802  GV.setVisibility(*V);
803 }
804 
805 static void setVisibilityFromDLLStorageClass(const clang::LangOptions &LO,
806  llvm::Module &M) {
807  if (!LO.VisibilityFromDLLStorageClass)
808  return;
809 
810  std::optional<llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes> DLLExportVisibility =
811  getLLVMVisibility(LO.getDLLExportVisibility());
812 
813  std::optional<llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes>
814  NoDLLStorageClassVisibility =
815  getLLVMVisibility(LO.getNoDLLStorageClassVisibility());
816 
817  std::optional<llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes>
818  ExternDeclDLLImportVisibility =
819  getLLVMVisibility(LO.getExternDeclDLLImportVisibility());
820 
821  std::optional<llvm::GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes>
822  ExternDeclNoDLLStorageClassVisibility =
823  getLLVMVisibility(LO.getExternDeclNoDLLStorageClassVisibility());
824 
825  for (llvm::GlobalValue &GV : M.global_values()) {
826  if (GV.hasAppendingLinkage() || GV.hasLocalLinkage())
827  continue;
828 
829  if (GV.isDeclarationForLinker())
830  setLLVMVisibility(GV, GV.getDLLStorageClass() ==
831  llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass
832  ? ExternDeclDLLImportVisibility
833  : ExternDeclNoDLLStorageClassVisibility);
834  else
835  setLLVMVisibility(GV, GV.getDLLStorageClass() ==
836  llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass
837  ? DLLExportVisibility
838  : NoDLLStorageClassVisibility);
839 
840  GV.setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass);
841  }
842 }
843 
844 static llvm::MDNode *getAspectsMD(ASTContext &ASTContext,
845  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx, StringRef Name,
846  const SYCLUsesAspectsAttr *A) {
847  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 4> AspectsMD;
848  AspectsMD.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, Name));
849  for (auto *Aspect : A->aspects()) {
850  llvm::APSInt AspectInt = Aspect->EvaluateKnownConstInt(ASTContext);
851  AspectsMD.push_back(llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
852  llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(Ctx), AspectInt.getZExtValue())));
853  }
854  return llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, AspectsMD);
855 }
856 
857 static llvm::MDNode *getAspectEnumValueMD(ASTContext &ASTContext,
858  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx,
859  const EnumConstantDecl *ECD) {
860  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 2> AspectEnumValMD;
861  AspectEnumValMD.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, ECD->getName()));
862  AspectEnumValMD.push_back(
863  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
864  llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(Ctx), ECD->getInitVal().getSExtValue())));
865  return llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, AspectEnumValMD);
866 }
867 
868 static bool isStackProtectorOn(const LangOptions &LangOpts,
869  const llvm::Triple &Triple,
870  clang::LangOptions::StackProtectorMode Mode) {
871  if (Triple.isAMDGPU() || Triple.isNVPTX())
872  return false;
873  return LangOpts.getStackProtector() == Mode;
874 }
875 
876 void CodeGenModule::Release() {
877  Module *Primary = getContext().getCurrentNamedModule();
878  if (CXX20ModuleInits && Primary && !Primary->isHeaderLikeModule())
879  EmitModuleInitializers(Primary);
880  EmitDeferred();
881  DeferredDecls.insert(EmittedDeferredDecls.begin(),
882  EmittedDeferredDecls.end());
883  EmittedDeferredDecls.clear();
884  EmitVTablesOpportunistically();
885  applyGlobalValReplacements();
886  applyReplacements();
887  emitMultiVersionFunctions();
888 
889  if (Context.getLangOpts().IncrementalExtensions &&
890  GlobalTopLevelStmtBlockInFlight.first) {
891  const TopLevelStmtDecl *TLSD = GlobalTopLevelStmtBlockInFlight.second;
892  GlobalTopLevelStmtBlockInFlight.first->FinishFunction(TLSD->getEndLoc());
893  GlobalTopLevelStmtBlockInFlight = {nullptr, nullptr};
894  }
895 
896  // Module implementations are initialized the same way as a regular TU that
897  // imports one or more modules.
898  if (CXX20ModuleInits && Primary && Primary->isInterfaceOrPartition())
899  EmitCXXModuleInitFunc(Primary);
900  else
901  EmitCXXGlobalInitFunc();
902  EmitCXXGlobalCleanUpFunc();
903  registerGlobalDtorsWithAtExit();
904  EmitCXXThreadLocalInitFunc();
905  if (ObjCRuntime)
906  if (llvm::Function *ObjCInitFunction = ObjCRuntime->ModuleInitFunction())
907  AddGlobalCtor(ObjCInitFunction);
908  if (Context.getLangOpts().CUDA && CUDARuntime) {
909  if (llvm::Function *CudaCtorFunction = CUDARuntime->finalizeModule())
910  AddGlobalCtor(CudaCtorFunction);
911  }
912  if (OpenMPRuntime) {
913  OpenMPRuntime->createOffloadEntriesAndInfoMetadata();
914  OpenMPRuntime->clear();
915  }
916  if (PGOReader) {
917  getModule().setProfileSummary(
918  PGOReader->getSummary(/* UseCS */ false).getMD(VMContext),
919  llvm::ProfileSummary::PSK_Instr);
920  if (PGOStats.hasDiagnostics())
921  PGOStats.reportDiagnostics(getDiags(), getCodeGenOpts().MainFileName);
922  }
923  llvm::stable_sort(GlobalCtors, [](const Structor &L, const Structor &R) {
924  return L.LexOrder < R.LexOrder;
925  });
926  EmitCtorList(GlobalCtors, "llvm.global_ctors");
927  EmitCtorList(GlobalDtors, "llvm.global_dtors");
928  EmitGlobalAnnotations();
929  EmitStaticExternCAliases();
930  checkAliases();
931  EmitDeferredUnusedCoverageMappings();
932  CodeGenPGO(*this).setValueProfilingFlag(getModule());
933  CodeGenPGO(*this).setProfileVersion(getModule());
934  if (CoverageMapping)
935  CoverageMapping->emit();
936  if (CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso) {
937  CodeGenFunction(*this).EmitCfiCheckFail();
938  CodeGenFunction(*this).EmitCfiCheckStub();
939  }
940  if (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::KCFI))
941  finalizeKCFITypes();
942  emitAtAvailableLinkGuard();
943  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isWasm())
944  EmitMainVoidAlias();
945 
946  if (getTriple().isAMDGPU()) {
947  // Emit amdhsa_code_object_version module flag, which is code object version
948  // times 100.
949  if (getTarget().getTargetOpts().CodeObjectVersion !=
950  llvm::CodeObjectVersionKind::COV_None) {
951  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error,
952  "amdhsa_code_object_version",
953  getTarget().getTargetOpts().CodeObjectVersion);
954  }
955 
956  // Currently, "-mprintf-kind" option is only supported for HIP
957  if (LangOpts.HIP) {
958  auto *MDStr = llvm::MDString::get(
959  getLLVMContext(), (getTarget().getTargetOpts().AMDGPUPrintfKindVal ==
960  TargetOptions::AMDGPUPrintfKind::Hostcall)
961  ? "hostcall"
962  : "buffered");
963  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "amdgpu_printf_kind",
964  MDStr);
965  }
966  }
967 
968  // Emit a global array containing all external kernels or device variables
969  // used by host functions and mark it as used for CUDA/HIP. This is necessary
970  // to get kernels or device variables in archives linked in even if these
971  // kernels or device variables are only used in host functions.
972  if (!Context.CUDAExternalDeviceDeclODRUsedByHost.empty()) {
973  SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 8> UsedArray;
974  for (auto D : Context.CUDAExternalDeviceDeclODRUsedByHost) {
975  GlobalDecl GD;
976  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D))
977  GD = GlobalDecl(FD, KernelReferenceKind::Kernel);
978  else
979  GD = GlobalDecl(D);
980  UsedArray.push_back(llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
981  GetAddrOfGlobal(GD), Int8PtrTy));
982  }
983 
984  llvm::ArrayType *ATy = llvm::ArrayType::get(Int8PtrTy, UsedArray.size());
985 
986  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
987  getModule(), ATy, false, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
988  llvm::ConstantArray::get(ATy, UsedArray), "__clang_gpu_used_external");
989  addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
990  }
991  if (LangOpts.HIP && !getLangOpts().OffloadingNewDriver) {
992  // Emit a unique ID so that host and device binaries from the same
993  // compilation unit can be associated.
994  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
995  getModule(), Int8Ty, false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
996  llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Int8Ty),
997  "__hip_cuid_" + getContext().getCUIDHash());
998  addCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
999  }
1000  emitLLVMUsed();
1001  if (SanStats)
1002  SanStats->finish();
1003 
1004  if (CodeGenOpts.Autolink &&
1005  (Context.getLangOpts().Modules || !LinkerOptionsMetadata.empty())) {
1006  EmitModuleLinkOptions();
1007  }
1008 
1009  // On ELF we pass the dependent library specifiers directly to the linker
1010  // without manipulating them. This is in contrast to other platforms where
1011  // they are mapped to a specific linker option by the compiler. This
1012  // difference is a result of the greater variety of ELF linkers and the fact
1013  // that ELF linkers tend to handle libraries in a more complicated fashion
1014  // than on other platforms. This forces us to defer handling the dependent
1015  // libs to the linker.
1016  //
1017  // CUDA/HIP device and host libraries are different. Currently there is no
1018  // way to differentiate dependent libraries for host or device. Existing
1019  // usage of #pragma comment(lib, *) is intended for host libraries on
1020  // Windows. Therefore emit llvm.dependent-libraries only for host.
1021  if (!ELFDependentLibraries.empty() && !Context.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
1022  auto *NMD = getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata("llvm.dependent-libraries");
1023  for (auto *MD : ELFDependentLibraries)
1024  NMD->addOperand(MD);
1025  }
1026 
1027  // Record mregparm value now so it is visible through rest of codegen.
1028  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::x86)
1029  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "NumRegisterParameters",
1030  CodeGenOpts.NumRegisterParameters);
1031 
1032  if (CodeGenOpts.DwarfVersion) {
1033  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Max, "Dwarf Version",
1034  CodeGenOpts.DwarfVersion);
1035  }
1036 
1037  if (CodeGenOpts.Dwarf64)
1038  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Max, "DWARF64", 1);
1039 
1040  if (Context.getLangOpts().SemanticInterposition)
1041  // Require various optimization to respect semantic interposition.
1042  getModule().setSemanticInterposition(true);
1043 
1044  if (CodeGenOpts.EmitCodeView) {
1045  // Indicate that we want CodeView in the metadata.
1046  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "CodeView", 1);
1047  }
1048  if (CodeGenOpts.CodeViewGHash) {
1049  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "CodeViewGHash", 1);
1050  }
1051  if (CodeGenOpts.ControlFlowGuard) {
1052  // Function ID tables and checks for Control Flow Guard (cfguard=2).
1053  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "cfguard", 2);
1054  } else if (CodeGenOpts.ControlFlowGuardNoChecks) {
1055  // Function ID tables for Control Flow Guard (cfguard=1).
1056  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "cfguard", 1);
1057  }
1058  if (CodeGenOpts.EHContGuard) {
1059  // Function ID tables for EH Continuation Guard.
1060  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "ehcontguard", 1);
1061  }
1062  if (Context.getLangOpts().Kernel) {
1063  // Note if we are compiling with /kernel.
1064  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "ms-kernel", 1);
1065  }
1066  if (CodeGenOpts.OptimizationLevel > 0 && CodeGenOpts.StrictVTablePointers) {
1067  // We don't support LTO with 2 with different StrictVTablePointers
1068  // FIXME: we could support it by stripping all the information introduced
1069  // by StrictVTablePointers.
1070 
1071  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "StrictVTablePointers",1);
1072 
1073  llvm::Metadata *Ops[2] = {
1074  llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "StrictVTablePointers"),
1075  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1076  llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(VMContext), 1))};
1077 
1078  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Require,
1079  "StrictVTablePointersRequirement",
1080  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, Ops));
1081  }
1082  if (getModuleDebugInfo())
1083  // We support a single version in the linked module. The LLVM
1084  // parser will drop debug info with a different version number
1085  // (and warn about it, too).
1086  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "Debug Info Version",
1087  llvm::DEBUG_METADATA_VERSION);
1088 
1089  // We need to record the widths of enums and wchar_t, so that we can generate
1090  // the correct build attributes in the ARM backend. wchar_size is also used by
1091  // TargetLibraryInfo.
1092  uint64_t WCharWidth =
1093  Context.getTypeSizeInChars(Context.getWideCharType()).getQuantity();
1094  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "wchar_size", WCharWidth);
1095 
1096  if (getTriple().isOSzOS()) {
1097  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning,
1098  "zos_product_major_version",
1099  uint32_t(CLANG_VERSION_MAJOR));
1100  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning,
1101  "zos_product_minor_version",
1102  uint32_t(CLANG_VERSION_MINOR));
1103  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "zos_product_patchlevel",
1104  uint32_t(CLANG_VERSION_PATCHLEVEL));
1105  std::string ProductId = getClangVendor() + "clang";
1106  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "zos_product_id",
1107  llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, ProductId));
1108 
1109  // Record the language because we need it for the PPA2.
1110  StringRef lang_str = languageToString(
1111  LangStandard::getLangStandardForKind(LangOpts.LangStd).Language);
1112  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "zos_cu_language",
1113  llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, lang_str));
1114 
1115  time_t TT = PreprocessorOpts.SourceDateEpoch
1116  ? *PreprocessorOpts.SourceDateEpoch
1117  : std::time(nullptr);
1118  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Max, "zos_translation_time",
1119  static_cast<uint64_t>(TT));
1120 
1121  // Multiple modes will be supported here.
1122  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "zos_le_char_mode",
1123  llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "ascii"));
1124  }
1125 
1126  llvm::Triple T = Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple();
1127  if (T.isARM() || T.isThumb()) {
1128  // The minimum width of an enum in bytes
1129  uint64_t EnumWidth = Context.getLangOpts().ShortEnums ? 1 : 4;
1130  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "min_enum_size", EnumWidth);
1131  }
1132 
1133  if (T.isRISCV()) {
1134  StringRef ABIStr = Target.getABI();
1135  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
1136  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "target-abi",
1137  llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, ABIStr));
1138 
1139  // Add the canonical ISA string as metadata so the backend can set the ELF
1140  // attributes correctly. We use AppendUnique so LTO will keep all of the
1141  // unique ISA strings that were linked together.
1142  const std::vector<std::string> &Features =
1143  getTarget().getTargetOpts().Features;
1144  auto ParseResult =
1145  llvm::RISCVISAInfo::parseFeatures(T.isRISCV64() ? 64 : 32, Features);
1146  if (!errorToBool(ParseResult.takeError()))
1147  getModule().addModuleFlag(
1148  llvm::Module::AppendUnique, "riscv-isa",
1149  llvm::MDNode::get(
1150  Ctx, llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, (*ParseResult)->toString())));
1151  }
1152 
1153  if (CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso) {
1154  // Indicate that we want cross-DSO control flow integrity checks.
1155  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "Cross-DSO CFI", 1);
1156  }
1157 
1158  if (CodeGenOpts.WholeProgramVTables) {
1159  // Indicate whether VFE was enabled for this module, so that the
1160  // vcall_visibility metadata added under whole program vtables is handled
1161  // appropriately in the optimizer.
1162  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "Virtual Function Elim",
1163  CodeGenOpts.VirtualFunctionElimination);
1164  }
1165 
1166  if (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFIICall)) {
1167  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override,
1168  "CFI Canonical Jump Tables",
1169  CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCanonicalJumpTables);
1170  }
1171 
1172  if (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::KCFI)) {
1173  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "kcfi", 1);
1174  // KCFI assumes patchable-function-prefix is the same for all indirectly
1175  // called functions. Store the expected offset for code generation.
1176  if (CodeGenOpts.PatchableFunctionEntryOffset)
1177  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "kcfi-offset",
1178  CodeGenOpts.PatchableFunctionEntryOffset);
1179  }
1180 
1181  if (CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionReturn &&
1182  Target.checkCFProtectionReturnSupported(getDiags())) {
1183  // Indicate that we want to instrument return control flow protection.
1184  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Min, "cf-protection-return",
1185  1);
1186  }
1187 
1188  if (CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionBranch &&
1189  Target.checkCFProtectionBranchSupported(getDiags())) {
1190  // Indicate that we want to instrument branch control flow protection.
1191  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Min, "cf-protection-branch",
1192  1);
1193  }
1194 
1195  if (CodeGenOpts.FunctionReturnThunks)
1196  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "function_return_thunk_extern", 1);
1197 
1198  if (CodeGenOpts.IndirectBranchCSPrefix)
1199  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "indirect_branch_cs_prefix", 1);
1200 
1201  // Add module metadata for return address signing (ignoring
1202  // non-leaf/all) and stack tagging. These are actually turned on by function
1203  // attributes, but we use module metadata to emit build attributes. This is
1204  // needed for LTO, where the function attributes are inside bitcode
1205  // serialised into a global variable by the time build attributes are
1206  // emitted, so we can't access them. LTO objects could be compiled with
1207  // different flags therefore module flags are set to "Min" behavior to achieve
1208  // the same end result of the normal build where e.g BTI is off if any object
1209  // doesn't support it.
1210  if (Context.getTargetInfo().hasFeature("ptrauth") &&
1211  LangOpts.getSignReturnAddressScope() !=
1212  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressScopeKind::None)
1213  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override,
1214  "sign-return-address-buildattr", 1);
1215  if (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::MemtagStack))
1216  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override,
1217  "tag-stack-memory-buildattr", 1);
1218 
1219  if (T.isARM() || T.isThumb() || T.isAArch64()) {
1220  if (LangOpts.BranchTargetEnforcement)
1221  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Min, "branch-target-enforcement",
1222  1);
1223  if (LangOpts.BranchProtectionPAuthLR)
1224  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Min, "branch-protection-pauth-lr",
1225  1);
1226  if (LangOpts.GuardedControlStack)
1227  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Min, "guarded-control-stack", 1);
1228  if (LangOpts.hasSignReturnAddress())
1229  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Min, "sign-return-address", 1);
1230  if (LangOpts.isSignReturnAddressScopeAll())
1231  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Min, "sign-return-address-all",
1232  1);
1233  if (!LangOpts.isSignReturnAddressWithAKey())
1234  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Min,
1235  "sign-return-address-with-bkey", 1);
1236  }
1237 
1238  if (CodeGenOpts.StackClashProtector)
1239  getModule().addModuleFlag(
1240  llvm::Module::Override, "probe-stack",
1241  llvm::MDString::get(TheModule.getContext(), "inline-asm"));
1242 
1243  if (CodeGenOpts.StackProbeSize && CodeGenOpts.StackProbeSize != 4096)
1244  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Min, "stack-probe-size",
1245  CodeGenOpts.StackProbeSize);
1246 
1247  if (!CodeGenOpts.MemoryProfileOutput.empty()) {
1248  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
1249  getModule().addModuleFlag(
1250  llvm::Module::Error, "MemProfProfileFilename",
1251  llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, CodeGenOpts.MemoryProfileOutput));
1252  }
1253 
1254  if ((LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice || LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) && getTriple().isNVPTX()) {
1255  // Indicate whether __nvvm_reflect should be configured to flush denormal
1256  // floating point values to 0. (This corresponds to its "__CUDA_FTZ"
1257  // property.)
1258  getModule().addModuleFlag(
1259  llvm::Module::Max, "nvvm-reflect-ftz",
1260  (CodeGenOpts.FP32DenormalMode.Output != llvm::DenormalMode::IEEE) ||
1261  (CodeGenOpts.FPDenormalMode.Output != llvm::DenormalMode::IEEE));
1262  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Max, "nvvm-reflect-prec-sqrt",
1263  getTarget().getTargetOpts().NVVMCudaPrecSqrt);
1264  }
1265 
1266  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && LangOpts.SYCLIsNativeCPU) {
1267  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "is-native-cpu", 1);
1268  }
1269 
1270  if (LangOpts.EHAsynch)
1271  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Warning, "eh-asynch", 1);
1272 
1273  // Indicate whether this Module was compiled with -fopenmp
1274  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && !getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd)
1275  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Max, "openmp", LangOpts.OpenMP);
1276  if (getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice)
1277  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Max, "openmp-device",
1278  LangOpts.OpenMP);
1279 
1280  // Emit OpenCL specific module metadata: OpenCL/SPIR version.
1281  if (LangOpts.OpenCL || (LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice && getTriple().isSPIRV())) {
1282  EmitOpenCLMetadata();
1283  // Emit SPIR version.
1284  if (getTriple().isSPIR()) {
1285  // SPIR v2.0 s2.12 - The SPIR version used by the module is stored in the
1286  // opencl.spir.version named metadata.
1287  // C++ for OpenCL has a distinct mapping for version compatibility with
1288  // OpenCL.
1289  auto Version = LangOpts.getOpenCLCompatibleVersion();
1290  llvm::Metadata *SPIRVerElts[] = {
1291  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1292  Int32Ty, Version / 100)),
1293  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1294  Int32Ty, (Version / 100 > 1) ? 0 : 2))};
1295  llvm::NamedMDNode *SPIRVerMD =
1296  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("opencl.spir.version");
1297  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
1298  SPIRVerMD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, SPIRVerElts));
1299  }
1300  }
1301 
1302  // Emit SYCL specific module metadata: OpenCL/SPIR version, OpenCL language,
1303  // metadata for optional features (device aspects).
1304  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
1305  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
1306  llvm::Metadata *SPIRVerElts[] = {
1307  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 1)),
1308  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 2))};
1309  llvm::NamedMDNode *SPIRVerMD =
1310  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("opencl.spir.version");
1311  SPIRVerMD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, SPIRVerElts));
1312  // We are trying to look like OpenCL C++ for SPIR-V translator.
1313  // 4 - OpenCL_CPP, 100000 - OpenCL C++ version 1.0
1314  // 0 - ESIMD, if any kernel or function is an explicit SIMD one
1315  int Lang = llvm::any_of(TheModule,
1316  [](const auto &F) {
1317  return F.getMetadata("sycl_explicit_simd");
1318  })
1319  ? 0
1320  : 4;
1321 
1322  llvm::Metadata *SPIRVSourceElts[] = {
1323  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Lang)),
1324  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, 100000))};
1325  llvm::NamedMDNode *SPIRVSourceMD =
1326  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("spirv.Source");
1327  SPIRVSourceMD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, SPIRVSourceElts));
1328 
1329  // Emit type name with list of associated device aspects.
1330  if (TypesWithAspects.size() > 0) {
1331  llvm::NamedMDNode *AspectsMD =
1332  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("sycl_types_that_use_aspects");
1333  for (const auto &Type : TypesWithAspects) {
1334  StringRef Name = Type.first;
1335  const RecordDecl *RD = Type.second;
1336  AspectsMD->addOperand(getAspectsMD(Context, TheModule.getContext(),
1337  Name,
1338  RD->getAttr<SYCLUsesAspectsAttr>()));
1339  }
1340  }
1341 
1342  // Emit metadata for all aspects defined in the aspects enum.
1343  if (AspectsEnumDecl) {
1344  llvm::NamedMDNode *AspectEnumValsMD =
1345  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("sycl_aspects");
1346  for (const EnumConstantDecl *ECD : AspectsEnumDecl->enumerators())
1347  AspectEnumValsMD->addOperand(
1348  getAspectEnumValueMD(Context, TheModule.getContext(), ECD));
1349  }
1350  }
1351 
1352  // HLSL related end of code gen work items.
1353  if (LangOpts.HLSL)
1354  getHLSLRuntime().finishCodeGen();
1355 
1356  if (uint32_t PLevel = Context.getLangOpts().PICLevel) {
1357  assert(PLevel < 3 && "Invalid PIC Level");
1358  getModule().setPICLevel(static_cast<llvm::PICLevel::Level>(PLevel));
1359  if (Context.getLangOpts().PIE)
1360  getModule().setPIELevel(static_cast<llvm::PIELevel::Level>(PLevel));
1361  }
1362 
1363  if (getCodeGenOpts().CodeModel.size() > 0) {
1364  unsigned CM = llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(getCodeGenOpts().CodeModel)
1365  .Case("tiny", llvm::CodeModel::Tiny)
1366  .Case("small", llvm::CodeModel::Small)
1367  .Case("kernel", llvm::CodeModel::Kernel)
1368  .Case("medium", llvm::CodeModel::Medium)
1369  .Case("large", llvm::CodeModel::Large)
1370  .Default(~0u);
1371  if (CM != ~0u) {
1372  llvm::CodeModel::Model codeModel = static_cast<llvm::CodeModel::Model>(CM);
1373  getModule().setCodeModel(codeModel);
1374 
1375  if ((CM == llvm::CodeModel::Medium || CM == llvm::CodeModel::Large) &&
1376  Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() ==
1377  llvm::Triple::x86_64) {
1378  getModule().setLargeDataThreshold(getCodeGenOpts().LargeDataThreshold);
1379  }
1380  }
1381  }
1382 
1383  if (CodeGenOpts.NoPLT)
1384  getModule().setRtLibUseGOT();
1385  if (getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() &&
1386  CodeGenOpts.DirectAccessExternalData !=
1387  getModule().getDirectAccessExternalData()) {
1388  getModule().setDirectAccessExternalData(
1389  CodeGenOpts.DirectAccessExternalData);
1390  }
1391  if (CodeGenOpts.UnwindTables)
1392  getModule().setUwtable(llvm::UWTableKind(CodeGenOpts.UnwindTables));
1393 
1394  switch (CodeGenOpts.getFramePointer()) {
1395  case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::None:
1396  // 0 ("none") is the default.
1397  break;
1398  case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::NonLeaf:
1399  getModule().setFramePointer(llvm::FramePointerKind::NonLeaf);
1400  break;
1401  case CodeGenOptions::FramePointerKind::All:
1402  getModule().setFramePointer(llvm::FramePointerKind::All);
1403  break;
1404  }
1405 
1406  SimplifyPersonality();
1407 
1408  if (getCodeGenOpts().EmitDeclMetadata)
1409  EmitDeclMetadata();
1410 
1411  if (getCodeGenOpts().CoverageNotesFile.size() ||
1412  getCodeGenOpts().CoverageDataFile.size())
1413  EmitCoverageFile();
1414 
1415  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
1416  DI->finalize();
1417 
1418  if (getCodeGenOpts().EmitVersionIdentMetadata)
1419  EmitVersionIdentMetadata();
1420 
1421  if (!getCodeGenOpts().RecordCommandLine.empty())
1422  EmitCommandLineMetadata();
1423 
1424  if (!getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuard.empty())
1425  getModule().setStackProtectorGuard(getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuard);
1426  if (!getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuardReg.empty())
1427  getModule().setStackProtectorGuardReg(
1428  getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuardReg);
1429  if (!getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuardSymbol.empty())
1430  getModule().setStackProtectorGuardSymbol(
1431  getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuardSymbol);
1432  if (getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuardOffset != INT_MAX)
1433  getModule().setStackProtectorGuardOffset(
1434  getCodeGenOpts().StackProtectorGuardOffset);
1435  if (getCodeGenOpts().StackAlignment)
1436  getModule().setOverrideStackAlignment(getCodeGenOpts().StackAlignment);
1437  if (getCodeGenOpts().SkipRaxSetup)
1438  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "SkipRaxSetup", 1);
1439  if (getLangOpts().RegCall4)
1440  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Override, "RegCallv4", 1);
1441 
1442  if (getContext().getTargetInfo().getMaxTLSAlign())
1443  getModule().addModuleFlag(llvm::Module::Error, "MaxTLSAlign",
1444  getContext().getTargetInfo().getMaxTLSAlign());
1445 
1446  getTargetCodeGenInfo().emitTargetGlobals(*this);
1447 
1448  getTargetCodeGenInfo().emitTargetMetadata(*this, MangledDeclNames);
1449 
1450  EmitBackendOptionsMetadata(getCodeGenOpts());
1451 
1452  // If there is device offloading code embed it in the host now.
1453  EmbedObject(&getModule(), CodeGenOpts, getDiags());
1454 
1455  // Set visibility from DLL storage class
1456  // We do this at the end of LLVM IR generation; after any operation
1457  // that might affect the DLL storage class or the visibility, and
1458  // before anything that might act on these.
1459  setVisibilityFromDLLStorageClass(LangOpts, getModule());
1460 }

1462 void CodeGenModule::EmitOpenCLMetadata() {
1463  // SPIR v2.0 s2.13 - The OpenCL version used by the module is stored in the
1464  // opencl.ocl.version named metadata node.
1465  // C++ for OpenCL has a distinct mapping for versions compatibile with OpenCL.
1466  auto Version = LangOpts.getOpenCLCompatibleVersion();
1467  llvm::Metadata *OCLVerElts[] = {
1468  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1469  Int32Ty, Version / 100)),
1470  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1471  Int32Ty, (Version % 100) / 10))};
1472  llvm::NamedMDNode *OCLVerMD =
1473  TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("opencl.ocl.version");
1474  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
1475  OCLVerMD->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, OCLVerElts));
1476 }

1502 TBAAAccessInfo CodeGenModule::getTBAAAccessInfo(QualType AccessType) {
1503  if (!TBAA)
1504  return TBAAAccessInfo();
1505  if (getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) {
1506  // As CUDA builtin surface/texture types are replaced, skip generating TBAA
1507  // access info.
1508  if (AccessType->isCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceType()) {
1509  if (getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceDeviceType() !=
1510  nullptr)
1511  return TBAAAccessInfo();
1512  } else if (AccessType->isCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureType()) {
1513  if (getTargetCodeGenInfo().getCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureDeviceType() !=
1514  nullptr)
1515  return TBAAAccessInfo();
1516  }
1517  }
1518  return TBAA->getAccessInfo(AccessType);
1519 }

1586 /// ErrorUnsupported - Print out an error that codegen doesn't support the

1588 void CodeGenModule::ErrorUnsupported(const Stmt *S, const char *Type) {

1590  "cannot compile this %0 yet");

1608 
1609 void CodeGenModule::setGlobalVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
1610  const NamedDecl *D) const {
1611  // Internal definitions always have default visibility.
1612  if (GV->hasLocalLinkage()) {
1613  GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility);
1614  return;
1615  }
1616  if (!D)
1617  return;
1618 
1619  // Set visibility for definitions, and for declarations if requested globally
1620  // or set explicitly.
1621  LinkageInfo LV = D->getLinkageAndVisibility();
1622 
1623  // OpenMP declare target variables must be visible to the host so they can
1624  // be registered. We require protected visibility unless the variable has
1625  // the DT_nohost modifier and does not need to be registered.
1626  if (Context.getLangOpts().OpenMP &&
1627  Context.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice && isa<VarDecl>(D) &&
1628  D->hasAttr<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr>() &&
1629  D->getAttr<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr>()->getDevType() !=
1630  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::DT_NoHost &&
1631  LV.getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility) {
1632  GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::ProtectedVisibility);
1633  return;
1634  }
1635 
1636  if (GV->hasDLLExportStorageClass() || GV->hasDLLImportStorageClass()) {
1637  // Reject incompatible dlllstorage and visibility annotations.
1638  if (!LV.isVisibilityExplicit())
1639  return;
1640  if (GV->hasDLLExportStorageClass()) {
1641  if (LV.getVisibility() == HiddenVisibility)
1642  getDiags().Report(D->getLocation(),
1643  diag::err_hidden_visibility_dllexport);
1644  } else if (LV.getVisibility() != DefaultVisibility) {
1645  getDiags().Report(D->getLocation(),
1646  diag::err_non_default_visibility_dllimport);
1647  }
1648  return;
1649  }
1650 
1651  if (LV.isVisibilityExplicit() || getLangOpts().SetVisibilityForExternDecls ||
1652  !GV->isDeclarationForLinker())
1653  GV->setVisibility(GetLLVMVisibility(LV.getVisibility()));
1654 }
1655 
1656 static bool shouldAssumeDSOLocal(const CodeGenModule &CGM,
1657  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
1658  if (GV->hasLocalLinkage())
1659  return true;
1660 
1661  if (!GV->hasDefaultVisibility() && !GV->hasExternalWeakLinkage())
1662  return true;
1663 
1664  // DLLImport explicitly marks the GV as external.
1665  if (GV->hasDLLImportStorageClass())
1666  return false;
1667 
1668  const llvm::Triple &TT = CGM.getTriple();
1669  const auto &CGOpts = CGM.getCodeGenOpts();
1670  if (TT.isWindowsGNUEnvironment()) {
1671  // In MinGW, variables without DLLImport can still be automatically
1672  // imported from a DLL by the linker; don't mark variables that
1673  // potentially could come from another DLL as DSO local.
1674 
1675  // With EmulatedTLS, TLS variables can be autoimported from other DLLs
1676  // (and this actually happens in the public interface of libstdc++), so
1677  // such variables can't be marked as DSO local. (Native TLS variables
1678  // can't be dllimported at all, though.)
1679  if (GV->isDeclarationForLinker() && isa<llvm::GlobalVariable>(GV) &&
1680  (!GV->isThreadLocal() || CGM.getCodeGenOpts().EmulatedTLS) &&
1681  CGOpts.AutoImport)
1682  return false;
1683  }
1684 
1685  // On COFF, don't mark 'extern_weak' symbols as DSO local. If these symbols
1686  // remain unresolved in the link, they can be resolved to zero, which is
1687  // outside the current DSO.
1688  if (TT.isOSBinFormatCOFF() && GV->hasExternalWeakLinkage())
1689  return false;
1690 
1691  // Every other GV is local on COFF.
1692  // Make an exception for windows OS in the triple: Some firmware builds use
1693  // *-win32-macho triples. This (accidentally?) produced windows relocations
1694  // without GOT tables in older clang versions; Keep this behaviour.
1695  // FIXME: even thread local variables?
1696  if (TT.isOSBinFormatCOFF() || (TT.isOSWindows() && TT.isOSBinFormatMachO()))
1697  return true;
1698 
1699  // Only handle COFF and ELF for now.
1700  if (!TT.isOSBinFormatELF())
1701  return false;
1702 
1703  // If this is not an executable, don't assume anything is local.
1704  llvm::Reloc::Model RM = CGOpts.RelocationModel;
1705  const auto &LOpts = CGM.getLangOpts();
1706  if (RM != llvm::Reloc::Static && !LOpts.PIE) {
1707  // On ELF, if -fno-semantic-interposition is specified and the target
1708  // supports local aliases, there will be neither CC1
1709  // -fsemantic-interposition nor -fhalf-no-semantic-interposition. Set
1710  // dso_local on the function if using a local alias is preferable (can avoid
1711  // PLT indirection).
1712  if (!(isa<llvm::Function>(GV) && GV->canBenefitFromLocalAlias()))
1713  return false;
1714  return !(CGM.getLangOpts().SemanticInterposition ||
1715  CGM.getLangOpts().HalfNoSemanticInterposition);
1716  }
1717 
1718  // A definition cannot be preempted from an executable.
1719  if (!GV->isDeclarationForLinker())
1720  return true;
1721 
1722  // Most PIC code sequences that assume that a symbol is local cannot produce a
1723  // 0 if it turns out the symbol is undefined. While this is ABI and relocation
1724  // depended, it seems worth it to handle it here.
1725  if (RM == llvm::Reloc::PIC_ && GV->hasExternalWeakLinkage())
1726  return false;
1727 
1728  // PowerPC64 prefers TOC indirection to avoid copy relocations.
1729  if (TT.isPPC64())
1730  return false;
1731 
1732  if (CGOpts.DirectAccessExternalData) {
1733  // If -fdirect-access-external-data (default for -fno-pic), set dso_local
1734  // for non-thread-local variables. If the symbol is not defined in the
1735  // executable, a copy relocation will be needed at link time. dso_local is
1736  // excluded for thread-local variables because they generally don't support
1737  // copy relocations.
1738  if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(GV))
1739  if (!Var->isThreadLocal())
1740  return true;
1741 
1742  // -fno-pic sets dso_local on a function declaration to allow direct
1743  // accesses when taking its address (similar to a data symbol). If the
1744  // function is not defined in the executable, a canonical PLT entry will be
1745  // needed at link time. -fno-direct-access-external-data can avoid the
1746  // canonical PLT entry. We don't generalize this condition to -fpie/-fpic as
1747  // it could just cause trouble without providing perceptible benefits.
1748  if (isa<llvm::Function>(GV) && !CGOpts.NoPLT && RM == llvm::Reloc::Static)
1749  return true;
1750  }
1751 
1752  // If we can use copy relocations we can assume it is local.
1753 
1754  // Otherwise don't assume it is local.
1755  return false;
1756 }
1757 
1758 void CodeGenModule::setDSOLocal(llvm::GlobalValue *GV) const {
1759  GV->setDSOLocal(shouldAssumeDSOLocal(*this, GV));
1760 }

1762 void CodeGenModule::setDLLImportDLLExport(llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
1763  GlobalDecl GD) const {
1764  const auto *D = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(GD.getDecl());
1765  // C++ destructors have a few C++ ABI specific special cases.
1766  if (const auto *Dtor = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXDestructorDecl>(D)) {
1767  getCXXABI().setCXXDestructorDLLStorage(GV, Dtor, GD.getDtorType());
1768  return;
1769  }
1770  setDLLImportDLLExport(GV, D);
1771 }

1804 static llvm::GlobalVariable::ThreadLocalMode GetLLVMTLSModel(StringRef S) {
1805  return llvm::StringSwitch<llvm::GlobalVariable::ThreadLocalMode>(S)
1806  .Case("global-dynamic", llvm::GlobalVariable::GeneralDynamicTLSModel)
1807  .Case("local-dynamic", llvm::GlobalVariable::LocalDynamicTLSModel)
1808  .Case("initial-exec", llvm::GlobalVariable::InitialExecTLSModel)
1809  .Case("local-exec", llvm::GlobalVariable::LocalExecTLSModel);
1810 }
1811 
1812 llvm::GlobalVariable::ThreadLocalMode
1813 CodeGenModule::GetDefaultLLVMTLSModel() const {
1814  switch (CodeGenOpts.getDefaultTLSModel()) {
1815  case CodeGenOptions::GeneralDynamicTLSModel:
1816  return llvm::GlobalVariable::GeneralDynamicTLSModel;
1817  case CodeGenOptions::LocalDynamicTLSModel:
1818  return llvm::GlobalVariable::LocalDynamicTLSModel;
1819  case CodeGenOptions::InitialExecTLSModel:
1820  return llvm::GlobalVariable::InitialExecTLSModel;
1821  case CodeGenOptions::LocalExecTLSModel:
1822  return llvm::GlobalVariable::LocalExecTLSModel;
1823  }
1824  llvm_unreachable("Invalid TLS model!");
1825 }

1827 void CodeGenModule::setTLSMode(llvm::GlobalValue *GV, const VarDecl &D) const {
1828  assert(D.getTLSKind() && "setting TLS mode on non-TLS var!");
1829 
1830  llvm::GlobalValue::ThreadLocalMode TLM;
1831  TLM = GetDefaultLLVMTLSModel();
1832 
1833  // Override the TLS model if it is explicitly specified.
1834  if (const TLSModelAttr *Attr = D.getAttr<TLSModelAttr>()) {
1835  TLM = GetLLVMTLSModel(Attr->getModel());
1836  }
1837 
1838  GV->setThreadLocalMode(TLM);
1839 }

1841 static std::string getCPUSpecificMangling(const CodeGenModule &CGM,
1842  StringRef Name) {
1843  const TargetInfo &Target = CGM.getTarget();
1844  return (Twine('.') + Twine(Target.CPUSpecificManglingCharacter(Name))).str();
1845 }
1846 
1847 static void AppendCPUSpecificCPUDispatchMangling(const CodeGenModule &CGM,
1848  const CPUSpecificAttr *Attr,
1849  unsigned CPUIndex,
1850  raw_ostream &Out) {
1851  // cpu_specific gets the current name, dispatch gets the resolver if IFunc is
1852  // supported.
1853  if (Attr)
1854  Out << getCPUSpecificMangling(CGM, Attr->getCPUName(CPUIndex)->getName());
1855  else if (CGM.getTarget().supportsIFunc())
1856  Out << ".resolver";
1857 }
1858 
1859 // Returns true if GD is a function decl with internal linkage and
1860 // needs a unique suffix after the mangled name.
1861 static bool isUniqueInternalLinkageDecl(GlobalDecl GD,
1862  CodeGenModule &CGM) {
1863  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
1864  return !CGM.getModuleNameHash().empty() && isa<FunctionDecl>(D) &&
1865  (CGM.getFunctionLinkage(GD) == llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage);
1866 }
1867 
1868 static std::string getMangledNameImpl(CodeGenModule &CGM, GlobalDecl GD,
1869  const NamedDecl *ND,
1870  bool OmitMultiVersionMangling = false) {
1871  SmallString<256> Buffer;
1872  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
1873  MangleContext &MC = CGM.getCXXABI().getMangleContext();
1874  if (!CGM.getModuleNameHash().empty())
1875  MC.needsUniqueInternalLinkageNames();
1876  bool ShouldMangle = MC.shouldMangleDeclName(ND);
1877  if (ShouldMangle)
1878  MC.mangleName(GD.getWithDecl(ND), Out);
1879  else {
1880  IdentifierInfo *II = ND->getIdentifier();
1881  assert(II && "Attempt to mangle unnamed decl.");
1882  const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND);
1883 
1884  if (FD &&
1885  FD->getType()->castAs<FunctionType>()->getCallConv() == CC_X86RegCall) {
1886  if (CGM.getLangOpts().RegCall4)
1887  Out << "__regcall4__" << II->getName();
1888  else
1889  Out << "__regcall3__" << II->getName();
1890  } else if (FD && FD->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>() &&
1891  GD.getKernelReferenceKind() == KernelReferenceKind::Stub) {
1892  Out << "__device_stub__" << II->getName();
1893  } else {
1894  Out << II->getName();
1895  }
1896  }
1897 
1898  // Check if the module name hash should be appended for internal linkage
1899  // symbols. This should come before multi-version target suffixes are
1900  // appended. This is to keep the name and module hash suffix of the
1901  // internal linkage function together. The unique suffix should only be
1902  // added when name mangling is done to make sure that the final name can
1903  // be properly demangled. For example, for C functions without prototypes,
1904  // name mangling is not done and the unique suffix should not be appeneded
1905  // then.
1906  if (ShouldMangle && isUniqueInternalLinkageDecl(GD, CGM)) {
1907  assert(CGM.getCodeGenOpts().UniqueInternalLinkageNames &&
1908  "Hash computed when not explicitly requested");
1909  Out << CGM.getModuleNameHash();
1910  }
1911 
1912  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(ND))
1913  if (FD->isMultiVersion() && !OmitMultiVersionMangling) {
1914  switch (FD->getMultiVersionKind()) {
1915  case MultiVersionKind::CPUDispatch:
1916  case MultiVersionKind::CPUSpecific:
1917  AppendCPUSpecificCPUDispatchMangling(CGM,
1918  FD->getAttr<CPUSpecificAttr>(),
1919  GD.getMultiVersionIndex(), Out);
1920  break;
1921  case MultiVersionKind::Target: {
1922  auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<TargetAttr>();
1923  const ABIInfo &Info = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getABIInfo();
1924  Info.appendAttributeMangling(Attr, Out);
1925  break;
1926  }
1927  case MultiVersionKind::TargetVersion: {
1928  auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<TargetVersionAttr>();
1929  const ABIInfo &Info = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getABIInfo();
1930  Info.appendAttributeMangling(Attr, Out);
1931  break;
1932  }
1933  case MultiVersionKind::TargetClones: {
1934  auto *Attr = FD->getAttr<TargetClonesAttr>();
1935  unsigned Index = GD.getMultiVersionIndex();
1936  const ABIInfo &Info = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getABIInfo();
1937  Info.appendAttributeMangling(Attr, Index, Out);
1938  break;
1939  }
1940  case MultiVersionKind::None:
1941  llvm_unreachable("None multiversion type isn't valid here");
1942  }
1943  }
1944 
1945  // Make unique name for device side static file-scope variable for HIP.
1946  if (CGM.getContext().shouldExternalize(ND) &&
1947  CGM.getLangOpts().GPURelocatableDeviceCode &&
1948  CGM.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice)
1949  CGM.printPostfixForExternalizedDecl(Out, ND);
1950 
1951  return std::string(Out.str());
1952 }
1953 
1954 void CodeGenModule::UpdateMultiVersionNames(GlobalDecl GD,
1955  const FunctionDecl *FD,
1956  StringRef &CurName) {
1957  if (!FD->isMultiVersion())
1958  return;
1959 
1960  // Get the name of what this would be without the 'target' attribute. This
1961  // allows us to lookup the version that was emitted when this wasn't a
1962  // multiversion function.
1963  std::string NonTargetName =
1964  getMangledNameImpl(*this, GD, FD, /*OmitMultiVersionMangling=*/true);
1965  GlobalDecl OtherGD;
1966  if (lookupRepresentativeDecl(NonTargetName, OtherGD)) {
1967  assert(OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl()
1968  .getDecl()
1969  ->getAsFunction()
1970  ->isMultiVersion() &&
1971  "Other GD should now be a multiversioned function");
1972  // OtherFD is the version of this function that was mangled BEFORE
1973  // becoming a MultiVersion function. It potentially needs to be updated.
1974  const FunctionDecl *OtherFD = OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl()
1975  .getDecl()
1976  ->getAsFunction()
1977  ->getMostRecentDecl();
1978  std::string OtherName = getMangledNameImpl(*this, OtherGD, OtherFD);
1979  // This is so that if the initial version was already the 'default'
1980  // version, we don't try to update it.
1981  if (OtherName != NonTargetName) {
1982  // Remove instead of erase, since others may have stored the StringRef
1983  // to this.
1984  const auto ExistingRecord = Manglings.find(NonTargetName);
1985  if (ExistingRecord != std::end(Manglings))
1986  Manglings.remove(&(*ExistingRecord));
1987  auto Result = Manglings.insert(std::make_pair(OtherName, OtherGD));
1988  StringRef OtherNameRef = MangledDeclNames[OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl()] =
1989  Result.first->first();
1990  // If this is the current decl is being created, make sure we update the name.
1991  if (GD.getCanonicalDecl() == OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl())
1992  CurName = OtherNameRef;
1993  if (llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(NonTargetName))
1994  Entry->setName(OtherName);
1995  }
1996  }
1997 }
1998 
1999 StringRef CodeGenModule::getMangledName(GlobalDecl GD) {
2000  GlobalDecl CanonicalGD = GD.getCanonicalDecl();
2001 
2002  // Some ABIs don't have constructor variants. Make sure that base and
2003  // complete constructors get mangled the same.
2004  if (const auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(CanonicalGD.getDecl())) {
2005  if (!getTarget().getCXXABI().hasConstructorVariants()) {
2006  CXXCtorType OrigCtorType = GD.getCtorType();
2007  assert(OrigCtorType == Ctor_Base || OrigCtorType == Ctor_Complete);
2008  if (OrigCtorType == Ctor_Base)
2009  CanonicalGD = GlobalDecl(CD, Ctor_Complete);
2010  }
2011  }
2012 
2013  // In CUDA/HIP device compilation with -fgpu-rdc, the mangled name of a
2014  // static device variable depends on whether the variable is referenced by
2015  // a host or device host function. Therefore the mangled name cannot be
2016  // cached.
2017  if (!LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice || !getContext().mayExternalize(GD.getDecl())) {
2018  auto FoundName = MangledDeclNames.find(CanonicalGD);
2019  if (FoundName != MangledDeclNames.end())
2020  return FoundName->second;
2021  }
2022 
2023  // Keep the first result in the case of a mangling collision.
2024  const auto *ND = cast<NamedDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2025  std::string MangledName = getMangledNameImpl(*this, GD, ND);
2026 
2027  // Ensure either we have different ABIs between host and device compilations,
2028  // says host compilation following MSVC ABI but device compilation follows
2029  // Itanium C++ ABI or, if they follow the same ABI, kernel names after
2030  // mangling should be the same after name stubbing. The later checking is
2031  // very important as the device kernel name being mangled in host-compilation
2032  // is used to resolve the device binaries to be executed. Inconsistent naming
2033  // result in undefined behavior. Even though we cannot check that naming
2034  // directly between host- and device-compilations, the host- and
2035  // device-mangling in host compilation could help catching certain ones.
2036  assert(!isa<FunctionDecl>(ND) || !ND->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>() ||
2037  getContext().shouldExternalize(ND) || getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice ||
2038  (getContext().getAuxTargetInfo() &&
2039  (getContext().getAuxTargetInfo()->getCXXABI() !=
2040  getContext().getTargetInfo().getCXXABI())) ||
2041  getCUDARuntime().getDeviceSideName(ND) ==
2042  getMangledNameImpl(
2043  *this,
2044  GD.getWithKernelReferenceKind(KernelReferenceKind::Kernel),
2045  ND));
2046 
2047  auto Result = Manglings.insert(std::make_pair(MangledName, GD));
2048  return MangledDeclNames[CanonicalGD] = Result.first->first();
2049 }
2050 
2051 StringRef CodeGenModule::getBlockMangledName(GlobalDecl GD,
2052  const BlockDecl *BD) {
2053  MangleContext &MangleCtx = getCXXABI().getMangleContext();
2054  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
2055 
2056  SmallString<256> Buffer;
2057  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Buffer);
2058  if (!D)
2059  MangleCtx.mangleGlobalBlock(BD,
2060  dyn_cast_or_null<VarDecl>(initializedGlobalDecl.getDecl()), Out);
2061  else if (const auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(D))
2062  MangleCtx.mangleCtorBlock(CD, GD.getCtorType(), BD, Out);
2063  else if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D))
2064  MangleCtx.mangleDtorBlock(DD, GD.getDtorType(), BD, Out);
2065  else
2066  MangleCtx.mangleBlock(cast<DeclContext>(D), BD, Out);
2067 
2068  auto Result = Manglings.insert(std::make_pair(Out.str(), BD));
2069  return Result.first->first();
2070 }
2071 
2072 const GlobalDecl CodeGenModule::getMangledNameDecl(StringRef Name) {
2073  auto it = MangledDeclNames.begin();
2074  while (it != MangledDeclNames.end()) {
2075  if (it->second == Name)
2076  return it->first;
2077  it++;
2078  }
2079  return GlobalDecl();
2080 }

2084 }

2095 /// AddGlobalDtor - Add a function to the list that will be called
2096 /// when the module is unloaded.
2097 void CodeGenModule::AddGlobalDtor(llvm::Function *Dtor, int Priority,
2098  bool IsDtorAttrFunc) {

2100  (!getContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSAIX() || IsDtorAttrFunc)) {

2108 
2109 void CodeGenModule::EmitCtorList(CtorList &Fns, const char *GlobalName) {
2110  if (Fns.empty()) return;
2111 
2112  // Ctor function type is void()*.
2113  llvm::FunctionType* CtorFTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, false);
2114  llvm::Type *CtorPFTy = llvm::PointerType::get(CtorFTy,
2115  TheModule.getDataLayout().getProgramAddressSpace());
2116  llvm::PointerType *TargetType = VoidPtrTy;
2117  // Get target type when templated global variables are used,
2118  // to emit them correctly in the target (default) address space and avoid
2119  // emitting them in a private address space.
2120  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
2121  TargetType = llvm::PointerType::get(
2122  getLLVMContext(), getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default));
2123 
2124  // Get the type of a ctor entry, { i32, void ()*, i8* }.
2125  llvm::StructType *CtorStructTy =
2126  llvm::StructType::get(Int32Ty, CtorPFTy, TargetType);
2127 
2128  // Construct the constructor and destructor arrays.
2129  ConstantInitBuilder builder(*this);
2130  auto ctors = builder.beginArray(CtorStructTy);
2131  for (const auto &I : Fns) {
2132  auto ctor = ctors.beginStruct(CtorStructTy);
2133  ctor.addInt(Int32Ty, I.Priority);
2134  ctor.add(I.Initializer);
2135  if (I.AssociatedData)
2136  ctor.add(llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
2137  I.AssociatedData, TargetType));
2138  else
2139  ctor.addNullPointer(TargetType);
2140  ctor.finishAndAddTo(ctors);
2141  }
2142 
2143  auto list =
2144  ctors.finishAndCreateGlobal(GlobalName, getPointerAlign(),
2145  /*constant*/ false,
2146  llvm::GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage);
2147 
2148  // The LTO linker doesn't seem to like it when we set an alignment
2149  // on appending variables. Take it off as a workaround.
2150  list->setAlignment(std::nullopt);
2151 
2152  Fns.clear();
2153 }
2154 
2155 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes
2156 CodeGenModule::getFunctionLinkage(GlobalDecl GD) {
2157  const auto *D = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2158 
2159  GVALinkage Linkage = getContext().GetGVALinkageForFunction(D);
2160 
2161  if (const auto *Dtor = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D))
2162  return getCXXABI().getCXXDestructorLinkage(Linkage, Dtor, GD.getDtorType());
2163 
2164  return getLLVMLinkageForDeclarator(D, Linkage);
2165 }

2167 llvm::ConstantInt *CodeGenModule::CreateCrossDsoCfiTypeId(llvm::Metadata *MD) {
2168  llvm::MDString *MDS = dyn_cast<llvm::MDString>(MD);
2169  if (!MDS) return nullptr;
2170 
2171  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int64Ty, llvm::MD5Hash(MDS->getString()));
2172 }

2174 llvm::ConstantInt *CodeGenModule::CreateKCFITypeId(QualType T) {
2175  if (auto *FnType = T->getAs<FunctionProtoType>())
2176  T = getContext().getFunctionType(
2177  FnType->getReturnType(), FnType->getParamTypes(),
2178  FnType->getExtProtoInfo().withExceptionSpec(EST_None));
2179 
2180  std::string OutName;
2181  llvm::raw_string_ostream Out(OutName);
2182  getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCanonicalTypeName(
2183  T, Out, getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiICallNormalizeIntegers);
2184 
2185  if (getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiICallNormalizeIntegers)
2186  Out << ".normalized";
2187 
2188  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty,
2189  static_cast<uint32_t>(llvm::xxHash64(OutName)));
2190 }
