2192 void CodeGenModule::SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl GD,
2193  const CGFunctionInfo &Info,
2194  llvm::Function *F, bool IsThunk) {
2195  unsigned CallingConv;
2196  llvm::AttributeList PAL;
2197  ConstructAttributeList(F->getName(), Info, GD, PAL, CallingConv,
2198  /*AttrOnCallSite=*/false, IsThunk);
2199  if (CallingConv == llvm::CallingConv::X86_VectorCall &&
2200  getTarget().getTriple().isWindowsArm64EC()) {
2201  SourceLocation Loc;
2202  if (const Decl *D = GD.getDecl())
2203  Loc = D->getLocation();
2204 
2205  Error(Loc, "__vectorcall calling convention is not currently supported");
2206  }
2207  F->setAttributes(PAL);
2208  F->setCallingConv(static_cast<llvm::CallingConv::ID>(CallingConv));
2209 }
2210 
2211 static void removeImageAccessQualifier(std::string& TyName) {
2212  std::string ReadOnlyQual("__read_only");
2213  std::string::size_type ReadOnlyPos = TyName.find(ReadOnlyQual);
2214  if (ReadOnlyPos != std::string::npos)
2215  // "+ 1" for the space after access qualifier.
2216  TyName.erase(ReadOnlyPos, ReadOnlyQual.size() + 1);
2217  else {
2218  std::string WriteOnlyQual("__write_only");
2219  std::string::size_type WriteOnlyPos = TyName.find(WriteOnlyQual);
2220  if (WriteOnlyPos != std::string::npos)
2221  TyName.erase(WriteOnlyPos, WriteOnlyQual.size() + 1);
2222  else {
2223  std::string ReadWriteQual("__read_write");
2224  std::string::size_type ReadWritePos = TyName.find(ReadWriteQual);
2225  if (ReadWritePos != std::string::npos)
2226  TyName.erase(ReadWritePos, ReadWriteQual.size() + 1);
2227  }
2228  }
2229 }
2230 
2231 // Returns the address space id that should be produced to the
2232 // kernel_arg_addr_space metadata. This is always fixed to the ids
2233 // as specified in the SPIR 2.0 specification in order to differentiate
2234 // for example in clGetKernelArgInfo() implementation between the address
2235 // spaces with targets without unique mapping to the OpenCL address spaces
2236 // (basically all single AS CPUs).
2237 static unsigned ArgInfoAddressSpace(LangAS AS) {
2238  switch (AS) {
2239  case LangAS::opencl_global:
2240  case LangAS::sycl_global:
2241  return 1;
2242  case LangAS::opencl_constant:
2243  return 2;
2244  case LangAS::opencl_local:
2245  case LangAS::sycl_local:
2246  return 3;
2247  case LangAS::opencl_generic:
2248  return 4; // Not in SPIR 2.0 specs.
2249  case LangAS::opencl_global_device:
2250  case LangAS::sycl_global_device:
2251  return 5;
2252  case LangAS::opencl_global_host:
2253  case LangAS::sycl_global_host:
2254  return 6;
2255  default:
2256  return 0; // Assume private.
2257  }
2258 }
2259 
2260 void CodeGenModule::GenKernelArgMetadata(llvm::Function *Fn,
2261  const FunctionDecl *FD,
2262  CodeGenFunction *CGF) {
2263  assert(((FD && CGF) || (!FD && !CGF)) &&
2264  "Incorrect use - FD and CGF should either be both null or not!");
2265  // Create MDNodes that represent the kernel arg metadata.
2266  // Each MDNode is a list in the form of "key", N number of values which is
2267  // the same number of values as their are kernel arguments.
2268 
2269  const PrintingPolicy &Policy = Context.getPrintingPolicy();
2270 
2271  // MDNode for the kernel argument address space qualifiers.
2272  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> addressQuals;
2273 
2274  // MDNode for the kernel argument access qualifiers (images only).
2275  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> accessQuals;
2276 
2277  // MDNode for the kernel argument type names.
2278  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argTypeNames;
2279 
2280  // MDNode for the kernel argument base type names.
2281  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argBaseTypeNames;
2282 
2283  // MDNode for the kernel argument type qualifiers.
2284  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argTypeQuals;
2285 
2286  // MDNode for the kernel argument names.
2287  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argNames;
2288 
2289  // MDNode for the intel_buffer_location attribute.
2290  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argSYCLBufferLocationAttr;
2291 
2292  // MDNode for listing SYCL kernel pointer arguments originating from
2293  // accessors.
2294  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 8> argSYCLAccessorPtrs;
2295 
2296  bool isKernelArgAnAccessor = false;
2297 
2298  if (FD && CGF)
2299  for (unsigned i = 0, e = FD->getNumParams(); i != e; ++i) {
2300  const ParmVarDecl *parm = FD->getParamDecl(i);
2301  // Get argument name.
2302  argNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, parm->getName()));
2303 
2304  if (!getLangOpts().OpenCL && !getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
2305  continue;
2306  QualType ty = parm->getType();
2307  std::string typeQuals;
2308 
2309  // Get image and pipe access qualifier:
2310  if (ty->isImageType() || ty->isPipeType()) {
2311  const Decl *PDecl = parm;
2312  if (const auto *TD = ty->getAs<TypedefType>())
2313  PDecl = TD->getDecl();
2314  const OpenCLAccessAttr *A = PDecl->getAttr<OpenCLAccessAttr>();
2315  if (A && A->isWriteOnly())
2316  accessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "write_only"));
2317  else if (A && A->isReadWrite())
2318  accessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "read_write"));
2319  else
2320  accessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "read_only"));
2321  } else
2322  accessQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, "none"));
2323 
2324  auto getTypeSpelling = [&](QualType Ty) {
2325  auto typeName = Ty.getUnqualifiedType().getAsString(Policy);
2326 
2327  if (Ty.isCanonical()) {
2328  StringRef typeNameRef = typeName;
2329  // Turn "unsigned type" to "utype"
2330  if (typeNameRef.consume_front("unsigned "))
2331  return std::string("u") + typeNameRef.str();
2332  if (typeNameRef.consume_front("signed "))
2333  return typeNameRef.str();
2334  }
2335 
2336  return typeName;
2337  };
2338 
2339  if (ty->isPointerType()) {
2340  QualType pointeeTy = ty->getPointeeType();
2341 
2342  // Get address qualifier.
2343  addressQuals.push_back(
2344  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getInt32(
2345  ArgInfoAddressSpace(pointeeTy.getAddressSpace()))));
2346 
2347  // Get argument type name.
2348  std::string typeName = getTypeSpelling(pointeeTy) + "*";
2349  std::string baseTypeName =
2350  getTypeSpelling(pointeeTy.getCanonicalType()) + "*";
2351  argTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, typeName));
2352  argBaseTypeNames.push_back(
2353  llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, baseTypeName));
2354 
2355  // Get argument type qualifiers:
2356  if (ty.isRestrictQualified())
2357  typeQuals = "restrict";
2358  if (pointeeTy.isConstQualified() ||
2359  (pointeeTy.getAddressSpace() == LangAS::opencl_constant))
2360  typeQuals += typeQuals.empty() ? "const" : " const";
2361  if (pointeeTy.isVolatileQualified())
2362  typeQuals += typeQuals.empty() ? "volatile" : " volatile";
2363  } else {
2364  uint32_t AddrSpc = 0;
2365  bool isPipe = ty->isPipeType();
2366  if (ty->isImageType() || isPipe)
2367  AddrSpc = ArgInfoAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_global);
2368 
2369  addressQuals.push_back(
2370  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getInt32(AddrSpc)));
2371 
2372  // Get argument type name.
2373  ty = isPipe ? ty->castAs<PipeType>()->getElementType() : ty;
2374  std::string typeName = getTypeSpelling(ty);
2375  std::string baseTypeName = getTypeSpelling(ty.getCanonicalType());
2376 
2377  // Remove access qualifiers on images
2378  // (as they are inseparable from type in clang implementation,
2379  // but OpenCL spec provides a special query to get access qualifier
2380  // via clGetKernelArgInfo with CL_KERNEL_ARG_ACCESS_QUALIFIER):
2381  if (ty->isImageType()) {
2382  removeImageAccessQualifier(typeName);
2383  removeImageAccessQualifier(baseTypeName);
2384  }
2385 
2386  argTypeNames.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, typeName));
2387  argBaseTypeNames.push_back(
2388  llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, baseTypeName));
2389 
2390  if (isPipe)
2391  typeQuals = "pipe";
2392  }
2393  argTypeQuals.push_back(llvm::MDString::get(VMContext, typeQuals));
2394 
2395  auto *SYCLBufferLocationAttr =
2396  parm->getAttr<SYCLIntelBufferLocationAttr>();
2397  argSYCLBufferLocationAttr.push_back(
2398  (SYCLBufferLocationAttr)
2399  ? llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getInt32(
2400  SYCLBufferLocationAttr->getLocationID()))
2401  : llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getInt32(-1)));
2402 
2403  // If a kernel pointer argument comes from an accessor, we generate
2404  // the following metadata :
2405  // 1. kernel_arg_runtime_aligned - To indicate that this pointer has
2406  // runtime allocated alignment.
2407  // 2. kernel_arg_exclusive_ptr - To indicate that it is illegal to
2408  // dereference the pointer from outside current invocation of the
2409  // kernel.
2410  // In both cases, the value of metadata element is 'true' for any
2411  // kernel arguments that corresponds to the base pointer of an accessor
2412  // and 'false' otherwise.
2413  // Note: Although both metadata apply only to the base pointer of an
2414  // accessor currently, it is possible that one or both may be extended
2415  // to include other pointers. Therefore, both metadata are required.
2416  if (parm->hasAttr<SYCLAccessorPtrAttr>()) {
2417  isKernelArgAnAccessor = true;
2418  argSYCLAccessorPtrs.push_back(
2419  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getTrue()));
2420  } else {
2421  argSYCLAccessorPtrs.push_back(
2422  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CGF->Builder.getFalse()));
2423  }
2424  }
2425 
2426  bool IsEsimdFunction = FD && FD->hasAttr<SYCLSimdAttr>();
2427 
2428  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && !IsEsimdFunction) {
2429  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_buffer_location",
2430  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argSYCLBufferLocationAttr));
2431  // Generate this metadata only if atleast one kernel argument is an
2432  // accessor.
2433  if (isKernelArgAnAccessor) {
2434  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_runtime_aligned",
2435  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argSYCLAccessorPtrs));
2436  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_exclusive_ptr",
2437  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argSYCLAccessorPtrs));
2438  }
2439  } else {
2440  if (getLangOpts().OpenCL || getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice) {
2441  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_addr_space",
2442  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, addressQuals));
2443  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_access_qual",
2444  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, accessQuals));
2445  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_type",
2446  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argTypeNames));
2447  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_base_type",
2448  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argBaseTypeNames));
2449  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_type_qual",
2450  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argTypeQuals));
2451  if (IsEsimdFunction)
2452  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_accessor_ptr",
2453  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argSYCLAccessorPtrs));
2454  }
2455  if (getCodeGenOpts().EmitOpenCLArgMetadata ||
2456  getCodeGenOpts().HIPSaveKernelArgName)
2457  Fn->setMetadata("kernel_arg_name",
2458  llvm::MDNode::get(VMContext, argNames));
2459  }
2460 }
2461 
2462 /// Determines whether the language options require us to model
2463 /// unwind exceptions. We treat -fexceptions as mandating this
2464 /// except under the fragile ObjC ABI with only ObjC exceptions
2465 /// enabled. This means, for example, that C with -fexceptions
2466 /// enables this.
2467 static bool hasUnwindExceptions(const LangOptions &LangOpts) {
2468  // If exceptions are completely disabled, obviously this is false.
2469  if (!LangOpts.Exceptions) return false;
2470 
2471  // If C++ exceptions are enabled, this is true.
2472  if (LangOpts.CXXExceptions) return true;
2473 
2474  // If ObjC exceptions are enabled, this depends on the ABI.
2475  if (LangOpts.ObjCExceptions) {
2476  return LangOpts.ObjCRuntime.hasUnwindExceptions();
2477  }
2478 
2479  return true;
2480 }
2481 
2482 static bool requiresMemberFunctionPointerTypeMetadata(CodeGenModule &CGM,
2483  const CXXMethodDecl *MD) {
2484  // Check that the type metadata can ever actually be used by a call.
2485  if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().LTOUnit ||
2486  !CGM.HasHiddenLTOVisibility(MD->getParent()))
2487  return false;
2488 
2489  // Only functions whose address can be taken with a member function pointer
2490  // need this sort of type metadata.
2491  return MD->isImplicitObjectMemberFunction() && !MD->isVirtual() &&
2492  !isa<CXXConstructorDecl, CXXDestructorDecl>(MD);
2493 }
2494 
2495 SmallVector<const CXXRecordDecl *, 0>
2496 CodeGenModule::getMostBaseClasses(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2497  llvm::SetVector<const CXXRecordDecl *> MostBases;
2498 
2499  std::function<void (const CXXRecordDecl *)> CollectMostBases;
2500  CollectMostBases = [&](const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
2501  if (RD->getNumBases() == 0)
2502  MostBases.insert(RD);
2503  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &B : RD->bases())
2504  CollectMostBases(B.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
2505  };
2506  CollectMostBases(RD);
2507  return MostBases.takeVector();
2508 }
2509 
2510 /// Function checks whether given DeclContext contains a topmost
2511 /// namespace with name "sycl"
2512 static bool checkIfDeclaredInSYCLNamespace(const Decl *D) {
2513  const DeclContext *DC = D->getDeclContext()->getEnclosingNamespaceContext();
2514  const auto *ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(DC);
2515  if (!ND)
2516  return false;
2517 
2518  while (const DeclContext *Parent = ND->getParent()) {
2519  if (!isa<NamespaceDecl>(Parent))
2520  break;
2521  ND = cast<NamespaceDecl>(Parent);
2522  }
2523 
2524  return ND && ND->getName() == "sycl";
2525 }
2526 
2527 void CodeGenModule::SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(const Decl *D,
2528  llvm::Function *F) {
2529  llvm::AttrBuilder B(F->getContext());
2530 
2531  if ((!D || !D->hasAttr<NoUwtableAttr>()) && CodeGenOpts.UnwindTables)
2532  B.addUWTableAttr(llvm::UWTableKind(CodeGenOpts.UnwindTables));
2533 
2534  if (CodeGenOpts.StackClashProtector)
2535  B.addAttribute("probe-stack", "inline-asm");
2536 
2537  if (CodeGenOpts.StackProbeSize && CodeGenOpts.StackProbeSize != 4096)
2538  B.addAttribute("stack-probe-size",
2539  std::to_string(CodeGenOpts.StackProbeSize));
2540 
2541  if (!hasUnwindExceptions(LangOpts))
2542  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoUnwind);
2543 
2544  if (D && D->hasAttr<NoStackProtectorAttr>())
2545  ; // Do nothing.
2546  else if (D && D->hasAttr<StrictGuardStackCheckAttr>() &&
2547  isStackProtectorOn(LangOpts, getTriple(), LangOptions::SSPOn))
2548  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::StackProtectStrong);
2549  else if (isStackProtectorOn(LangOpts, getTriple(), LangOptions::SSPOn))
2550  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::StackProtect);
2551  else if (isStackProtectorOn(LangOpts, getTriple(), LangOptions::SSPStrong))
2552  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::StackProtectStrong);
2553  else if (isStackProtectorOn(LangOpts, getTriple(), LangOptions::SSPReq))
2554  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::StackProtectReq);
2555 
2556  if (!D) {
2557  // If we don't have a declaration to control inlining, the function isn't
2558  // explicitly marked as alwaysinline for semantic reasons, and inlining is
2559  // disabled, mark the function as noinline.
2560  if (!F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline) &&
2561  CodeGenOpts.getInlining() == CodeGenOptions::OnlyAlwaysInlining)
2562  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2563 
2564  F->addFnAttrs(B);
2565  return;
2566  }
2567 
2568  // Handle SME attributes that apply to function definitions,
2569  // rather than to function prototypes.
2570  if (D->hasAttr<ArmLocallyStreamingAttr>())
2571  B.addAttribute("aarch64_pstate_sm_body");
2572 
2573  if (auto *Attr = D->getAttr<ArmNewAttr>()) {
2574  if (Attr->isNewZA())
2575  B.addAttribute("aarch64_new_za");
2576  if (Attr->isNewZT0())
2577  B.addAttribute("aarch64_new_zt0");
2578  }
2579 
2580  // Track whether we need to add the optnone LLVM attribute,
2581  // starting with the default for this optimization level.
2582  bool ShouldAddOptNone =
2583  !CodeGenOpts.DisableO0ImplyOptNone && CodeGenOpts.OptimizationLevel == 0;
2584  // We can't add optnone in the following cases, it won't pass the verifier.
2585  ShouldAddOptNone &= !D->hasAttr<MinSizeAttr>();
2586  ShouldAddOptNone &= !D->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>();
2587 
2588  // Add optnone, but do so only if the function isn't always_inline.
2589  if ((ShouldAddOptNone || D->hasAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>()) &&
2590  !F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline)) {
2591  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeNone);
2592 
2593  // OptimizeNone implies noinline; we should not be inlining such functions.
2594  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2595 
2596  // We still need to handle naked functions even though optnone subsumes
2597  // much of their semantics.
2598  if (D->hasAttr<NakedAttr>())
2599  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Naked);
2600 
2601  // OptimizeNone wins over OptimizeForSize and MinSize.
2602  F->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeForSize);
2603  F->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::MinSize);
2604  } else if (D->hasAttr<NakedAttr>()) {
2605  // Naked implies noinline: we should not be inlining such functions.
2606  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Naked);
2607  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2608  } else if (D->hasAttr<NoDuplicateAttr>()) {
2609  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoDuplicate);
2610  } else if (D->hasAttr<NoInlineAttr>() && !F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline)) {
2611  // Add noinline if the function isn't always_inline.
2612  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2613  } else if (D->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>() &&
2614  !F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline)) {
2615  // (noinline wins over always_inline, and we can't specify both in IR)
2616  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline);
2617  } else if (CodeGenOpts.getInlining() == CodeGenOptions::OnlyAlwaysInlining) {
2618  // If we're not inlining, then force everything that isn't always_inline to
2619  // carry an explicit noinline attribute.
2620  if (!F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline))
2621  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2622  } else {
2623  // Otherwise, propagate the inline hint attribute and potentially use its
2624  // absence to mark things as noinline.
2625  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
2626  // Search function and template pattern redeclarations for inline.
2627  auto CheckForInline = [](const FunctionDecl *FD) {
2628  auto CheckRedeclForInline = [](const FunctionDecl *Redecl) {
2629  return Redecl->isInlineSpecified();
2630  };
2631  if (any_of(FD->redecls(), CheckRedeclForInline))
2632  return true;
2633  const FunctionDecl *Pattern = FD->getTemplateInstantiationPattern();
2634  if (!Pattern)
2635  return false;
2636  return any_of(Pattern->redecls(), CheckRedeclForInline);
2637  };
2638  if (CheckForInline(FD)) {
2639  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::InlineHint);
2640  } else if (CodeGenOpts.getInlining() ==
2641  CodeGenOptions::OnlyHintInlining &&
2642  !FD->isInlined() &&
2643  !F->hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::AlwaysInline)) {
2644  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2645  }
2646  }
2647  }
2648 
2649  // Add other optimization related attributes if we are optimizing this
2650  // function.
2651  if (!D->hasAttr<OptimizeNoneAttr>()) {
2652  if (D->hasAttr<ColdAttr>()) {
2653  if (!ShouldAddOptNone)
2654  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeForSize);
2655  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Cold);
2656  }
2657  if (D->hasAttr<HotAttr>())
2658  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::Hot);
2659  if (D->hasAttr<MinSizeAttr>())
2660  B.addAttribute(llvm::Attribute::MinSize);
2661  }
2662 
2663  F->addFnAttrs(B);
2664 
2665  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice && getCodeGenOpts().OptimizeSYCLFramework &&
2666  checkIfDeclaredInSYCLNamespace(D)) {
2667  F->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::OptimizeNone);
2668  F->removeFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
2669  }
2670 
2671  unsigned alignment = D->getMaxAlignment() / Context.getCharWidth();
2672  if (alignment)
2673  F->setAlignment(llvm::Align(alignment));
2674 
2675  if (!D->hasAttr<AlignedAttr>())
2676  if (LangOpts.FunctionAlignment)
2677  F->setAlignment(llvm::Align(1ull << LangOpts.FunctionAlignment));
2678 
2679  // Some C++ ABIs require 2-byte alignment for member functions, in order to
2680  // reserve a bit for differentiating between virtual and non-virtual member
2681  // functions. If the current target's C++ ABI requires this and this is a
2682  // member function, set its alignment accordingly.
2683  if (getTarget().getCXXABI().areMemberFunctionsAligned()) {
2684  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D) && F->getPointerAlignment(getDataLayout()) < 2)
2685  F->setAlignment(std::max(llvm::Align(2), F->getAlign().valueOrOne()));
2686  }
2687 
2688  // In the cross-dso CFI mode with canonical jump tables, we want !type
2689  // attributes on definitions only.
2690  if (CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso &&
2691  CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCanonicalJumpTables) {
2692  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
2693  // Skip available_externally functions. They won't be codegen'ed in the
2694  // current module anyway.
2695  if (getContext().GetGVALinkageForFunction(FD) != GVA_AvailableExternally)
2696  CreateFunctionTypeMetadataForIcall(FD, F);
2697  }
2698  }
2699 
2700  // Emit type metadata on member functions for member function pointer checks.
2701  // These are only ever necessary on definitions; we're guaranteed that the
2702  // definition will be present in the LTO unit as a result of LTO visibility.
2703  auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D);
2704  if (MD && requiresMemberFunctionPointerTypeMetadata(*this, MD)) {
2705  for (const CXXRecordDecl *Base : getMostBaseClasses(MD->getParent())) {
2706  llvm::Metadata *Id =
2707  CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(Context.getMemberPointerType(
2708  MD->getType(), Context.getRecordType(Base).getTypePtr()));
2709  F->addTypeMetadata(0, Id);
2710  }
2711  }
2712 }
2713 
2714 void CodeGenModule::SetCommonAttributes(GlobalDecl GD, llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
2715  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
2716  if (isa_and_nonnull<NamedDecl>(D))
2717  setGVProperties(GV, GD);
2718  else
2719  GV->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility);
2720 
2721  if (D && D->hasAttr<UsedAttr>())
2722  addUsedOrCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
2723 
2724  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast_if_present<VarDecl>(D);
2725  VD &&
2726  ((CodeGenOpts.KeepPersistentStorageVariables &&
2727  (VD->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static ||
2728  VD->getStorageDuration() == SD_Thread)) ||
2729  (CodeGenOpts.KeepStaticConsts && VD->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static &&
2730  VD->getType().isConstQualified())))
2731  addUsedOrCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
2732 
2733  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice) {
2734  // Add internal device_global variables to llvm.compiler.used array to
2735  // prevent early optimizations from removing these variables from the
2736  // module.
2737  if (D && isa<VarDecl>(D)) {
2738  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
2739  const RecordDecl *RD = VD->getType()->getAsRecordDecl();
2740  if (RD && RD->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>() &&
2741  VD->getFormalLinkage() == Linkage::Internal)
2742  addUsedOrCompilerUsedGlobal(GV);
2743  }
2744  }
2745 }
2746 
2747 bool CodeGenModule::GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes(GlobalDecl GD,
2748  llvm::AttrBuilder &Attrs,
2749  bool SetTargetFeatures) {
2750  // Add target-cpu and target-features attributes to functions. If
2751  // we have a decl for the function and it has a target attribute then
2752  // parse that and add it to the feature set.
2753  StringRef TargetCPU = getTarget().getTargetOpts().CPU;
2754  StringRef TuneCPU = getTarget().getTargetOpts().TuneCPU;
2755  std::vector<std::string> Features;
2756  const auto *FD = dyn_cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2757  FD = FD ? FD->getMostRecentDecl() : FD;
2758  const auto *TD = FD ? FD->getAttr<TargetAttr>() : nullptr;
2759  const auto *TV = FD ? FD->getAttr<TargetVersionAttr>() : nullptr;
2760  assert((!TD || !TV) && "both target_version and target specified");
2761  const auto *SD = FD ? FD->getAttr<CPUSpecificAttr>() : nullptr;
2762  const auto *TC = FD ? FD->getAttr<TargetClonesAttr>() : nullptr;
2763  bool AddedAttr = false;
2764  if (TD || TV || SD || TC) {
2765  llvm::StringMap<bool> FeatureMap;
2766  getContext().getFunctionFeatureMap(FeatureMap, GD);
2767 
2768  // Produce the canonical string for this set of features.
2769  for (const llvm::StringMap<bool>::value_type &Entry : FeatureMap)
2770  Features.push_back((Entry.getValue() ? "+" : "-") + Entry.getKey().str());
2771 
2772  // Now add the target-cpu and target-features to the function.
2773  // While we populated the feature map above, we still need to
2774  // get and parse the target attribute so we can get the cpu for
2775  // the function.
2776  if (TD) {
2777  ParsedTargetAttr ParsedAttr =
2778  Target.parseTargetAttr(TD->getFeaturesStr());
2779  if (!ParsedAttr.CPU.empty() &&
2780  getTarget().isValidCPUName(ParsedAttr.CPU)) {
2781  TargetCPU = ParsedAttr.CPU;
2782  TuneCPU = ""; // Clear the tune CPU.
2783  }
2784  if (!ParsedAttr.Tune.empty() &&
2785  getTarget().isValidCPUName(ParsedAttr.Tune))
2786  TuneCPU = ParsedAttr.Tune;
2787  }
2788 
2789  if (SD) {
2790  // Apply the given CPU name as the 'tune-cpu' so that the optimizer can
2791  // favor this processor.
2792  TuneCPU = SD->getCPUName(GD.getMultiVersionIndex())->getName();
2793  }
2794  } else {
2795  // Otherwise just add the existing target cpu and target features to the
2796  // function.
2797  Features = getTarget().getTargetOpts().Features;
2798  }
2799 
2800  if (!TargetCPU.empty()) {
2801  Attrs.addAttribute("target-cpu", TargetCPU);
2802  AddedAttr = true;
2803  }
2804  if (!TuneCPU.empty()) {
2805  Attrs.addAttribute("tune-cpu", TuneCPU);
2806  AddedAttr = true;
2807  }
2808  if (!Features.empty() && SetTargetFeatures) {
2809  llvm::erase_if(Features, [&](const std::string& F) {
2810  return getTarget().isReadOnlyFeature(F.substr(1));
2811  });
2812  llvm::sort(Features);
2813  Attrs.addAttribute("target-features", llvm::join(Features, ","));
2814  AddedAttr = true;
2815  }
2816 
2817  return AddedAttr;
2818 }
2819 
2820 void CodeGenModule::setNonAliasAttributes(GlobalDecl GD,
2821  llvm::GlobalObject *GO) {
2822  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
2823  SetCommonAttributes(GD, GO);
2824 
2825  if (D) {
2826  if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(GO)) {
2827  if (D->hasAttr<RetainAttr>())
2828  addUsedGlobal(GV);
2829  if (auto *SA = D->getAttr<PragmaClangBSSSectionAttr>())
2830  GV->addAttribute("bss-section", SA->getName());
2831  if (auto *SA = D->getAttr<PragmaClangDataSectionAttr>())
2832  GV->addAttribute("data-section", SA->getName());
2833  if (auto *SA = D->getAttr<PragmaClangRodataSectionAttr>())
2834  GV->addAttribute("rodata-section", SA->getName());
2835  if (auto *SA = D->getAttr<PragmaClangRelroSectionAttr>())
2836  GV->addAttribute("relro-section", SA->getName());
2837  }
2838 
2839  if (auto *F = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(GO)) {
2840  if (D->hasAttr<RetainAttr>())
2841  addUsedGlobal(F);
2842  if (auto *SA = D->getAttr<PragmaClangTextSectionAttr>())
2843  if (!D->getAttr<SectionAttr>())
2844  F->setSection(SA->getName());
2845 
2846  llvm::AttrBuilder Attrs(F->getContext());
2847  if (GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes(GD, Attrs)) {
2848  // We know that GetCPUAndFeaturesAttributes will always have the
2849  // newest set, since it has the newest possible FunctionDecl, so the
2850  // new ones should replace the old.
2851  llvm::AttributeMask RemoveAttrs;
2852  RemoveAttrs.addAttribute("target-cpu");
2853  RemoveAttrs.addAttribute("target-features");
2854  RemoveAttrs.addAttribute("tune-cpu");
2855  F->removeFnAttrs(RemoveAttrs);
2856  F->addFnAttrs(Attrs);
2857  }
2858  }
2859 
2860  if (const auto *CSA = D->getAttr<CodeSegAttr>())
2861  GO->setSection(CSA->getName());
2862  else if (const auto *SA = D->getAttr<SectionAttr>())
2863  GO->setSection(SA->getName());
2864  }
2865 
2866  getTargetCodeGenInfo().setTargetAttributes(D, GO, *this);
2867 }

2869 void CodeGenModule::SetInternalFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl GD,
2870  llvm::Function *F,
2871  const CGFunctionInfo &FI) {
2872  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
2873  SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GD, FI, F, /*IsThunk=*/false);
2874  SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(D, F);
2875 
2876  F->setLinkage(llvm::Function::InternalLinkage);
2877 
2878  setNonAliasAttributes(GD, F);
2879 }

2881 static void setLinkageForGV(llvm::GlobalValue *GV, const NamedDecl *ND) {
2882  // Set linkage and visibility in case we never see a definition.
2883  LinkageInfo LV = ND->getLinkageAndVisibility();
2884  // Don't set internal linkage on declarations.
2885  // "extern_weak" is overloaded in LLVM; we probably should have
2886  // separate linkage types for this.
2887  if (isExternallyVisible(LV.getLinkage()) &&
2888  (ND->hasAttr<WeakAttr>() || ND->isWeakImported()))
2889  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage);
2890 }

2892 void CodeGenModule::CreateFunctionTypeMetadataForIcall(const FunctionDecl *FD,
2893  llvm::Function *F) {
2894  // Only if we are checking indirect calls.
2895  if (!LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFIICall))
2896  return;
2897 
2898  // Non-static class methods are handled via vtable or member function pointer
2899  // checks elsewhere.
2900  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(FD) && !cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)->isStatic())
2901  return;
2902 
2903  llvm::Metadata *MD = CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(FD->getType());
2904  F->addTypeMetadata(0, MD);
2905  F->addTypeMetadata(0, CreateMetadataIdentifierGeneralized(FD->getType()));
2906 
2907  // Emit a hash-based bit set entry for cross-DSO calls.
2908  if (CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso)
2909  if (auto CrossDsoTypeId = CreateCrossDsoCfiTypeId(MD))
2910  F->addTypeMetadata(0, llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CrossDsoTypeId));
2911 }

2913 void CodeGenModule::setKCFIType(const FunctionDecl *FD, llvm::Function *F) {
2914  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = F->getContext();
2915  llvm::MDBuilder MDB(Ctx);
2916  F->setMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_kcfi_type,
2917  llvm::MDNode::get(
2918  Ctx, MDB.createConstant(CreateKCFITypeId(FD->getType()))));
2919 }
2920 
2921 static bool allowKCFIIdentifier(StringRef Name) {
2922  // KCFI type identifier constants are only necessary for external assembly
2923  // functions, which means it's safe to skip unusual names. Subset of
2924  // MCAsmInfo::isAcceptableChar() and MCAsmInfoXCOFF::isAcceptableChar().
2925  return llvm::all_of(Name, [](const char &C) {
2926  return llvm::isAlnum(C) || C == '_' || C == '.';
2927  });
2928 }
2929 
2930 void CodeGenModule::finalizeKCFITypes() {
2931  llvm::Module &M = getModule();
2932  for (auto &F : M.functions()) {
2933  // Remove KCFI type metadata from non-address-taken local functions.
2934  bool AddressTaken = F.hasAddressTaken();
2935  if (!AddressTaken && F.hasLocalLinkage())
2936  F.eraseMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_kcfi_type);
2937 
2938  // Generate a constant with the expected KCFI type identifier for all
2939  // address-taken function declarations to support annotating indirectly
2940  // called assembly functions.
2941  if (!AddressTaken || !F.isDeclaration())
2942  continue;
2943 
2944  const llvm::ConstantInt *Type;
2945  if (const llvm::MDNode *MD = F.getMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_kcfi_type))
2946  Type = llvm::mdconst::extract<llvm::ConstantInt>(MD->getOperand(0));
2947  else
2948  continue;
2949 
2950  StringRef Name = F.getName();
2951  if (!allowKCFIIdentifier(Name))
2952  continue;
2953 
2954  std::string Asm = (".weak __kcfi_typeid_" + Name + "\n.set __kcfi_typeid_" +
2955  Name + ", " + Twine(Type->getZExtValue()) + "\n")
2956  .str();
2957  M.appendModuleInlineAsm(Asm);
2958  }
2959 }
2960 
2961 template <typename AttrT>
2962 void applySYCLAspectsMD(AttrT *A, ASTContext &ACtx, llvm::LLVMContext &LLVMCtx,
2963  llvm::Function *F, StringRef MDName) {
2964  SmallVector<llvm::Metadata *, 4> AspectsMD;
2965  for (auto *Aspect : A->aspects()) {
2966  llvm::APSInt AspectInt = Aspect->EvaluateKnownConstInt(ACtx);
2967  auto *T = llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(LLVMCtx);
2968  auto *C = llvm::Constant::getIntegerValue(T, AspectInt);
2969  AspectsMD.push_back(llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(C));
2970  }
2971  F->setMetadata(MDName, llvm::MDNode::get(LLVMCtx, AspectsMD));
2972 }

2974 void CodeGenModule::SetFunctionAttributes(GlobalDecl GD, llvm::Function *F,
2975  bool IsIncompleteFunction,
2976  bool IsThunk) {
2977 
2978  if (llvm::Intrinsic::ID IID = F->getIntrinsicID()) {
2979  // If this is an intrinsic function, set the function's attributes
2980  // to the intrinsic's attributes.
2981  F->setAttributes(llvm::Intrinsic::getAttributes(getLLVMContext(), IID));
2982  return;
2983  }
2984 
2985  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
2986 
2987  if (!IsIncompleteFunction)
2988  SetLLVMFunctionAttributes(GD, getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD), F,
2989  IsThunk);
2990 
2991  // Add the Returned attribute for "this", except for iOS 5 and earlier
2992  // where substantial code, including the libstdc++ dylib, was compiled with
2993  // GCC and does not actually return "this".
2994  if (!IsThunk && getCXXABI().HasThisReturn(GD) &&
2995  !(getTriple().isiOS() && getTriple().isOSVersionLT(6))) {
2996  assert(!F->arg_empty() &&
2997  F->arg_begin()->getType()
2998  ->canLosslesslyBitCastTo(F->getReturnType()) &&
2999  "unexpected this return");
3000  F->addParamAttr(0, llvm::Attribute::Returned);
3001  }
3002 
3003  // Only a few attributes are set on declarations; these may later be
3004  // overridden by a definition.
3005 
3006  setLinkageForGV(F, FD);
3007  setGVProperties(F, FD);
3008 
3009  // Setup target-specific attributes.
3010  if (!IsIncompleteFunction && F->isDeclaration())
3011  getTargetCodeGenInfo().setTargetAttributes(FD, F, *this);
3012 
3013  if (const auto *CSA = FD->getAttr<CodeSegAttr>())
3014  F->setSection(CSA->getName());
3015  else if (const auto *SA = FD->getAttr<SectionAttr>())
3016  F->setSection(SA->getName());
3017 
3018  if (const auto *EA = FD->getAttr<ErrorAttr>()) {
3019  if (EA->isError())
3020  F->addFnAttr("dontcall-error", EA->getUserDiagnostic());
3021  else if (EA->isWarning())
3022  F->addFnAttr("dontcall-warn", EA->getUserDiagnostic());
3023  }
3024 
3025  // If we plan on emitting this inline builtin, we can't treat it as a builtin.
3026  if (FD->isInlineBuiltinDeclaration()) {
3027  const FunctionDecl *FDBody;
3028  bool HasBody = FD->hasBody(FDBody);
3029  (void)HasBody;
3030  assert(HasBody && "Inline builtin declarations should always have an "
3031  "available body!");
3032  if (shouldEmitFunction(FDBody))
3033  F->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoBuiltin);
3034  }
3035 
3036  if (FD->isReplaceableGlobalAllocationFunction()) {
3037  // A replaceable global allocation function does not act like a builtin by
3038  // default, only if it is invoked by a new-expression or delete-expression.
3039  F->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoBuiltin);
3040  }
3041 
3042  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(FD) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(FD))
3043  F->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3044  else if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD))
3045  if (MD->isVirtual())
3046  F->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3047 
3048  // Don't emit entries for function declarations in the cross-DSO mode. This
3049  // is handled with better precision by the receiving DSO. But if jump tables
3050  // are non-canonical then we need type metadata in order to produce the local
3051  // jump table.
3052  if (!CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso ||
3053  !CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCanonicalJumpTables)
3054  CreateFunctionTypeMetadataForIcall(FD, F);
3055 
3056  if (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::KCFI))
3057  setKCFIType(FD, F);
3058 
3059  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && FD->hasAttr<OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr>())
3060  getOpenMPRuntime().emitDeclareSimdFunction(FD, F);
3061 
3062  if (CodeGenOpts.InlineMaxStackSize != UINT_MAX)
3063  F->addFnAttr("inline-max-stacksize", llvm::utostr(CodeGenOpts.InlineMaxStackSize));
3064 
3065  if (const auto *CB = FD->getAttr<CallbackAttr>()) {
3066  // Annotate the callback behavior as metadata:
3067  // - The callback callee (as argument number).
3068  // - The callback payloads (as argument numbers).
3069  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = F->getContext();
3070  llvm::MDBuilder MDB(Ctx);
3071 
3072  // The payload indices are all but the first one in the encoding. The first
3073  // identifies the callback callee.
3074  int CalleeIdx = *CB->encoding_begin();
3075  ArrayRef<int> PayloadIndices(CB->encoding_begin() + 1, CB->encoding_end());
3076  F->addMetadata(llvm::LLVMContext::MD_callback,
3077  *llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, {MDB.createCallbackEncoding(
3078  CalleeIdx, PayloadIndices,
3079  /* VarArgsArePassed */ false)}));
3080  }
3081 
3082  // Apply SYCL specific attributes/metadata.
3083  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<SYCLDeviceHasAttr>())
3084  applySYCLAspectsMD(A, getContext(), getLLVMContext(), F,
3085  "sycl_declared_aspects");
3086 
3087  if (const auto *A = FD->getAttr<SYCLUsesAspectsAttr>())
3088  applySYCLAspectsMD(A, getContext(), getLLVMContext(), F,
3089  "sycl_used_aspects");
3090 }

3104 void CodeGenModule::addUsedOrCompilerUsedGlobal(llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {

3106  "Only globals with definition can force usage.");

3113 static void emitUsed(CodeGenModule &CGM, StringRef Name,
3114  std::vector<llvm::WeakTrackingVH> &List) {
3115  // Don't create llvm.used if there is no need.
3116  if (List.empty())
3117  return;
3118  // For SYCL emit pointers in the default address space which is a superset of
3119  // other address spaces, so that casts from any other address spaces will be
3120  // valid.
3121  llvm::PointerType *TargetType = CGM.Int8PtrTy;
3122  if (CGM.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
3123  TargetType = llvm::PointerType::get(
3124  CGM.getLLVMContext(),
3125  CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default));
3126 
3127  // Convert List to what ConstantArray needs.
3128  SmallVector<llvm::Constant*, 8> UsedArray;
3129  UsedArray.resize(List.size());
3130  for (unsigned i = 0, e = List.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3131  UsedArray[i] = llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
3132  cast<llvm::Constant>(&*List[i]), TargetType);
3133  }
3134 
3135  if (UsedArray.empty())
3136  return;
3137  llvm::ArrayType *ATy = llvm::ArrayType::get(TargetType, UsedArray.size());
3138 
3139  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3140  CGM.getModule(), ATy, false, llvm::GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage,
3141  llvm::ConstantArray::get(ATy, UsedArray), Name);
3142 
3143  GV->setSection("llvm.metadata");
3144 }
3145 
3146 void CodeGenModule::emitLLVMUsed() {
3147  emitUsed(*this, "llvm.used", LLVMUsed);
3148  emitUsed(*this, "llvm.compiler.used", LLVMCompilerUsed);
3149 }

3165 void CodeGenModule::AddDependentLib(StringRef Lib) {

3167  if (getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {
3168  ELFDependentLibraries.push_back(
3169  llvm::MDNode::get(C, llvm::MDString::get(C, Lib)));
3170  return;
3171  }
3172 
3173  llvm::SmallString<24> Opt;
3174  getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDependentLibraryOption(Lib, Opt);

3178 
3179 /// Add link options implied by the given module, including modules
3180 /// it depends on, using a postorder walk.
3181 static void addLinkOptionsPostorder(CodeGenModule &CGM, Module *Mod,
3182  SmallVectorImpl<llvm::MDNode *> &Metadata,
3183  llvm::SmallPtrSet<Module *, 16> &Visited) {
3184  // Import this module's parent.
3185  if (Mod->Parent && Visited.insert(Mod->Parent).second) {
3186  addLinkOptionsPostorder(CGM, Mod->Parent, Metadata, Visited);
3187  }
3188 
3189  // Import this module's dependencies.
3190  for (Module *Import : llvm::reverse(Mod->Imports)) {
3191  if (Visited.insert(Import).second)
3192  addLinkOptionsPostorder(CGM, Import, Metadata, Visited);
3193  }
3194 
3195  // Add linker options to link against the libraries/frameworks
3196  // described by this module.
3197  llvm::LLVMContext &Context = CGM.getLLVMContext();
3198  bool IsELF = CGM.getTarget().getTriple().isOSBinFormatELF();
3199 
3200  // For modules that use export_as for linking, use that module
3201  // name instead.
3202  if (Mod->UseExportAsModuleLinkName)
3203  return;
3204 
3205  for (const Module::LinkLibrary &LL : llvm::reverse(Mod->LinkLibraries)) {
3206  // Link against a framework. Frameworks are currently Darwin only, so we
3207  // don't to ask TargetCodeGenInfo for the spelling of the linker option.
3208  if (LL.IsFramework) {
3209  llvm::Metadata *Args[2] = {llvm::MDString::get(Context, "-framework"),
3210  llvm::MDString::get(Context, LL.Library)};
3211 
3212  Metadata.push_back(llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Args));
3213  continue;
3214  }
3215 
3216  // Link against a library.
3217  if (IsELF) {
3218  llvm::Metadata *Args[2] = {
3219  llvm::MDString::get(Context, "lib"),
3220  llvm::MDString::get(Context, LL.Library),
3221  };
3222  Metadata.push_back(llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Args));
3223  } else {
3224  llvm::SmallString<24> Opt;
3225  CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDependentLibraryOption(LL.Library, Opt);
3226  auto *OptString = llvm::MDString::get(Context, Opt);
3227  Metadata.push_back(llvm::MDNode::get(Context, OptString));
3228  }
3229  }
3230 }
3231 
3232 void CodeGenModule::EmitModuleInitializers(clang::Module *Primary) {
3233  assert(Primary->isNamedModuleUnit() &&
3234  "We should only emit module initializers for named modules.");
3235 
3236  // Emit the initializers in the order that sub-modules appear in the
3237  // source, first Global Module Fragments, if present.
3238  if (auto GMF = Primary->getGlobalModuleFragment()) {
3239  for (Decl *D : getContext().getModuleInitializers(GMF)) {
3240  if (isa<ImportDecl>(D))
3241  continue;
3242  assert(isa<VarDecl>(D) && "GMF initializer decl is not a var?");
3243  EmitTopLevelDecl(D);
3244  }
3245  }
3246  // Second any associated with the module, itself.
3247  for (Decl *D : getContext().getModuleInitializers(Primary)) {
3248  // Skip import decls, the inits for those are called explicitly.
3249  if (isa<ImportDecl>(D))
3250  continue;
3251  EmitTopLevelDecl(D);
3252  }
3253  // Third any associated with the Privat eMOdule Fragment, if present.
3254  if (auto PMF = Primary->getPrivateModuleFragment()) {
3255  for (Decl *D : getContext().getModuleInitializers(PMF)) {
3256  // Skip import decls, the inits for those are called explicitly.
3257  if (isa<ImportDecl>(D))
3258  continue;
3259  assert(isa<VarDecl>(D) && "PMF initializer decl is not a var?");
3260  EmitTopLevelDecl(D);
3261  }
3262  }
3263 }
3264 
3265 void CodeGenModule::EmitModuleLinkOptions() {
3266  // Collect the set of all of the modules we want to visit to emit link
3267  // options, which is essentially the imported modules and all of their
3268  // non-explicit child modules.
3269  llvm::SetVector<clang::Module *> LinkModules;
3270  llvm::SmallPtrSet<clang::Module *, 16> Visited;
3271  SmallVector<clang::Module *, 16> Stack;
3272 
3273  // Seed the stack with imported modules.
3274  for (Module *M : ImportedModules) {
3275  // Do not add any link flags when an implementation TU of a module imports
3276  // a header of that same module.
3277  if (M->getTopLevelModuleName() == getLangOpts().CurrentModule &&
3278  !getLangOpts().isCompilingModule())
3279  continue;
3280  if (Visited.insert(M).second)
3281  Stack.push_back(M);
3282  }
3283 
3284  // Find all of the modules to import, making a little effort to prune
3285  // non-leaf modules.
3286  while (!Stack.empty()) {
3287  clang::Module *Mod = Stack.pop_back_val();
3288 
3289  bool AnyChildren = false;
3290 
3291  // Visit the submodules of this module.
3292  for (const auto &SM : Mod->submodules()) {
3293  // Skip explicit children; they need to be explicitly imported to be
3294  // linked against.
3295  if (SM->IsExplicit)
3296  continue;
3297 
3298  if (Visited.insert(SM).second) {
3299  Stack.push_back(SM);
3300  AnyChildren = true;
3301  }
3302  }
3303 
3304  // We didn't find any children, so add this module to the list of
3305  // modules to link against.
3306  if (!AnyChildren) {
3307  LinkModules.insert(Mod);
3308  }
3309  }
3310 
3311  // Add link options for all of the imported modules in reverse topological
3312  // order. We don't do anything to try to order import link flags with respect
3313  // to linker options inserted by things like #pragma comment().
3314  SmallVector<llvm::MDNode *, 16> MetadataArgs;
3315  Visited.clear();
3316  for (Module *M : LinkModules)
3317  if (Visited.insert(M).second)
3318  addLinkOptionsPostorder(*this, M, MetadataArgs, Visited);
3319  std::reverse(MetadataArgs.begin(), MetadataArgs.end());
3320  LinkerOptionsMetadata.append(MetadataArgs.begin(), MetadataArgs.end());
3321 
3322  // Add the linker options metadata flag.
3323  auto *NMD = getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata("llvm.linker.options");
3324  for (auto *MD : LinkerOptionsMetadata)
3325  NMD->addOperand(MD);
3326 }
3327 
3328 void CodeGenModule::EmitDeferred() {
3329  // Emit deferred declare target declarations.
3330  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && !getLangOpts().OpenMPSimd)
3331  getOpenMPRuntime().emitDeferredTargetDecls();
3332 
3333  // Emit code for any potentially referenced deferred decls. Since a
3334  // previously unused static decl may become used during the generation of code
3335  // for a static function, iterate until no changes are made.
3336 
3337  if (!DeferredVTables.empty()) {
3338  EmitDeferredVTables();
3339 
3340  // Emitting a vtable doesn't directly cause more vtables to
3341  // become deferred, although it can cause functions to be
3342  // emitted that then need those vtables.
3343  assert(DeferredVTables.empty());
3344  }
3345 
3346  // Emit CUDA/HIP static device variables referenced by host code only.
3347  // Note we should not clear CUDADeviceVarODRUsedByHost since it is still
3348  // needed for further handling.
3349  if (getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice)
3350  llvm::append_range(DeferredDeclsToEmit,
3351  getContext().CUDADeviceVarODRUsedByHost);
3352 
3353  // Stop if we're out of both deferred vtables and deferred declarations.
3354  if (DeferredDeclsToEmit.empty())
3355  return;
3356 
3357  // Grab the list of decls to emit. If EmitGlobalDefinition schedules more
3358  // work, it will not interfere with this.
3359  std::vector<GlobalDecl> CurDeclsToEmit;
3360  CurDeclsToEmit.swap(DeferredDeclsToEmit);
3361 
3362  for (GlobalDecl &D : CurDeclsToEmit) {
3363  // Emit a dummy __host__ function if a legit one is not already present in
3364  // case of SYCL compilation of CUDA sources.
3365  if (SYCLCUDAIsHost(LangOpts)) {
3366  GlobalDecl OtherD;
3367  if (lookupRepresentativeDecl(getMangledName(D), OtherD) &&
3368  (D.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl() !=
3369  OtherD.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl()) &&
3370  D.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl()->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>())
3371  continue;
3372  }
3373  // Emit a dummy __host__ function if a legit one is not already present in
3374  // case of SYCL compilation of CUDA sources.
3375  if (SYCLCUDAIsSYCLDevice(LangOpts)) {
3376  GlobalDecl OtherD;
3377  if (lookupRepresentativeDecl(getMangledName(D), OtherD) &&
3378  (D.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl() !=
3379  OtherD.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl()) &&
3380  D.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl()->hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>())
3381  continue;
3382  }
3383  const ValueDecl *VD = cast<ValueDecl>(D.getDecl());
3384  // If emitting for SYCL device, emit the deferred alias
3385  // as well as what it aliases.
3386  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
3387  if (AliasAttr *Attr = VD->getAttr<AliasAttr>()) {
3388  StringRef AliaseeName = Attr->getAliasee();
3389  auto DDI = DeferredDecls.find(AliaseeName);
3390  // Emit what is aliased first.
3391  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end()) {
3392  GlobalDecl GD = DDI->second;
3393  llvm::GlobalValue *AliaseeGV =
3394  dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(GetAddrOfGlobal(GD, ForDefinition));
3395  if (!AliaseeGV)
3396  AliaseeGV = GetGlobalValue(getMangledName(GD));
3397  assert(AliaseeGV);
3398  EmitGlobalDefinition(GD, AliaseeGV);
3399  // Remove the entry just added to the DeferredDeclsToEmit
3400  // since we have emitted it.
3401  DeferredDeclsToEmit.pop_back();
3402  }
3403  // Now emit the alias itself.
3404  EmitAliasDefinition(D);
3405  continue;
3406  }
3407  }
3408  // We should call GetAddrOfGlobal with IsForDefinition set to true in order
3409  // to get GlobalValue with exactly the type we need, not something that
3410  // might had been created for another decl with the same mangled name but
3411  // different type.
3412  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(
3413  GetAddrOfGlobal(D, ForDefinition));
3414 
3415  // In case of different address spaces, we may still get a cast, even with
3416  // IsForDefinition equal to true. Query mangled names table to get
3417  // GlobalValue.
3418  if (!GV)
3419  GV = GetGlobalValue(getMangledName(D));
3420 
3421  // Make sure GetGlobalValue returned non-null.
3422  assert(GV);
3423 
3424  // Check to see if we've already emitted this. This is necessary
3425  // for a couple of reasons: first, decls can end up in the
3426  // deferred-decls queue multiple times, and second, decls can end
3427  // up with definitions in unusual ways (e.g. by an extern inline
3428  // function acquiring a strong function redefinition). Just
3429  // ignore these cases.
3430  if (!GV->isDeclaration())
3431  continue;
3432 
3433  // If this is OpenMP, check if it is legal to emit this global normally.
3434  if (LangOpts.OpenMP && OpenMPRuntime && OpenMPRuntime->emitTargetGlobal(D))
3435  continue;
3436 
3437  // Otherwise, emit the definition and move on to the next one.
3438  EmitGlobalDefinition(D, GV);
3439 
3440  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
3441  // If there are any aliases deferred for this, emit those now.
3442  for (auto It = DeferredAliases.begin(); It != DeferredAliases.end();
3443  /*no increment*/) {
3444  const ValueDecl *Global = cast<ValueDecl>(It->second.getDecl());
3445  if (It->first == getMangledName(D)) {
3446  EmitAliasDefinition(Global);
3447  It = DeferredAliases.erase(It);
3448  } else {
3449  ++It;
3450  }
3451  }
3452  }
3453 
3454  // If we found out that we need to emit more decls, do that recursively.
3455  // This has the advantage that the decls are emitted in a DFS and related
3456  // ones are close together, which is convenient for testing.
3457  if (!DeferredVTables.empty() || !DeferredDeclsToEmit.empty()) {
3458  EmitDeferred();
3459  assert(DeferredVTables.empty() && DeferredDeclsToEmit.empty());
3460  }
3461  }
3462 }
3463 
3464 void CodeGenModule::EmitVTablesOpportunistically() {
3465  // Try to emit external vtables as available_externally if they have emitted
3466  // all inlined virtual functions. It runs after EmitDeferred() and therefore
3467  // is not allowed to create new references to things that need to be emitted
3468  // lazily. Note that it also uses fact that we eagerly emitting RTTI.
3469 
3470  assert((OpportunisticVTables.empty() || shouldOpportunisticallyEmitVTables())
3471  && "Only emit opportunistic vtables with optimizations");
3472 
3473  for (const CXXRecordDecl *RD : OpportunisticVTables) {
3474  assert(getVTables().isVTableExternal(RD) &&
3475  "This queue should only contain external vtables");
3476  if (getCXXABI().canSpeculativelyEmitVTable(RD))
3477  VTables.GenerateClassData(RD);
3478  }
3479  OpportunisticVTables.clear();
3480 }

3482 void CodeGenModule::EmitGlobalAnnotations() {
3483  for (const auto& [MangledName, VD] : DeferredAnnotations) {
3484  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
3485  if (GV)
3486  AddGlobalAnnotations(VD, GV);
3487  }
3488  DeferredAnnotations.clear();
3489 
3490  if (Annotations.empty())
3491  return;
3492 
3493  // Create a new global variable for the ConstantStruct in the Module.
3494  llvm::Constant *Array = llvm::ConstantArray::get(llvm::ArrayType::get(
3495  Annotations[0]->getType(), Annotations.size()), Annotations);
3496  auto *gv = new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), Array->getType(), false,
3497  llvm::GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage,
3498  Array, "llvm.global.annotations");
3499  gv->setSection(AnnotationSection);
3500 }

3502 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::EmitAnnotationString(StringRef Str) {
3503  llvm::Constant *&AStr = AnnotationStrings[Str];
3504  if (AStr)
3505  return AStr;
3506 
3507  // Not found yet, create a new global.
3508  llvm::Constant *s = llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(getLLVMContext(), Str);
3509  auto *gv = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3510  getModule(), s->getType(), true, llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, s,
3511  ".str", nullptr, llvm::GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal,
3512  ConstGlobalsPtrTy->getAddressSpace());
3513  gv->setSection(AnnotationSection);
3514  gv->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3515  AStr = gv;
3516  return gv;
3517 }

3524  return EmitAnnotationString(SM.getBufferName(Loc));

3535 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::EmitAnnotationArgs(const AnnotateAttr *Attr) {
3536  ArrayRef<Expr *> Exprs = {Attr->args_begin(), Attr->args_size()};
3537  if (Exprs.empty())
3538  return llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(ConstGlobalsPtrTy);
3539 
3540  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3541  for (Expr *E : Exprs) {
3542  ID.Add(cast<clang::ConstantExpr>(E)->getAPValueResult());
3543  }
3544  llvm::Constant *&Lookup = AnnotationArgs[ID.ComputeHash()];
3545  if (Lookup)
3546  return Lookup;
3547 
3548  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> LLVMArgs;
3549  LLVMArgs.reserve(Exprs.size());
3550  ConstantEmitter ConstEmiter(*this);
3551  llvm::transform(Exprs, std::back_inserter(LLVMArgs), [&](const Expr *E) {
3552  const auto *CE = cast<clang::ConstantExpr>(E);
3553  return ConstEmiter.emitAbstract(CE->getBeginLoc(), CE->getAPValueResult(),
3554  CE->getType());
3555  });
3556  auto *Struct = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(LLVMArgs);
3557  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), Struct->getType(), true,
3558  llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, Struct,
3559  ".args");
3560  GV->setSection(AnnotationSection);
3561  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3562 
3563  Lookup = GV;
3564  return GV;
3565 }
3566 
3567 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::EmitAnnotateAttr(llvm::GlobalValue *GV,
3568  const AnnotateAttr *AA,
3569  SourceLocation L) {
3570  // Get the globals for file name, annotation, and the line number.
3571  llvm::Constant *AnnoGV = EmitAnnotationString(AA->getAnnotation()),
3572  *UnitGV = EmitAnnotationUnit(L),
3573  *LineNoCst = EmitAnnotationLineNo(L),
3574  *Args = EmitAnnotationArgs(AA);
3575 
3576  llvm::Constant *GVInGlobalsAS = GV;
3577  if (GV->getAddressSpace() !=
3578  getDataLayout().getDefaultGlobalsAddressSpace()) {
3579  GVInGlobalsAS = llvm::ConstantExpr::getAddrSpaceCast(
3580  GV,
3581  llvm::PointerType::get(
3582  GV->getContext(), getDataLayout().getDefaultGlobalsAddressSpace()));
3583  }
3584 
3585  // Create the ConstantStruct for the global annotation.
3586  llvm::Constant *Fields[] = {
3587  GVInGlobalsAS, AnnoGV, UnitGV, LineNoCst, Args,
3588  };
3589  return llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Fields);
3590 }

3592 void CodeGenModule::AddGlobalAnnotations(const ValueDecl *D,
3593  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
3594  assert(D->hasAttr<AnnotateAttr>() && "no annotate attribute");
3595  // Get the struct elements for these annotations.
3596  for (const auto *I : D->specific_attrs<AnnotateAttr>())
3597  Annotations.push_back(EmitAnnotateAttr(GV, I, D->getLocation()));
3598 }

3600 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::EmitSYCLAnnotationArgs(
3601  llvm::SmallVectorImpl<std::pair<std::string, std::string>>
3602  &AnnotationNameValPairs) {
3603 
3604  if (AnnotationNameValPairs.empty())
3605  return llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(ConstGlobalsPtrTy);
3606 
3607  // For each name-value pair of the SYCL annotation attribute, create an
3608  // annotation string for it. This will be the annotation arguments. If the
3609  // value is the empty string, use a null-pointer instead.
3610  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Constant *, 4> LLVMArgs;
3611  llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3612  LLVMArgs.reserve(AnnotationNameValPairs.size() * 2);
3613  for (const std::pair<std::string, std::string> &NVP :
3614  AnnotationNameValPairs) {
3615  llvm::Constant *NameStrC = EmitAnnotationString(NVP.first);
3616  llvm::Constant *ValueStrC =
3617  NVP.second == "" ? llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(ConstGlobalsPtrTy)
3618  : EmitAnnotationString(NVP.second);
3619  LLVMArgs.push_back(NameStrC);
3620  LLVMArgs.push_back(ValueStrC);
3621  ID.Add(NameStrC);
3622  ID.Add(ValueStrC);
3623  }
3624 
3625  // If another SYCL annotation had the same arguments we can reuse the
3626  // annotation value it created.
3627  llvm::Constant *&LookupRef = SYCLAnnotationArgs[ID.ComputeHash()];
3628  if (LookupRef)
3629  return LookupRef;
3630 
3631  // Create an anonymous struct global variable pointing to the annotation
3632  // arguments in the order they were added above. This is the final constant
3633  // used as the annotation value.
3634  auto *Struct = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(LLVMArgs);
3635  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3636  getModule(), Struct->getType(), true, llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
3637  Struct, ".args", nullptr, llvm::GlobalValue::NotThreadLocal,
3638  ConstGlobalsPtrTy->getAddressSpace());
3639  GV->setSection(AnnotationSection);
3640  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3641  auto *Bitcasted = llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(GV, ConstGlobalsPtrTy);
3642 
3643  // Set the look-up reference to the final annotation value for future
3644  // annotations to reuse.
3645  LookupRef = Bitcasted;
3646  return Bitcasted;
3647 }

3652  assert(A && "no add_ir_attributes_global_variable attribute");

3655  for (const std::pair<std::string, std::string> &NameValuePair :
3656  NameValuePairs)
