3669 bool CodeGenModule::isInNoSanitizeList(SanitizerMask Kind, llvm::Function *Fn,
3670  SourceLocation Loc) const {
3671  const auto &NoSanitizeL = getContext().getNoSanitizeList();
3672  // NoSanitize by function name.
3673  if (NoSanitizeL.containsFunction(Kind, Fn->getName()))
3674  return true;
3675  // NoSanitize by location. Check "mainfile" prefix.
3676  auto &SM = Context.getSourceManager();
3677  FileEntryRef MainFile = *SM.getFileEntryRefForID(SM.getMainFileID());
3678  if (NoSanitizeL.containsMainFile(Kind, MainFile.getName()))
3679  return true;
3680 
3681  // Check "src" prefix.
3682  if (Loc.isValid())
3683  return NoSanitizeL.containsLocation(Kind, Loc);
3684  // If location is unknown, this may be a compiler-generated function. Assume
3685  // it's located in the main file.
3686  return NoSanitizeL.containsFile(Kind, MainFile.getName());
3687 }
3688 
3689 bool CodeGenModule::isInNoSanitizeList(SanitizerMask Kind,
3690  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV,
3691  SourceLocation Loc, QualType Ty,
3692  StringRef Category) const {
3693  const auto &NoSanitizeL = getContext().getNoSanitizeList();
3694  if (NoSanitizeL.containsGlobal(Kind, GV->getName(), Category))
3695  return true;
3696  auto &SM = Context.getSourceManager();
3697  if (NoSanitizeL.containsMainFile(
3698  Kind, SM.getFileEntryRefForID(SM.getMainFileID())->getName(),
3699  Category))
3700  return true;
3701  if (NoSanitizeL.containsLocation(Kind, Loc, Category))
3702  return true;
3703 
3704  // Check global type.
3705  if (!Ty.isNull()) {
3706  // Drill down the array types: if global variable of a fixed type is
3707  // not sanitized, we also don't instrument arrays of them.
3708  while (auto AT = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(Ty.getTypePtr()))
3709  Ty = AT->getElementType();
3710  Ty = Ty.getCanonicalType().getUnqualifiedType();
3711  // Only record types (classes, structs etc.) are ignored.
3712  if (Ty->isRecordType()) {
3713  std::string TypeStr = Ty.getAsString(getContext().getPrintingPolicy());
3714  if (NoSanitizeL.containsType(Kind, TypeStr, Category))
3715  return true;
3716  }
3717  }
3718  return false;
3719 }
3720 
3721 bool CodeGenModule::imbueXRayAttrs(llvm::Function *Fn, SourceLocation Loc,
3722  StringRef Category) const {
3723  const auto &XRayFilter = getContext().getXRayFilter();
3724  using ImbueAttr = XRayFunctionFilter::ImbueAttribute;
3725  auto Attr = ImbueAttr::NONE;
3726  if (Loc.isValid())
3727  Attr = XRayFilter.shouldImbueLocation(Loc, Category);
3728  if (Attr == ImbueAttr::NONE)
3729  Attr = XRayFilter.shouldImbueFunction(Fn->getName());
3730  switch (Attr) {
3731  case ImbueAttr::NONE:
3732  return false;
3733  case ImbueAttr::ALWAYS:
3734  Fn->addFnAttr("function-instrument", "xray-always");
3735  break;
3736  case ImbueAttr::ALWAYS_ARG1:
3737  Fn->addFnAttr("function-instrument", "xray-always");
3738  Fn->addFnAttr("xray-log-args", "1");
3739  break;
3740  case ImbueAttr::NEVER:
3741  Fn->addFnAttr("function-instrument", "xray-never");
3742  break;
3743  }
3744  return true;
3745 }
3746 
3747 ProfileList::ExclusionType
3748 CodeGenModule::isFunctionBlockedByProfileList(llvm::Function *Fn,
3749  SourceLocation Loc) const {
3750  const auto &ProfileList = getContext().getProfileList();
3751  // If the profile list is empty, then instrument everything.
3752  if (ProfileList.isEmpty())
3753  return ProfileList::Allow;
3754  CodeGenOptions::ProfileInstrKind Kind = getCodeGenOpts().getProfileInstr();
3755  // First, check the function name.
3756  if (auto V = ProfileList.isFunctionExcluded(Fn->getName(), Kind))
3757  return *V;
3758  // Next, check the source location.
3759  if (Loc.isValid())
3760  if (auto V = ProfileList.isLocationExcluded(Loc, Kind))
3761  return *V;
3762  // If location is unknown, this may be a compiler-generated function. Assume
3763  // it's located in the main file.
3764  auto &SM = Context.getSourceManager();
3765  if (auto MainFile = SM.getFileEntryRefForID(SM.getMainFileID()))
3766  if (auto V = ProfileList.isFileExcluded(MainFile->getName(), Kind))
3767  return *V;
3768  return ProfileList.getDefault(Kind);
3769 }
3770 
3771 ProfileList::ExclusionType
3772 CodeGenModule::isFunctionBlockedFromProfileInstr(llvm::Function *Fn,
3773  SourceLocation Loc) const {
3774  auto V = isFunctionBlockedByProfileList(Fn, Loc);
3775  if (V != ProfileList::Allow)
3776  return V;
3777 
3778  auto NumGroups = getCodeGenOpts().ProfileTotalFunctionGroups;
3779  if (NumGroups > 1) {
3780  auto Group = llvm::crc32(arrayRefFromStringRef(Fn->getName())) % NumGroups;
3781  if (Group != getCodeGenOpts().ProfileSelectedFunctionGroup)
3782  return ProfileList::Skip;
3783  }
3784  return ProfileList::Allow;
3785 }
3786 
3787 bool CodeGenModule::MustBeEmitted(const ValueDecl *Global) {
3788  // Never defer when EmitAllDecls is specified.
3789  if (LangOpts.EmitAllDecls)
3790  return true;
3791 
3792  const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Global);
3793  if (VD &&
3794  ((CodeGenOpts.KeepPersistentStorageVariables &&
3795  (VD->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static ||
3796  VD->getStorageDuration() == SD_Thread)) ||
3797  (CodeGenOpts.KeepStaticConsts && VD->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static &&
3798  VD->getType().isConstQualified())))
3799  return true;
3800 
3801  return getContext().DeclMustBeEmitted(Global);
3802 }
3803 
3804 bool CodeGenModule::MayBeEmittedEagerly(const ValueDecl *Global) {
3805  // In OpenMP 5.0 variables and function may be marked as
3806  // device_type(host/nohost) and we should not emit them eagerly unless we sure
3807  // that they must be emitted on the host/device. To be sure we need to have
3808  // seen a declare target with an explicit mentioning of the function, we know
3809  // we have if the level of the declare target attribute is -1. Note that we
3810  // check somewhere else if we should emit this at all.
3811  if (LangOpts.OpenMP >= 50 && !LangOpts.OpenMPSimd) {
3812  std::optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr *> ActiveAttr =
3813  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::getActiveAttr(Global);
3814  if (!ActiveAttr || (*ActiveAttr)->getLevel() != (unsigned)-1)
3815  return false;
3816  }
3817 
3818  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Global)) {
3819  if (FD->getTemplateSpecializationKind() == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation)
3820  // Implicit template instantiations may change linkage if they are later
3821  // explicitly instantiated, so they should not be emitted eagerly.
3822  return false;
3823  // Defer until all versions have been semantically checked.
3824  if (FD->hasAttr<TargetVersionAttr>() && !FD->isMultiVersion())
3825  return false;
3826  }
3827  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Global)) {
3828  if (Context.getInlineVariableDefinitionKind(VD) ==
3829  ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::WeakUnknown)
3830  // A definition of an inline constexpr static data member may change
3831  // linkage later if it's redeclared outside the class.
3832  return false;
3833  if (CXX20ModuleInits && VD->getOwningModule() &&
3834  !VD->getOwningModule()->isModuleMapModule()) {
3835  // For CXX20, module-owned initializers need to be deferred, since it is
3836  // not known at this point if they will be run for the current module or
3837  // as part of the initializer for an imported one.
3838  return false;
3839  }
3840  }
3841  // If OpenMP is enabled and threadprivates must be generated like TLS, delay
3842  // codegen for global variables, because they may be marked as threadprivate.
3843  if (LangOpts.OpenMP && LangOpts.OpenMPUseTLS &&
3844  getContext().getTargetInfo().isTLSSupported() && isa<VarDecl>(Global) &&
3845  !Global->getType().isConstantStorage(getContext(), false, false) &&
3846  !OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(Global))
3847  return false;
3848 
3849  return true;
3850 }
3851 
3852 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfMSGuidDecl(const MSGuidDecl *GD) {
3853  StringRef Name = getMangledName(GD);
3854 
3855  // The UUID descriptor should be pointer aligned.
3856  CharUnits Alignment = CharUnits::fromQuantity(PointerAlignInBytes);
3857 
3858  // Look for an existing global.
3859  if (llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = getModule().getNamedGlobal(Name))
3860  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
3861 
3862  ConstantEmitter Emitter(*this);
3863  llvm::Constant *Init;
3864 
3865  APValue &V = GD->getAsAPValue();
3866  if (!V.isAbsent()) {
3867  // If possible, emit the APValue version of the initializer. In particular,
3868  // this gets the type of the constant right.
3869  Init = Emitter.emitForInitializer(
3870  GD->getAsAPValue(), GD->getType().getAddressSpace(), GD->getType());
3871  } else {
3872  // As a fallback, directly construct the constant.
3873  // FIXME: This may get padding wrong under esoteric struct layout rules.
3874  // MSVC appears to create a complete type 'struct __s_GUID' that it
3875  // presumably uses to represent these constants.
3876  MSGuidDecl::Parts Parts = GD->getParts();
3877  llvm::Constant *Fields[4] = {
3878  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int32Ty, Parts.Part1),
3879  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int16Ty, Parts.Part2),
3880  llvm::ConstantInt::get(Int16Ty, Parts.Part3),
3881  llvm::ConstantDataArray::getRaw(
3882  StringRef(reinterpret_cast<char *>(Parts.Part4And5), 8), 8,
3883  Int8Ty)};
3884  Init = llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Fields);
3885  }
3886 
3887  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
3888  getModule(), Init->getType(),
3889  /*isConstant=*/true, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage, Init, Name);
3890  if (supportsCOMDAT())
3891  GV->setComdat(TheModule.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
3892  setDSOLocal(GV);
3893 
3894  if (!V.isAbsent()) {
3895  Emitter.finalize(GV);
3896  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
3897  }
3898 
3899  llvm::Type *Ty = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(GD->getType());
3900  return ConstantAddress(GV, Ty, Alignment);
3901 }
3902 
3903 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfUnnamedGlobalConstantDecl(
3904  const UnnamedGlobalConstantDecl *GCD) {
3905  CharUnits Alignment = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(GCD->getType());
3906 
3907  llvm::GlobalVariable **Entry = nullptr;
3908  Entry = &UnnamedGlobalConstantDeclMap[GCD];
3909  if (*Entry)
3910  return ConstantAddress(*Entry, (*Entry)->getValueType(), Alignment);
3911 
3912  ConstantEmitter Emitter(*this);
3913  llvm::Constant *Init;
3914 
3915  const APValue &V = GCD->getValue();
3916 
3917  assert(!V.isAbsent());
3918  Init = Emitter.emitForInitializer(V, GCD->getType().getAddressSpace(),
3919  GCD->getType());
3920 
3921  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), Init->getType(),
3922  /*isConstant=*/true,
3923  llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, Init,
3924  ".constant");
3925  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
3926  GV->setAlignment(Alignment.getAsAlign());
3927 
3928  Emitter.finalize(GV);
3929 
3930  *Entry = GV;
3931  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
3932 }
3933 
3934 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfTemplateParamObject(
3935  const TemplateParamObjectDecl *TPO) {
3936  StringRef Name = getMangledName(TPO);
3937  CharUnits Alignment = getNaturalTypeAlignment(TPO->getType());
3938 
3939  if (llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = getModule().getNamedGlobal(Name))
3940  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
3941 
3942  ConstantEmitter Emitter(*this);
3943  llvm::Constant *Init = Emitter.emitForInitializer(
3944  TPO->getValue(), TPO->getType().getAddressSpace(), TPO->getType());
3945 
3946  if (!Init) {
3947  ErrorUnsupported(TPO, "template parameter object");
3948  return ConstantAddress::invalid();
3949  }
3950 
3951  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage =
3952  isExternallyVisible(TPO->getLinkageAndVisibility().getLinkage())
3953  ? llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage
3954  : llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
3955  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), Init->getType(),
3956  /*isConstant=*/true, Linkage, Init, Name);
3957  setGVProperties(GV, TPO);
3958  if (supportsCOMDAT())
3959  GV->setComdat(TheModule.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
3960  Emitter.finalize(GV);
3961 
3962  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
3963 }
3964 
3965 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetWeakRefReference(const ValueDecl *VD) {
3966  const AliasAttr *AA = VD->getAttr<AliasAttr>();
3967  assert(AA && "No alias?");
3968 
3969  CharUnits Alignment = getContext().getDeclAlign(VD);
3970  llvm::Type *DeclTy = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType());
3971 
3972  // See if there is already something with the target's name in the module.
3973  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(AA->getAliasee());
3974  if (Entry)
3975  return ConstantAddress(Entry, DeclTy, Alignment);
3976 
3977  llvm::Constant *Aliasee;
3978  if (isa<llvm::FunctionType>(DeclTy))
3979  Aliasee = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(AA->getAliasee(), DeclTy,
3980  GlobalDecl(cast<FunctionDecl>(VD)),
3981  /*ForVTable=*/false);
3982  else
3983  Aliasee = GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(AA->getAliasee(), DeclTy, LangAS::Default,
3984  nullptr);
3985 
3986  auto *F = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Aliasee);
3987  F->setLinkage(llvm::Function::ExternalWeakLinkage);
3988  WeakRefReferences.insert(F);
3989 
3990  return ConstantAddress(Aliasee, DeclTy, Alignment);
3991 }
3992 
3993 template <typename AttrT> static bool hasImplicitAttr(const ValueDecl *D) {
3994  if (!D)
3995  return false;
3996  if (auto *A = D->getAttr<AttrT>())
3997  return A->isImplicit();
3998  return D->isImplicit();
3999 }
4000 
4001 void CodeGenModule::EmitGlobal(GlobalDecl GD) {
4002  const auto *Global = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4003 
4004  // Weak references don't produce any output by themselves.
4005  if (Global->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>())
4006  return;
4007 
4008  // If this is an alias definition (which otherwise looks like a declaration)
4009  // handle it now.
4010  if (AliasAttr *Attr = Global->getAttr<AliasAttr>()) {
4011  // Emit the alias here if it is not SYCL device compilation.
4012  if (!LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
4013  return EmitAliasDefinition(GD);
4014  // Defer for SYCL devices, until either the alias or what it aliases
4015  // is used.
4016  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
4017  DeferredDecls[MangledName] = GD;
4018  StringRef AliaseeName = Attr->getAliasee();
4019  DeferredAliases[AliaseeName] = GD;
4020  return;
4021  }
4022 
4023  // IFunc like an alias whose value is resolved at runtime by calling resolver.
4024  if (Global->hasAttr<IFuncAttr>())
4025  return emitIFuncDefinition(GD);
4026 
4027  // If this is a cpu_dispatch multiversion function, emit the resolver.
4028  if (Global->hasAttr<CPUDispatchAttr>())
4029  return emitCPUDispatchDefinition(GD);
4030 
4031  // If this is CUDA, be selective about which declarations we emit.
4032  // Non-constexpr non-lambda implicit host device functions are not emitted
4033  // unless they are used on device side.
4034  if (LangOpts.CUDA) {
4035  if (LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice) {
4036  const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Global);
4037  if ((!Global->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() ||
4038  (LangOpts.OffloadImplicitHostDeviceTemplates && FD &&
4039  hasImplicitAttr<CUDAHostAttr>(FD) &&
4040  hasImplicitAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>(FD) && !FD->isConstexpr() &&
4041  !isLambdaCallOperator(FD) &&
4042  !getContext().CUDAImplicitHostDeviceFunUsedByDevice.count(FD))) &&
4043  !Global->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>() &&
4044  !Global->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>() &&
4045  !Global->hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>() &&
4046  !Global->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceType() &&
4047  !Global->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureType() &&
4048  !(LangOpts.HIPStdPar && isa<FunctionDecl>(Global) &&
4049  !Global->hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>()))
4050  return;
4051  } else {
4052  // We need to emit host-side 'shadows' for all global
4053  // device-side variables because the CUDA runtime needs their
4054  // size and host-side address in order to provide access to
4055  // their device-side incarnations.
4056 
4057  // So device-only functions are the only things we skip, except for SYCL.
4058  if (!LangOpts.isSYCL() && isa<FunctionDecl>(Global) &&
4059  !Global->hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>() && Global->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>())
4060  return;
4061 
4062  assert((isa<FunctionDecl>(Global) || isa<VarDecl>(Global)) &&
4063  "Expected Variable or Function");
4064  }
4065  }
4066 
4067  if (LangOpts.OpenMP) {
4068  // If this is OpenMP, check if it is legal to emit this global normally.
4069  if (OpenMPRuntime && OpenMPRuntime->emitTargetGlobal(GD))
4070  return;
4071  if (auto *DRD = dyn_cast<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(Global)) {
4072  if (MustBeEmitted(Global))
4073  EmitOMPDeclareReduction(DRD);
4074  return;
4075  }
4076  if (auto *DMD = dyn_cast<OMPDeclareMapperDecl>(Global)) {
4077  if (MustBeEmitted(Global))
4078  EmitOMPDeclareMapper(DMD);
4079  return;
4080  }
4081  }
4082 
4083  // Ignore declarations, they will be emitted on their first use.
4084  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Global)) {
4085  // Update deferred annotations with the latest declaration if the function
4086  // function was already used or defined.
4087  if (FD->hasAttr<AnnotateAttr>()) {
4088  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
4089  if (GetGlobalValue(MangledName))
4090  DeferredAnnotations[MangledName] = FD;
4091  }
4092 
4093  // Forward declarations are emitted lazily on first use.
4094  if (!FD->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody()) {
4095  if (!FD->doesDeclarationForceExternallyVisibleDefinition() &&
4096  (!FD->isMultiVersion() ||
4097  !FD->getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().isAArch64()))
4098  return;
4099 
4100  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
4101 
4102  // Compute the function info and LLVM type.
4103  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
4104  llvm::Type *Ty = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
4105 
4106  GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(MangledName, Ty, GD, /*ForVTable=*/false,
4107  /*DontDefer=*/false);
4108  return;
4109  }
4110  } else {
4111  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(Global);
4112  assert(VD->isFileVarDecl() && "Cannot emit local var decl as global.");
4113  if (VD->isThisDeclarationADefinition() != VarDecl::Definition &&
4114  !Context.isMSStaticDataMemberInlineDefinition(VD)) {
4115  if (LangOpts.OpenMP) {
4116  // Emit declaration of the must-be-emitted declare target variable.
4117  if (std::optional<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MapTypeTy> Res =
4118  OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(VD)) {
4119 
4120  // If this variable has external storage and doesn't require special
4121  // link handling we defer to its canonical definition.
4122  if (VD->hasExternalStorage() &&
4123  Res != OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Link)
4124  return;
4125 
4126  bool UnifiedMemoryEnabled =
4127  getOpenMPRuntime().hasRequiresUnifiedSharedMemory();
4128  if ((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To ||
4129  *Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Enter) &&
4130  !UnifiedMemoryEnabled) {
4131  (void)GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
4132  } else {
4133  assert(((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Link) ||
4134  ((*Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_To ||
4135  *Res == OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::MT_Enter) &&
4136  UnifiedMemoryEnabled)) &&
4137  "Link clause or to clause with unified memory expected.");
4138  (void)getOpenMPRuntime().getAddrOfDeclareTargetVar(VD);
4139  }
4140 
4141  return;
4142  }
4143  }
4144  // If this declaration may have caused an inline variable definition to
4145  // change linkage, make sure that it's emitted.
4146  if (Context.getInlineVariableDefinitionKind(VD) ==
4147  ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::Strong)
4148  GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
4149  return;
4150  }
4151  }
4152 
4153  // clang::ParseAST ensures that we emit the SYCL devices at the end, so
4154  // anything that is a device (or indirectly called) will be handled later.
4155  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && MustBeEmitted(Global)) {
4156  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
4157  return;
4158  }
4159 
4160  // Defer code generation to first use when possible, e.g. if this is an inline
4161  // function. If the global must always be emitted, do it eagerly if possible
4162  // to benefit from cache locality.
4163  if (MustBeEmitted(Global) && MayBeEmittedEagerly(Global)) {
4164  // Avoid emitting the same __host__ __device__ functions,
4165  // in SYCL-CUDA-host compilation, and
4166  if (SYCLCUDAIsHost(LangOpts) && isa<FunctionDecl>(Global) &&
4167  !Global->hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>() && Global->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()) {
4168  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
4169  return;
4170  }
4171  // in SYCL-CUDA-device compilation.
4172  if (SYCLCUDAIsSYCLDevice(LangOpts) && isa<FunctionDecl>(Global) &&
4173  Global->hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>() && !Global->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()) {
4174  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
4175  return;
4176  }
4177 
4178  // Emit the definition if it can't be deferred.
4179  EmitGlobalDefinition(GD);
4180  addEmittedDeferredDecl(GD);
4181  return;
4182  }
4183 
4184  // If we're deferring emission of a C++ variable with an
4185  // initializer, remember the order in which it appeared in the file.
4186  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && isa<VarDecl>(Global) &&
4187  cast<VarDecl>(Global)->hasInit()) {
4188  DelayedCXXInitPosition[Global] = CXXGlobalInits.size();
4189  CXXGlobalInits.push_back(nullptr);
4190  }
4191 
4192  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
4193  if (GetGlobalValue(MangledName) != nullptr) {
4194  // The value has already been used and should therefore be emitted.
4195  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
4196  } else if (MustBeEmitted(Global)) {
4197  // The value must be emitted, but cannot be emitted eagerly.
4198  assert(!MayBeEmittedEagerly(Global));
4199  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
4200  } else {
4201 
4202  // For SYCL compilation of CUDA sources,
4203  if (LangOpts.isSYCL() && LangOpts.CUDA && !LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice) {
4204  // in case of SYCL-CUDA-host,
4205  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsHost) {
4206  if (Global->hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>()) {
4207  // remove already present __device__ function.
4208  auto DDI = DeferredDecls.find(MangledName);
4209  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end())
4210  DeferredDecls.erase(DDI);
4211  } else if (Global->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()) {
4212  // do not insert a __device__ function if a __host__ one is present.
4213  auto DDI = DeferredDecls.find(MangledName);
4214  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end())
4215  return;
4216  }
4217  }
4218  // in case of SYCL-CUDA-device,
4219  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
4220  if (Global->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()) {
4221  // remove already present __host__ function.
4222  auto DDI = DeferredDecls.find(MangledName);
4223  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end())
4224  DeferredDecls.erase(DDI);
4225  } else if (Global->hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>()) {
4226  // do not insert a __host__ function if a __device__ one is present.
4227  auto DDI = DeferredDecls.find(MangledName);
4228  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end())
4229  return;
4230  }
4231  }
4232  }
4233 
4234  // Otherwise, remember that we saw a deferred decl with this name. The
4235  // first use of the mangled name will cause it to move into
4236  // DeferredDeclsToEmit.
4237  DeferredDecls[MangledName] = GD;
4238  }
4239 }

4241 // Check if T is a class type with a destructor that's not dllimport.
4242 static bool HasNonDllImportDtor(QualType T) {
4243  if (const auto *RT = T->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAs<RecordType>())
4244  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl()))
4245  if (RD->getDestructor() && !RD->getDestructor()->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
4246  return true;
4247 
4248  return false;
4249 }

4251 namespace {
4252  struct FunctionIsDirectlyRecursive
4253  : public ConstStmtVisitor<FunctionIsDirectlyRecursive, bool> {
4254  const StringRef Name;
4255  const Builtin::Context &BI;
4256  FunctionIsDirectlyRecursive(StringRef N, const Builtin::Context &C)
4257  : Name(N), BI(C) {}
4258 
4259  bool VisitCallExpr(const CallExpr *E) {
4260  const FunctionDecl *FD = E->getDirectCallee();
4261  if (!FD)
4262  return false;
4263  AsmLabelAttr *Attr = FD->getAttr<AsmLabelAttr>();
4264  if (Attr && Name == Attr->getLabel())
4265  return true;
4266  unsigned BuiltinID = FD->getBuiltinID();
4267  if (!BuiltinID || !BI.isLibFunction(BuiltinID))
4268  return false;
4269  StringRef BuiltinName = BI.getName(BuiltinID);
4270  if (BuiltinName.starts_with("__builtin_") &&
4271  Name == BuiltinName.slice(strlen("__builtin_"), StringRef::npos)) {
4272  return true;
4273  }
4274  return false;
4275  }
4276 
4277  bool VisitStmt(const Stmt *S) {
4278  for (const Stmt *Child : S->children())
4279  if (Child && this->Visit(Child))
4280  return true;
4281  return false;
4282  }
4283  };
4284 
4285  // Make sure we're not referencing non-imported vars or functions.
4286  struct DLLImportFunctionVisitor
4287  : public RecursiveASTVisitor<DLLImportFunctionVisitor> {
4288  bool SafeToInline = true;
4289 
4290  bool shouldVisitImplicitCode() const { return true; }
4291 
4292  bool VisitVarDecl(VarDecl *VD) {
4293  if (VD->getTLSKind()) {
4294  // A thread-local variable cannot be imported.
4295  SafeToInline = false;
4296  return SafeToInline;
4297  }
4298 
4299  // A variable definition might imply a destructor call.
4300  if (VD->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
4301  SafeToInline = !HasNonDllImportDtor(VD->getType());
4302 
4303  return SafeToInline;
4304  }
4305 
4306  bool VisitCXXBindTemporaryExpr(CXXBindTemporaryExpr *E) {
4307  if (const auto *D = E->getTemporary()->getDestructor())
4308  SafeToInline = D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
4309  return SafeToInline;
4310  }
4311 
4312  bool VisitDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *E) {
4313  ValueDecl *VD = E->getDecl();
4314  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(VD))
4315  SafeToInline = VD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
4316  else if (VarDecl *V = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(VD))
4317  SafeToInline = !V->hasGlobalStorage() || V->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
4318  return SafeToInline;
4319  }
4320 
4321  bool VisitCXXConstructExpr(CXXConstructExpr *E) {
4322  SafeToInline = E->getConstructor()->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
4323  return SafeToInline;
4324  }
4325 
4326  bool VisitCXXMemberCallExpr(CXXMemberCallExpr *E) {
4327  CXXMethodDecl *M = E->getMethodDecl();
4328  if (!M) {
4329  // Call through a pointer to member function. This is safe to inline.
4330  SafeToInline = true;
4331  } else {
4332  SafeToInline = M->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
4333  }
4334  return SafeToInline;
4335  }
4336 
4337  bool VisitCXXDeleteExpr(CXXDeleteExpr *E) {
4338  SafeToInline = E->getOperatorDelete()->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
4339  return SafeToInline;
4340  }
4341 
4342  bool VisitCXXNewExpr(CXXNewExpr *E) {
4343  SafeToInline = E->getOperatorNew()->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>();
4344  return SafeToInline;
4345  }
4346  };
4347 }
