4349 // isTriviallyRecursive - Check if this function calls another
4350 // decl that, because of the asm attribute or the other decl being a builtin,
4351 // ends up pointing to itself.
4352 bool
4353 CodeGenModule::isTriviallyRecursive(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
4354  StringRef Name;
4355  if (getCXXABI().getMangleContext().shouldMangleDeclName(FD)) {
4356  // asm labels are a special kind of mangling we have to support.
4357  AsmLabelAttr *Attr = FD->getAttr<AsmLabelAttr>();
4358  if (!Attr)
4359  return false;
4360  Name = Attr->getLabel();
4361  } else {
4362  Name = FD->getName();
4363  }
4364 
4365  FunctionIsDirectlyRecursive Walker(Name, Context.BuiltinInfo);
4366  const Stmt *Body = FD->getBody();
4367  return Body ? Walker.Visit(Body) : false;
4368 }
4369 
4370 bool CodeGenModule::shouldEmitFunction(GlobalDecl GD) {
4371  if (getFunctionLinkage(GD) != llvm::Function::AvailableExternallyLinkage)
4372  return true;
4373 
4374  const auto *F = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4375  if (CodeGenOpts.OptimizationLevel == 0 && !F->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>())
4376  return false;
4377 
4378  // We don't import function bodies from other named module units since that
4379  // behavior may break ABI compatibility of the current unit.
4380  if (const Module *M = F->getOwningModule();
4381  M && M->getTopLevelModule()->isNamedModule() &&
4382  getContext().getCurrentNamedModule() != M->getTopLevelModule()) {
4383  // There are practices to mark template member function as always-inline
4384  // and mark the template as extern explicit instantiation but not give
4385  // the definition for member function. So we have to emit the function
4386  // from explicitly instantiation with always-inline.
4387  //
4388  // See https://github.com/llvm/llvm-project/issues/86893 for details.
4389  //
4390  // TODO: Maybe it is better to give it a warning if we call a non-inline
4391  // function from other module units which is marked as always-inline.
4392  if (!F->isTemplateInstantiation() || !F->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>()) {
4393  return false;
4394  }
4395  }
4396 
4397  if (F->hasAttr<NoInlineAttr>())
4398  return false;
4399 
4400  if (F->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>() && !F->hasAttr<AlwaysInlineAttr>()) {
4401  // Check whether it would be safe to inline this dllimport function.
4402  DLLImportFunctionVisitor Visitor;
4403  Visitor.TraverseFunctionDecl(const_cast<FunctionDecl*>(F));
4404  if (!Visitor.SafeToInline)
4405  return false;
4406 
4407  if (const CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(F)) {
4408  // Implicit destructor invocations aren't captured in the AST, so the
4409  // check above can't see them. Check for them manually here.
4410  for (const Decl *Member : Dtor->getParent()->decls())
4411  if (isa<FieldDecl>(Member))
4412  if (HasNonDllImportDtor(cast<FieldDecl>(Member)->getType()))
4413  return false;
4414  for (const CXXBaseSpecifier &B : Dtor->getParent()->bases())
4415  if (HasNonDllImportDtor(B.getType()))
4416  return false;
4417  }
4418  }
4419 
4420  // Inline builtins declaration must be emitted. They often are fortified
4421  // functions.
4422  if (F->isInlineBuiltinDeclaration())
4423  return true;
4424 
4425  // PR9614. Avoid cases where the source code is lying to us. An available
4426  // externally function should have an equivalent function somewhere else,
4427  // but a function that calls itself through asm label/`__builtin_` trickery is
4428  // clearly not equivalent to the real implementation.
4429  // This happens in glibc's btowc and in some configure checks.
4430  return !isTriviallyRecursive(F);
4431 }
4432 
4433 bool CodeGenModule::shouldOpportunisticallyEmitVTables() {
4434  return CodeGenOpts.OptimizationLevel > 0;
4435 }
4436 
4437 void CodeGenModule::EmitMultiVersionFunctionDefinition(GlobalDecl GD,
4438  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
4439  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4440 
4441  if (FD->isCPUSpecificMultiVersion()) {
4442  auto *Spec = FD->getAttr<CPUSpecificAttr>();
4443  for (unsigned I = 0; I < Spec->cpus_size(); ++I)
4444  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GD.getWithMultiVersionIndex(I), nullptr);
4445  } else if (auto *TC = FD->getAttr<TargetClonesAttr>()) {
4446  for (unsigned I = 0; I < TC->featuresStrs_size(); ++I)
4447  // AArch64 favors the default target version over the clone if any.
4448  if ((!TC->isDefaultVersion(I) || !getTarget().getTriple().isAArch64()) &&
4449  TC->isFirstOfVersion(I))
4450  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GD.getWithMultiVersionIndex(I), nullptr);
4451  // Ensure that the resolver function is also emitted.
4452  GetOrCreateMultiVersionResolver(GD);
4453  } else
4454  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GD, GV);
4455  // Defer the resolver emission until we can reason whether the TU
4456  // contains a default target version implementation.
4457  if (FD->isTargetVersionMultiVersion())
4458  AddDeferredMultiVersionResolverToEmit(GD);
4459 }
4460 
4461 void CodeGenModule::EmitGlobalDefinition(GlobalDecl GD, llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
4462  const auto *D = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4463 
4464  PrettyStackTraceDecl CrashInfo(const_cast<ValueDecl *>(D), D->getLocation(),
4465  Context.getSourceManager(),
4466  "Generating code for declaration");
4467 
4468  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4469  // At -O0, don't generate IR for functions with available_externally
4470  // linkage.
4471  if (!shouldEmitFunction(GD))
4472  return;
4473 
4474  llvm::TimeTraceScope TimeScope("CodeGen Function", [&]() {
4475  std::string Name;
4476  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Name);
4477  FD->getNameForDiagnostic(OS, getContext().getPrintingPolicy(),
4478  /*Qualified=*/true);
4479  return Name;
4480  });
4481 
4482  if (const auto *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
4483  // Make sure to emit the definition(s) before we emit the thunks.
4484  // This is necessary for the generation of certain thunks.
4485  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(Method) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(Method))
4486  ABI->emitCXXStructor(GD);
4487  else if (FD->isMultiVersion())
4488  EmitMultiVersionFunctionDefinition(GD, GV);
4489  else
4490  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GD, GV);
4491 
4492  if (Method->isVirtual())
4493  getVTables().EmitThunks(GD);
4494 
4495  return;
4496  }
4497 
4498  if (FD->isMultiVersion())
4499  return EmitMultiVersionFunctionDefinition(GD, GV);
4500  return EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GD, GV);
4501  }
4502 
4503  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
4504  return EmitGlobalVarDefinition(VD, !VD->hasDefinition());
4505 
4506  llvm_unreachable("Invalid argument to EmitGlobalDefinition()");
4507 }
4508 
4509 static void ReplaceUsesOfNonProtoTypeWithRealFunction(llvm::GlobalValue *Old,
4510  llvm::Function *NewFn);
4511 
4512 static unsigned
4513 TargetMVPriority(const TargetInfo &TI,
4514  const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &RO) {
4515  unsigned Priority = 0;
4516  unsigned NumFeatures = 0;
4517  for (StringRef Feat : RO.Conditions.Features) {
4518  Priority = std::max(Priority, TI.multiVersionSortPriority(Feat));
4519  NumFeatures++;
4520  }
4521 
4522  if (!RO.Conditions.Architecture.empty())
4523  Priority = std::max(
4524  Priority, TI.multiVersionSortPriority(RO.Conditions.Architecture));
4525 
4526  Priority += TI.multiVersionFeatureCost() * NumFeatures;
4527 
4528  return Priority;
4529 }
4530 
4531 // Multiversion functions should be at most 'WeakODRLinkage' so that a different
4532 // TU can forward declare the function without causing problems. Particularly
4533 // in the cases of CPUDispatch, this causes issues. This also makes sure we
4534 // work with internal linkage functions, so that the same function name can be
4535 // used with internal linkage in multiple TUs.
4536 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes getMultiversionLinkage(CodeGenModule &CGM,
4537  GlobalDecl GD) {
4538  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4539  if (FD->getFormalLinkage() == Linkage::Internal)
4540  return llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
4541  return llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage;
4542 }
4543 
4544 static FunctionDecl *createDefaultTargetVersionFrom(const FunctionDecl *FD) {
4545  DeclContext *DeclCtx = FD->getASTContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
4546  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = FD->getTypeSourceInfo();
4547  StorageClass SC = FD->getStorageClass();
4548  DeclarationName Name = FD->getNameInfo().getName();
4549 
4550  FunctionDecl *NewDecl =
4551  FunctionDecl::Create(FD->getASTContext(), DeclCtx, FD->getBeginLoc(),
4552  FD->getEndLoc(), Name, TInfo->getType(), TInfo, SC);
4553 
4554  NewDecl->setIsMultiVersion();
4555  NewDecl->addAttr(TargetVersionAttr::CreateImplicit(
4556  NewDecl->getASTContext(), "default", NewDecl->getSourceRange()));
4557 
4558  return NewDecl;
4559 }
4560 
4561 void CodeGenModule::emitMultiVersionFunctions() {
4562  std::vector<GlobalDecl> MVFuncsToEmit;
4563  MultiVersionFuncs.swap(MVFuncsToEmit);
4564  for (GlobalDecl GD : MVFuncsToEmit) {
4565  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4566  assert(FD && "Expected a FunctionDecl");
4567 
4568  auto createFunction = [&](const FunctionDecl *Decl, unsigned MVIdx = 0) {
4569  GlobalDecl CurGD{Decl->isDefined() ? Decl->getDefinition() : Decl, MVIdx};
4570  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(CurGD);
4571  llvm::Constant *Func = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
4572  if (!Func) {
4573  if (Decl->isDefined()) {
4574  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(CurGD, nullptr);
4575  Func = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
4576  } else {
4577  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(CurGD);
4578  llvm::FunctionType *Ty = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
4579  Func = GetAddrOfFunction(CurGD, Ty, /*ForVTable=*/false,
4580  /*DontDefer=*/false, ForDefinition);
4581  }
4582  assert(Func && "This should have just been created");
4583  }
4584  return cast<llvm::Function>(Func);
4585  };
4586 
4587  bool HasDefaultDecl = !FD->isTargetVersionMultiVersion();
4588  bool ShouldEmitResolver =
4589  !getContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().isAArch64();
4590  SmallVector<CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption, 10> Options;
4591 
4592  getContext().forEachMultiversionedFunctionVersion(
4593  FD, [&](const FunctionDecl *CurFD) {
4594  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 8> Feats;
4595 
4596  if (const auto *TA = CurFD->getAttr<TargetAttr>()) {
4597  TA->getAddedFeatures(Feats);
4598  llvm::Function *Func = createFunction(CurFD);
4599  Options.emplace_back(Func, TA->getArchitecture(), Feats);
4600  } else if (const auto *TVA = CurFD->getAttr<TargetVersionAttr>()) {
4601  bool HasDefaultDef = TVA->isDefaultVersion() &&
4602  CurFD->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody();
4603  HasDefaultDecl |= TVA->isDefaultVersion();
4604  ShouldEmitResolver |= (CurFD->isUsed() || HasDefaultDef);
4605  TVA->getFeatures(Feats);
4606  llvm::Function *Func = createFunction(CurFD);
4607  Options.emplace_back(Func, /*Architecture*/ "", Feats);
4608  } else if (const auto *TC = CurFD->getAttr<TargetClonesAttr>()) {
4609  ShouldEmitResolver |= CurFD->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody();
4610  for (unsigned I = 0; I < TC->featuresStrs_size(); ++I) {
4611  if (!TC->isFirstOfVersion(I))
4612  continue;
4613 
4614  llvm::Function *Func = createFunction(CurFD, I);
4615  StringRef Architecture;
4616  Feats.clear();
4617  if (getTarget().getTriple().isAArch64())
4618  TC->getFeatures(Feats, I);
4619  else {
4620  StringRef Version = TC->getFeatureStr(I);
4621  if (Version.starts_with("arch="))
4622  Architecture = Version.drop_front(sizeof("arch=") - 1);
4623  else if (Version != "default")
4624  Feats.push_back(Version);
4625  }
4626  Options.emplace_back(Func, Architecture, Feats);
4627  }
4628  } else
4629  llvm_unreachable("unexpected MultiVersionKind");
4630  });
4631 
4632  if (!ShouldEmitResolver)
4633  continue;
4634 
4635  if (!HasDefaultDecl) {
4636  FunctionDecl *NewFD = createDefaultTargetVersionFrom(FD);
4637  llvm::Function *Func = createFunction(NewFD);
4638  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 1> Feats;
4639  Options.emplace_back(Func, /*Architecture*/ "", Feats);
4640  }
4641 
4642  llvm::Constant *ResolverConstant = GetOrCreateMultiVersionResolver(GD);
4643  if (auto *IFunc = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(ResolverConstant)) {
4644  ResolverConstant = IFunc->getResolver();
4645  if (FD->isTargetClonesMultiVersion() ||
4646  FD->isTargetVersionMultiVersion()) {
4647  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
4648  llvm::FunctionType *DeclTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
4649  std::string MangledName = getMangledNameImpl(
4650  *this, GD, FD, /*OmitMultiVersionMangling=*/true);
4651  // In prior versions of Clang, the mangling for ifuncs incorrectly
4652  // included an .ifunc suffix. This alias is generated for backward
4653  // compatibility. It is deprecated, and may be removed in the future.
4654  auto *Alias = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(
4655  DeclTy, 0, getMultiversionLinkage(*this, GD),
4656  MangledName + ".ifunc", IFunc, &getModule());
4657  SetCommonAttributes(FD, Alias);
4658  }
4659  }
4660  llvm::Function *ResolverFunc = cast<llvm::Function>(ResolverConstant);
4661 
4662  ResolverFunc->setLinkage(getMultiversionLinkage(*this, GD));
4663 
4664  if (!ResolverFunc->hasLocalLinkage() && supportsCOMDAT())
4665  ResolverFunc->setComdat(
4666  getModule().getOrInsertComdat(ResolverFunc->getName()));
4667 
4668  const TargetInfo &TI = getTarget();
4669  llvm::stable_sort(
4670  Options, [&TI](const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &LHS,
4671  const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &RHS) {
4672  return TargetMVPriority(TI, LHS) > TargetMVPriority(TI, RHS);
4673  });
4674  CodeGenFunction CGF(*this);
4675  CGF.EmitMultiVersionResolver(ResolverFunc, Options);
4676  }
4677 
4678  // Ensure that any additions to the deferred decls list caused by emitting a
4679  // variant are emitted. This can happen when the variant itself is inline and
4680  // calls a function without linkage.
4681  if (!MVFuncsToEmit.empty())
4682  EmitDeferred();
4683 
4684  // Ensure that any additions to the multiversion funcs list from either the
4685  // deferred decls or the multiversion functions themselves are emitted.
4686  if (!MultiVersionFuncs.empty())
4687  emitMultiVersionFunctions();
4688 }
4689 
4690 void CodeGenModule::emitCPUDispatchDefinition(GlobalDecl GD) {
4691  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4692  assert(FD && "Not a FunctionDecl?");
4693  assert(FD->isCPUDispatchMultiVersion() && "Not a multiversion function?");
4694  const auto *DD = FD->getAttr<CPUDispatchAttr>();
4695  assert(DD && "Not a cpu_dispatch Function?");
4696 
4697  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
4698  llvm::FunctionType *DeclTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
4699 
4700  StringRef ResolverName = getMangledName(GD);
4701  UpdateMultiVersionNames(GD, FD, ResolverName);
4702 
4703  llvm::Type *ResolverType;
4704  GlobalDecl ResolverGD;
4705  if (getTarget().supportsIFunc()) {
4706  ResolverType = llvm::FunctionType::get(
4707  llvm::PointerType::get(DeclTy,
4708  getTypes().getTargetAddressSpace(FD->getType())),
4709  false);
4710  }
4711  else {
4712  ResolverType = DeclTy;
4713  ResolverGD = GD;
4714  }
4715 
4716  auto *ResolverFunc = cast<llvm::Function>(GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
4717  ResolverName, ResolverType, ResolverGD, /*ForVTable=*/false));
4718  ResolverFunc->setLinkage(getMultiversionLinkage(*this, GD));
4719  if (supportsCOMDAT())
4720  ResolverFunc->setComdat(
4721  getModule().getOrInsertComdat(ResolverFunc->getName()));
4722 
4723  SmallVector<CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption, 10> Options;
4724  const TargetInfo &Target = getTarget();
4725  unsigned Index = 0;
4726  for (const IdentifierInfo *II : DD->cpus()) {
4727  // Get the name of the target function so we can look it up/create it.
4728  std::string MangledName = getMangledNameImpl(*this, GD, FD, true) +
4729  getCPUSpecificMangling(*this, II->getName());
4730 
4731  llvm::Constant *Func = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
4732 
4733  if (!Func) {
4734  GlobalDecl ExistingDecl = Manglings.lookup(MangledName);
4735  if (ExistingDecl.getDecl() &&
4736  ExistingDecl.getDecl()->getAsFunction()->isDefined()) {
4737  EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(ExistingDecl, nullptr);
4738  Func = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
4739  } else {
4740  if (!ExistingDecl.getDecl())
4741  ExistingDecl = GD.getWithMultiVersionIndex(Index);
4742 
4743  Func = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
4744  MangledName, DeclTy, ExistingDecl,
4745  /*ForVTable=*/false, /*DontDefer=*/true,
4746  /*IsThunk=*/false, llvm::AttributeList(), ForDefinition);
4747  }
4748  }
4749 
4750  llvm::SmallVector<StringRef, 32> Features;
4751  Target.getCPUSpecificCPUDispatchFeatures(II->getName(), Features);
4752  llvm::transform(Features, Features.begin(),
4753  [](StringRef Str) { return Str.substr(1); });
4754  llvm::erase_if(Features, [&Target](StringRef Feat) {
4755  return !Target.validateCpuSupports(Feat);
4756  });
4757  Options.emplace_back(cast<llvm::Function>(Func), StringRef{}, Features);
4758  ++Index;
4759  }
4760 
4761  llvm::stable_sort(
4762  Options, [](const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &LHS,
4763  const CodeGenFunction::MultiVersionResolverOption &RHS) {
4764  return llvm::X86::getCpuSupportsMask(LHS.Conditions.Features) >
4765  llvm::X86::getCpuSupportsMask(RHS.Conditions.Features);
4766  });
4767 
4768  // If the list contains multiple 'default' versions, such as when it contains
4769  // 'pentium' and 'generic', don't emit the call to the generic one (since we
4770  // always run on at least a 'pentium'). We do this by deleting the 'least
4771  // advanced' (read, lowest mangling letter).
4772  while (Options.size() > 1 &&
4773  llvm::all_of(llvm::X86::getCpuSupportsMask(
4774  (Options.end() - 2)->Conditions.Features),
4775  [](auto X) { return X == 0; })) {
4776  StringRef LHSName = (Options.end() - 2)->Function->getName();
4777  StringRef RHSName = (Options.end() - 1)->Function->getName();
4778  if (LHSName.compare(RHSName) < 0)
4779  Options.erase(Options.end() - 2);
4780  else
4781  Options.erase(Options.end() - 1);
4782  }
4783 
4784  CodeGenFunction CGF(*this);
4785  CGF.EmitMultiVersionResolver(ResolverFunc, Options);
4786 
4787  if (getTarget().supportsIFunc()) {
4788  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = getMultiversionLinkage(*this, GD);
4789  auto *IFunc = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(GetOrCreateMultiVersionResolver(GD));
4790 
4791  // Fix up function declarations that were created for cpu_specific before
4792  // cpu_dispatch was known
4793  if (!isa<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(IFunc)) {
4794  assert(cast<llvm::Function>(IFunc)->isDeclaration());
4795  auto *GI = llvm::GlobalIFunc::create(DeclTy, 0, Linkage, "", ResolverFunc,
4796  &getModule());
4797  GI->takeName(IFunc);
4798  IFunc->replaceAllUsesWith(GI);
4799  IFunc->eraseFromParent();
4800  IFunc = GI;
4801  }
4802 
4803  std::string AliasName = getMangledNameImpl(
4804  *this, GD, FD, /*OmitMultiVersionMangling=*/true);
4805  llvm::Constant *AliasFunc = GetGlobalValue(AliasName);
4806  if (!AliasFunc) {
4807  auto *GA = llvm::GlobalAlias::create(DeclTy, 0, Linkage, AliasName, IFunc,
4808  &getModule());
4809  SetCommonAttributes(GD, GA);
4810  }
4811  }
4812 }
4813 
4814 /// Adds a declaration to the list of multi version functions if not present.
4815 void CodeGenModule::AddDeferredMultiVersionResolverToEmit(GlobalDecl GD) {
4816  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4817  assert(FD && "Not a FunctionDecl?");
4818 
4819  if (FD->isTargetVersionMultiVersion() || FD->isTargetClonesMultiVersion()) {
4820  std::string MangledName =
4821  getMangledNameImpl(*this, GD, FD, /*OmitMultiVersionMangling=*/true);
4822  if (!DeferredResolversToEmit.insert(MangledName).second)
4823  return;
4824  }
4825  MultiVersionFuncs.push_back(GD);
4826 }
4827 
4828 /// If a dispatcher for the specified mangled name is not in the module, create
4829 /// and return an llvm Function with the specified type.
4830 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetOrCreateMultiVersionResolver(GlobalDecl GD) {
4831  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
4832  assert(FD && "Not a FunctionDecl?");
4833 
4834  std::string MangledName =
4835  getMangledNameImpl(*this, GD, FD, /*OmitMultiVersionMangling=*/true);
4836 
4837  // Holds the name of the resolver, in ifunc mode this is the ifunc (which has
4838  // a separate resolver).
4839  std::string ResolverName = MangledName;
4840  if (getTarget().supportsIFunc()) {
4841  switch (FD->getMultiVersionKind()) {
4842  case MultiVersionKind::None:
4843  llvm_unreachable("unexpected MultiVersionKind::None for resolver");
4844  case MultiVersionKind::Target:
4845  case MultiVersionKind::CPUSpecific:
4846  case MultiVersionKind::CPUDispatch:
4847  ResolverName += ".ifunc";
4848  break;
4849  case MultiVersionKind::TargetClones:
4850  case MultiVersionKind::TargetVersion:
4851  break;
4852  }
4853  } else if (FD->isTargetMultiVersion()) {
4854  ResolverName += ".resolver";
4855  }
4856 
4857  // If the resolver has already been created, just return it.
4858  if (llvm::GlobalValue *ResolverGV = GetGlobalValue(ResolverName))
4859  return ResolverGV;
4860 
4861  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
4862  llvm::FunctionType *DeclTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
4863 
4864  // The resolver needs to be created. For target and target_clones, defer
4865  // creation until the end of the TU.
4866  if (FD->isTargetMultiVersion() || FD->isTargetClonesMultiVersion())
4867  MultiVersionFuncs.push_back(GD);
4868 
4869  // For cpu_specific, don't create an ifunc yet because we don't know if the
4870  // cpu_dispatch will be emitted in this translation unit.
4871  if (getTarget().supportsIFunc() && !FD->isCPUSpecificMultiVersion()) {
4872  llvm::Type *ResolverType = llvm::FunctionType::get(
4873  llvm::PointerType::get(DeclTy,
4874  getTypes().getTargetAddressSpace(FD->getType())),
4875  false);
4876  llvm::Constant *Resolver = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
4877  MangledName + ".resolver", ResolverType, GlobalDecl{},
4878  /*ForVTable=*/false);
4879  llvm::GlobalIFunc *GIF =
4880  llvm::GlobalIFunc::create(DeclTy, 0, getMultiversionLinkage(*this, GD),
4881  "", Resolver, &getModule());
4882  GIF->setName(ResolverName);
4883  SetCommonAttributes(FD, GIF);
4884 
4885  return GIF;
4886  }
4887 
4888  llvm::Constant *Resolver = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
4889  ResolverName, DeclTy, GlobalDecl{}, /*ForVTable=*/false);
4890  assert(isa<llvm::GlobalValue>(Resolver) &&
4891  "Resolver should be created for the first time");
4892  SetCommonAttributes(FD, cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Resolver));
4893  return Resolver;
4894 }
4895 
4896 /// GetOrCreateLLVMFunction - If the specified mangled name is not in the
4897 /// module, create and return an llvm Function with the specified type. If there
4898 /// is something in the module with the specified name, return it potentially
4899 /// bitcasted to the right type.
4900 ///
4901 /// If D is non-null, it specifies a decl that correspond to this. This is used
4902 /// to set the attributes on the function when it is first created.
4903 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
4904  StringRef MangledName, llvm::Type *Ty, GlobalDecl GD, bool ForVTable,
4905  bool DontDefer, bool IsThunk, llvm::AttributeList ExtraAttrs,
4906  ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
4907  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
4908 
4909  // Any attempts to use a MultiVersion function should result in retrieving
4910  // the iFunc instead. Name Mangling will handle the rest of the changes.
4911  if (const FunctionDecl *FD = cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
4912  // For the device mark the function as one that should be emitted.
4913  if (getLangOpts().OpenMPIsTargetDevice && OpenMPRuntime &&
4914  !OpenMPRuntime->markAsGlobalTarget(GD) && FD->isDefined() &&
4915  !DontDefer && !IsForDefinition) {
4916  if (const FunctionDecl *FDDef = FD->getDefinition()) {
4917  GlobalDecl GDDef;
4918  if (const auto *CD = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(FDDef))
4919  GDDef = GlobalDecl(CD, GD.getCtorType());
4920  else if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(FDDef))
4921  GDDef = GlobalDecl(DD, GD.getDtorType());
4922  else
4923  GDDef = GlobalDecl(FDDef);
4924  EmitGlobal(GDDef);
4925  }
4926  }
4927 
4928  if (FD->isMultiVersion()) {
4929  UpdateMultiVersionNames(GD, FD, MangledName);
4930  if (FD->getASTContext().getTargetInfo().getTriple().isAArch64() &&
4931  !FD->isUsed())
4932  AddDeferredMultiVersionResolverToEmit(GD);
4933  else if (!IsForDefinition)
4934  return GetOrCreateMultiVersionResolver(GD);
4935  }
4936  }
4937 
4938  // Lookup the entry, lazily creating it if necessary.
4939  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
4940  if (Entry) {
4941  if (WeakRefReferences.erase(Entry)) {
4942  const FunctionDecl *FD = cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(D);
4943  if (FD && !FD->hasAttr<WeakAttr>())
4944  Entry->setLinkage(llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage);
4945  }
4946 
4947  // Handle dropped DLL attributes.
4948  if (D && !D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>() && !D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>() &&
4949  !shouldMapVisibilityToDLLExport(cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(D))) {
4950  Entry->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass);
4951  setDSOLocal(Entry);
4952  }
4953 
4954  // If there are two attempts to define the same mangled name, issue an
4955  // error.
4956  if (IsForDefinition && !Entry->isDeclaration()) {
4957  GlobalDecl OtherGD;
4958  // Check that GD is not yet in DiagnosedConflictingDefinitions is required
4959  // to make sure that we issue an error only once.
4960  if (lookupRepresentativeDecl(MangledName, OtherGD) &&
4961  (GD.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl() !=
4962  OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl()) &&
4963  DiagnosedConflictingDefinitions.insert(GD).second) {
4964  getDiags().Report(D->getLocation(), diag::err_duplicate_mangled_name)
4965  << MangledName;
4966  getDiags().Report(OtherGD.getDecl()->getLocation(),
4967  diag::note_previous_definition);
4968  }
4969  }
4970 
4971  if ((isa<llvm::Function>(Entry) || isa<llvm::GlobalAlias>(Entry)) &&
4972  (Entry->getValueType() == Ty)) {
4973  return Entry;
4974  }
4975 
4976  // Make sure the result is of the correct type.
4977  // (If function is requested for a definition, we always need to create a new
4978  // function, not just return a bitcast.)
4979  if (!IsForDefinition)
4980  return Entry;
4981  }
4982 
4983  // This function doesn't have a complete type (for example, the return
4984  // type is an incomplete struct). Use a fake type instead, and make
4985  // sure not to try to set attributes.
4986  bool IsIncompleteFunction = false;
4987 
4988  llvm::FunctionType *FTy;
4989  if (isa<llvm::FunctionType>(Ty)) {
4990  FTy = cast<llvm::FunctionType>(Ty);
4991  } else {
4992  FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(VoidTy, false);
4993  IsIncompleteFunction = true;
4994  }
4995 
4996  llvm::Function *F =
4997  llvm::Function::Create(FTy, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
4998  Entry ? StringRef() : MangledName, &getModule());
4999 
5000  // Store the declaration associated with this function so it is potentially
5001  // updated by further declarations or definitions and emitted at the end.
5002  if (D && D->hasAttr<AnnotateAttr>())
5003  DeferredAnnotations[MangledName] = cast<ValueDecl>(D);
5004 
5005  // If we already created a function with the same mangled name (but different
5006  // type) before, take its name and add it to the list of functions to be
5007  // replaced with F at the end of CodeGen.
5008  //
5009  // This happens if there is a prototype for a function (e.g. "int f()") and
5010  // then a definition of a different type (e.g. "int f(int x)").
5011  if (Entry) {
5012  F->takeName(Entry);
5013 
5014  // This might be an implementation of a function without a prototype, in
5015  // which case, try to do special replacement of calls which match the new
5016  // prototype. The really key thing here is that we also potentially drop
5017  // arguments from the call site so as to make a direct call, which makes the
5018  // inliner happier and suppresses a number of optimizer warnings (!) about
5019  // dropping arguments.
5020  if (!Entry->use_empty()) {
5021  ReplaceUsesOfNonProtoTypeWithRealFunction(Entry, F);
5022  Entry->removeDeadConstantUsers();
5023  }
5024 
5025  addGlobalValReplacement(Entry, F);
5026  }
5027 
5028  assert(F->getName() == MangledName && "name was uniqued!");
5029  if (D)
5030  SetFunctionAttributes(GD, F, IsIncompleteFunction, IsThunk);
5031  if (ExtraAttrs.hasFnAttrs()) {
5032  llvm::AttrBuilder B(F->getContext(), ExtraAttrs.getFnAttrs());
5033  F->addFnAttrs(B);
5034  }
5035 
5036  if (!DontDefer) {
5037  // All MSVC dtors other than the base dtor are linkonce_odr and delegate to
5038  // each other bottoming out with the base dtor. Therefore we emit non-base
5039  // dtors on usage, even if there is no dtor definition in the TU.
5040  if (isa_and_nonnull<CXXDestructorDecl>(D) &&
5041  getCXXABI().useThunkForDtorVariant(cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D),
5042  GD.getDtorType()))
5043  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD);
5044 
5045  // This is the first use or definition of a mangled name. If there is a
5046  // deferred decl with this name, remember that we need to emit it at the end
5047  // of the file.
5048  // In SYCL compilation of CUDA sources, avoid the emission if the
5049  // __device__/__host__ attributes do not match.
5050  auto DDI = DeferredDecls.find(MangledName);
5051  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end() &&
5052  (!(getLangOpts().isSYCL() && getLangOpts().CUDA &&
5053  !getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice) ||
5054  ((DDI->second).getDecl()->hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>() ==
5055  D->hasAttr<CUDAHostAttr>() &&
5056  (DDI->second).getDecl()->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() ==
5057  D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>()))) {
5058  // Move the potentially referenced deferred decl to the
5059  // DeferredDeclsToEmit list, and remove it from DeferredDecls (since we
5060  // don't need it anymore).
5061  addDeferredDeclToEmit(DDI->second);
5062  DeferredDecls.erase(DDI);
5063 
5064  // Otherwise, there are cases we have to worry about where we're
5065  // using a declaration for which we must emit a definition but where
5066  // we might not find a top-level definition:
5067  // - member functions defined inline in their classes
5068  // - friend functions defined inline in some class
5069  // - special member functions with implicit definitions
5070  // If we ever change our AST traversal to walk into class methods,
5071  // this will be unnecessary.
5072  //
5073  // We also don't emit a definition for a function if it's going to be an
5074  // entry in a vtable, unless it's already marked as used.
5075  } else if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && D) {
5076  // Look for a declaration that's lexically in a record.
5077  for (const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->getMostRecentDecl(); FD;
5078  FD = FD->getPreviousDecl()) {
5079  if (isa<CXXRecordDecl>(FD->getLexicalDeclContext())) {
5080  if (FD->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody()) {
5081  addDeferredDeclToEmit(GD.getWithDecl(FD));
5082  break;
5083  }
5084  }
5085  }
5086  }
5087  }
5088 
5089  // Make sure the result is of the requested type.
5090  if (!IsIncompleteFunction) {
5091  assert(F->getFunctionType() == Ty);
5092  return F;
5093  }
5094 
5095  return F;
5096 }
5097 
5098 /// GetAddrOfFunction - Return the address of the given function. If Ty is
5099 /// non-null, then this function will use the specified type if it has to
5100 /// create it (this occurs when we see a definition of the function).
5101 llvm::Constant *
5102 CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfFunction(GlobalDecl GD, llvm::Type *Ty, bool ForVTable,
5103  bool DontDefer,
5104  ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
5105  // If there was no specific requested type, just convert it now.
5106  if (!Ty) {
5107  const auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
5108  Ty = getTypes().ConvertType(FD->getType());
5109  }
5110 
5111  // Devirtualized destructor calls may come through here instead of via
5112  // getAddrOfCXXStructor. Make sure we use the MS ABI base destructor instead
5113  // of the complete destructor when necessary.
5114  if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(GD.getDecl())) {
5115  if (getTarget().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() &&
5116  GD.getDtorType() == Dtor_Complete &&
5117  DD->getParent()->getNumVBases() == 0)
5118  GD = GlobalDecl(DD, Dtor_Base);
5119  }
5120 
5121  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
5122  auto *F = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(MangledName, Ty, GD, ForVTable, DontDefer,
5123  /*IsThunk=*/false, llvm::AttributeList(),
5124  IsForDefinition);
5125  // Returns kernel handle for HIP kernel stub function.
5126  if (LangOpts.CUDA && !LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice &&
5127  cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl())->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>()) {
5128  auto *Handle = getCUDARuntime().getKernelHandle(
5129  cast<llvm::Function>(F->stripPointerCasts()), GD);
5130  if (IsForDefinition)
5131  return F;
5132  return Handle;
5133  }
5134  return F;
5135 }
5136 
5137 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetFunctionStart(const ValueDecl *Decl) {
5138  llvm::GlobalValue *F =
5139  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(GetAddrOfFunction(Decl)->stripPointerCasts());
5140 
5141  return llvm::NoCFIValue::get(F);
5142 }
5143 
5144 static const FunctionDecl *
5145 GetRuntimeFunctionDecl(ASTContext &C, StringRef Name) {
5146  TranslationUnitDecl *TUDecl = C.getTranslationUnitDecl();
5147  DeclContext *DC = TranslationUnitDecl::castToDeclContext(TUDecl);
5148 
5149  IdentifierInfo &CII = C.Idents.get(Name);
5150  for (const auto *Result : DC->lookup(&CII))
5151  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Result))
5152  return FD;
5153 
5154  if (!C.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
5155  return nullptr;
5156 
5157  // Demangle the premangled name from getTerminateFn()
5158  IdentifierInfo &CXXII =
5159  (Name == "_ZSt9terminatev" || Name == "?terminate@@YAXXZ")
5160  ? C.Idents.get("terminate")
5161  : C.Idents.get(Name);
5162 
5163  for (const auto &N : {"__cxxabiv1", "std"}) {
5164  IdentifierInfo &NS = C.Idents.get(N);
5165  for (const auto *Result : DC->lookup(&NS)) {
5166  const NamespaceDecl *ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(Result);
5167  if (auto *LSD = dyn_cast<LinkageSpecDecl>(Result))
5168  for (const auto *Result : LSD->lookup(&NS))
5169  if ((ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(Result)))
5170  break;
5171 
5172  if (ND)
5173  for (const auto *Result : ND->lookup(&CXXII))
5174  if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Result))
5175  return FD;
5176  }
5177  }
5178 
5179  return nullptr;
5180 }
5181 
5182 /// CreateRuntimeFunction - Create a new runtime function with the specified
5183 /// type and name.
5184 llvm::FunctionCallee
5185 CodeGenModule::CreateRuntimeFunction(llvm::FunctionType *FTy, StringRef Name,
5186  llvm::AttributeList ExtraAttrs, bool Local,
5187  bool AssumeConvergent) {
5188  if (AssumeConvergent) {
5189  ExtraAttrs =
5190  ExtraAttrs.addFnAttribute(VMContext, llvm::Attribute::Convergent);
5191  }
5192 
5193  llvm::Constant *C =
5194  GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(Name, FTy, GlobalDecl(), /*ForVTable=*/false,
5195  /*DontDefer=*/false, /*IsThunk=*/false,
5196  ExtraAttrs);
5197 
5198  if (auto *F = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(C)) {
5199  if (F->empty()) {
5200  F->setCallingConv(getRuntimeCC());
5201 
5202  // In Windows Itanium environments, try to mark runtime functions
5203  // dllimport. For Mingw and MSVC, don't. We don't really know if the user
5204  // will link their standard library statically or dynamically. Marking
5205  // functions imported when they are not imported can cause linker errors
5206  // and warnings.
5207  if (!Local && getTriple().isWindowsItaniumEnvironment() &&
5208  !getCodeGenOpts().LTOVisibilityPublicStd) {
5209  const FunctionDecl *FD = GetRuntimeFunctionDecl(Context, Name);
5210  if (!FD || FD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
5211  F->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass);
5212  F->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
5213  }
5214  }
5215  setDSOLocal(F);
5216  }
5217  }
5218 
5219  return {FTy, C};
5220 }
5221 
5222 static void maybeEmitPipeStorageMetadata(const VarDecl *D,
5223  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV,
5224  CodeGenModule &CGM) {
5225  // TODO: Applicable only on pipe storages. Currently they are defined
5226  // as structures inside of SYCL headers. Add a check for pipe_storage_t
5227  // when it ready.
5228  QualType PipeTy = D->getType();
5229  if (!PipeTy->isStructureType())
5230  return;
5231 
5232  if (const auto *IOAttr = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelPipeIOAttr>()) {
5233  const auto *CE = cast<ConstantExpr>(IOAttr->getID());
5234  std::optional<llvm::APSInt> ID = CE->getResultAsAPSInt();
5235  llvm::LLVMContext &Context = CGM.getLLVMContext();
5236 
5237  llvm::Metadata *AttrMDArgs[] = {
5238  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
5239  llvm::Type::getInt32Ty(Context), ID->getSExtValue()))};
5240  GV->setMetadata(IOAttr->getSpelling(),
5241  llvm::MDNode::get(Context, AttrMDArgs));
5242  }
5243 }
5244 
5245 /// GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal - If the specified mangled name is not in the module,
5246 /// create and return an llvm GlobalVariable with the specified type and address
5247 /// space. If there is something in the module with the specified name, return
5248 /// it potentially bitcasted to the right type.
5249 ///
5250 /// If D is non-null, it specifies a decl that correspond to this. This is used
5251 /// to set the attributes on the global when it is first created.
5252 ///
5253 /// If IsForDefinition is true, it is guaranteed that an actual global with
5254 /// type Ty will be returned, not conversion of a variable with the same
5255 /// mangled name but some other type.
5256 llvm::Constant *
5257 CodeGenModule::GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(StringRef MangledName, llvm::Type *Ty,
5258  LangAS AddrSpace, const VarDecl *D,
5259  ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
5260  // Lookup the entry, lazily creating it if necessary.
5261  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
5262  unsigned TargetAS = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(AddrSpace);
5263  if (Entry) {
5264  if (WeakRefReferences.erase(Entry)) {
5265  if (D && !D->hasAttr<WeakAttr>())
5266  Entry->setLinkage(llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage);
5267  }
5268 
5269  // Handle dropped DLL attributes.
5270  if (D && !D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>() && !D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>() &&
5271  !shouldMapVisibilityToDLLExport(D))
5272  Entry->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DefaultStorageClass);
5273 
5274  if (LangOpts.OpenMP && !LangOpts.OpenMPSimd && D)
5275  getOpenMPRuntime().registerTargetGlobalVariable(D, Entry);
5276 
5277  if (Entry->getValueType() == Ty && Entry->getAddressSpace() == TargetAS)
5278  return Entry;
5279 
5280  // If there are two attempts to define the same mangled name, issue an
5281  // error.
5282  if (IsForDefinition && !Entry->isDeclaration()) {
5283  GlobalDecl OtherGD;
5284  const VarDecl *OtherD;
5285 
5286  // Check that D is not yet in DiagnosedConflictingDefinitions is required
5287  // to make sure that we issue an error only once.
5288  if (D && lookupRepresentativeDecl(MangledName, OtherGD) &&
5289  (D->getCanonicalDecl() != OtherGD.getCanonicalDecl().getDecl()) &&
5290  (OtherD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(OtherGD.getDecl())) &&
5291  OtherD->hasInit() &&
5292  DiagnosedConflictingDefinitions.insert(D).second) {
5293  getDiags().Report(D->getLocation(), diag::err_duplicate_mangled_name)
5294  << MangledName;
5295  getDiags().Report(OtherGD.getDecl()->getLocation(),
5296  diag::note_previous_definition);
5297  }
5298  }
5299 
5300  // Make sure the result is of the correct type.
5301  if (Entry->getType()->getAddressSpace() != TargetAS)
5302  return llvm::ConstantExpr::getAddrSpaceCast(
5303  Entry, llvm::PointerType::get(Ty->getContext(), TargetAS));
5304 
5305  // (If global is requested for a definition, we always need to create a new
5306  // global, not just return a bitcast.)
5307  if (!IsForDefinition)
5308  return Entry;
5309  }
5310 
5311  auto DAddrSpace = GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(D);
5312 
5313  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
5314  getModule(), Ty, false, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage, nullptr,
5315  MangledName, nullptr, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal,
5316  getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(DAddrSpace));
5317 
5318  // If we already created a global with the same mangled name (but different
5319  // type) before, take its name and remove it from its parent.
5320  if (Entry) {
5321  GV->takeName(Entry);
5322 
5323  if (!Entry->use_empty()) {
5324  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(GV);
5325  }
5326 
5327  Entry->eraseFromParent();
5328  }
5329 
5330  // This is the first use or definition of a mangled name. If there is a
5331  // deferred decl with this name, remember that we need to emit it at the end
5332  // of the file.
5333  auto DDI = DeferredDecls.find(MangledName);
5334  if (DDI != DeferredDecls.end()) {
5335  // Move the potentially referenced deferred decl to the DeferredDeclsToEmit
5336  // list, and remove it from DeferredDecls (since we don't need it anymore).
5337  addDeferredDeclToEmit(DDI->second);
5338  DeferredDecls.erase(DDI);
5339  }
5340 
5341  // Handle things which are present even on external declarations.
5342  if (D) {
5343  if (LangOpts.OpenMP && !LangOpts.OpenMPSimd)
5344  getOpenMPRuntime().registerTargetGlobalVariable(D, GV);
5345 
5346  // FIXME: This code is overly simple and should be merged with other global
5347  // handling.
5348  GV->setConstant(D->getType().isConstantStorage(getContext(), false, false));
5349 
5350  GV->setAlignment(getContext().getDeclAlign(D).getAsAlign());
5351 
5352  setLinkageForGV(GV, D);
5353 
5354  if (D->getTLSKind()) {
5355  if (D->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic)
5356  CXXThreadLocals.push_back(D);
5357  setTLSMode(GV, *D);
5358  }
5359 
5360  setGVProperties(GV, D);
5361 
5362  // If required by the ABI, treat declarations of static data members with
5363  // inline initializers as definitions.
5364  if (getContext().isMSStaticDataMemberInlineDefinition(D)) {
5365  EmitGlobalVarDefinition(D);
5366  }
5367 
5368  // Emit section information for extern variables.
5369  if (D->hasExternalStorage()) {
5370  if (const SectionAttr *SA = D->getAttr<SectionAttr>())
5371  GV->setSection(SA->getName());
5372  }
5373 
5374  // Handle XCore specific ABI requirements.
5375  if (getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::xcore &&
5376  D->getLanguageLinkage() == CLanguageLinkage &&
5377  D->getType().isConstant(Context) &&
5378  isExternallyVisible(D->getLinkageAndVisibility().getLinkage()))
5379  GV->setSection(".cp.rodata");
5380 
5381  // Handle code model attribute
5382  if (const auto *CMA = D->getAttr<CodeModelAttr>())
5383  GV->setCodeModel(CMA->getModel());
5384 
5385  // Check if we a have a const declaration with an initializer, we may be
5386  // able to emit it as available_externally to expose it's value to the
5387  // optimizer.
5388  if (Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && GV->hasExternalLinkage() &&
5389  D->getType().isConstQualified() && !GV->hasInitializer() &&
5390  !D->hasDefinition() && D->hasInit() && !D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
5391  const auto *Record =
5392  Context.getBaseElementType(D->getType())->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
5393  bool HasMutableFields = Record && Record->hasMutableFields();
5394  if (!HasMutableFields) {
5395  const VarDecl *InitDecl;
5396  const Expr *InitExpr = D->getAnyInitializer(InitDecl);
5397  if (InitExpr) {
5398  ConstantEmitter emitter(*this);
5399  llvm::Constant *Init = emitter.tryEmitForInitializer(*InitDecl);
5400  if (Init) {
5401  auto *InitType = Init->getType();
5402  if (GV->getValueType() != InitType) {
5403  // The type of the initializer does not match the definition.
5404  // This happens when an initializer has a different type from
5405  // the type of the global (because of padding at the end of a
5406  // structure for instance).
5407  GV->setName(StringRef());
5408  // Make a new global with the correct type, this is now guaranteed
5409  // to work.
5410  auto *NewGV = cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
5411  GetAddrOfGlobalVar(D, InitType, IsForDefinition)
5412  ->stripPointerCasts());
5413 
5414  // Erase the old global, since it is no longer used.
5415  GV->eraseFromParent();
5416  GV = NewGV;
5417  } else {
5418  GV->setInitializer(Init);
5419  GV->setConstant(true);
5420  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage);
5421  }
5422  emitter.finalize(GV);
5423  }
5424  }
5425  }
5426  }
5427 
5428  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
5429  maybeEmitPipeStorageMetadata(D, GV, *this);
5430  }
5431 
5432  if (D &&
5433  D->isThisDeclarationADefinition(Context) == VarDecl::DeclarationOnly) {
5434  getTargetCodeGenInfo().setTargetAttributes(D, GV, *this);
5435  // External HIP managed variables needed to be recorded for transformation
5436  // in both device and host compilations.
5437  if (getLangOpts().CUDA && D && D->hasAttr<HIPManagedAttr>() &&
5438  D->hasExternalStorage())
5439  getCUDARuntime().handleVarRegistration(D, *GV);
5440  }
5441 
5442  if (D)
5443  SanitizerMD->reportGlobal(GV, *D);
5444 
5445  LangAS ExpectedAS =
5446  D ? D->getType().getAddressSpace()
5447  : (LangOpts.OpenCL ? LangAS::opencl_global : LangAS::Default);
5448  assert(getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(ExpectedAS) == TargetAS);
5449  if (DAddrSpace != ExpectedAS) {
5450  return getTargetCodeGenInfo().performAddrSpaceCast(
5451  *this, GV, DAddrSpace, ExpectedAS,
5452  llvm::PointerType::get(getLLVMContext(), TargetAS));
5453  }
5454 
5455  return GV;
5456 }
5457 
5458 llvm::Constant *
5459 CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfGlobal(GlobalDecl GD, ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
5460  const Decl *D = GD.getDecl();
5461 
5462  if (isa<CXXConstructorDecl>(D) || isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(D))
5463  return getAddrOfCXXStructor(GD, /*FnInfo=*/nullptr, /*FnType=*/nullptr,
5464  /*DontDefer=*/false, IsForDefinition);
5465 
5466  if (isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
5467  auto FInfo =
5468  &getTypes().arrangeCXXMethodDeclaration(cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D));
5469  auto Ty = getTypes().GetFunctionType(*FInfo);
5470  return GetAddrOfFunction(GD, Ty, /*ForVTable=*/false, /*DontDefer=*/false,
5471  IsForDefinition);
5472  }
5473 
5474  if (isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
5475  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
5476  llvm::FunctionType *Ty = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
5477  return GetAddrOfFunction(GD, Ty, /*ForVTable=*/false, /*DontDefer=*/false,
5478  IsForDefinition);
5479  }
5480 
5481  return GetAddrOfGlobalVar(cast<VarDecl>(D), /*Ty=*/nullptr, IsForDefinition);
5482 }
5483 
5484 llvm::GlobalVariable *CodeGenModule::CreateOrReplaceCXXRuntimeVariable(
5485  StringRef Name, llvm::Type *Ty, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage,
5486  llvm::Align Alignment) {
5487  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV = getModule().getNamedGlobal(Name);
5488  llvm::GlobalVariable *OldGV = nullptr;
5489 
5490  if (GV) {
5491  // Check if the variable has the right type.
5492  if (GV->getValueType() == Ty)
5493  return GV;
5494 
5495  // Because C++ name mangling, the only way we can end up with an already
5496  // existing global with the same name is if it has been declared extern "C".
5497  assert(GV->isDeclaration() && "Declaration has wrong type!");
5498  OldGV = GV;
5499  }
5500 
5501  // Create a new variable.
5502  GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), Ty, /*isConstant=*/true,
5503  Linkage, nullptr, Name);
5504 
5505  if (OldGV) {
5506  // Replace occurrences of the old variable if needed.
5507  GV->takeName(OldGV);
5508 
5509  if (!OldGV->use_empty()) {
5510  OldGV->replaceAllUsesWith(GV);
5511  }
5512 
5513  OldGV->eraseFromParent();
5514  }
5515 
5516  if (supportsCOMDAT() && GV->isWeakForLinker() &&
5517  !GV->hasAvailableExternallyLinkage())
5518  GV->setComdat(TheModule.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
5519 
5520  GV->setAlignment(Alignment);
5521 
5522  return GV;
5523 }
5524 
5525 /// GetAddrOfGlobalVar - Return the llvm::Constant for the address of the
5526 /// given global variable. If Ty is non-null and if the global doesn't exist,
5527 /// then it will be created with the specified type instead of whatever the
5528 /// normal requested type would be. If IsForDefinition is true, it is guaranteed
5529 /// that an actual global with type Ty will be returned, not conversion of a
5530 /// variable with the same mangled name but some other type.
5531 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfGlobalVar(const VarDecl *D,
5532  llvm::Type *Ty,
5533  ForDefinition_t IsForDefinition) {
5534  assert(D->hasGlobalStorage() && "Not a global variable");
5535  QualType ASTTy = D->getType();
5536  if (!Ty)
5537  Ty = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ASTTy);
5538 
5539  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(D);
5540  return GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(MangledName, Ty, ASTTy.getAddressSpace(), D,
5541  IsForDefinition);
5542 }
5543 
5544 /// CreateRuntimeVariable - Create a new runtime global variable with the
5545 /// specified type and name.
5546 llvm::Constant *
5547 CodeGenModule::CreateRuntimeVariable(llvm::Type *Ty,
5548  StringRef Name) {
5549  LangAS AddrSpace = getContext().getLangOpts().OpenCL ? LangAS::opencl_global
5550  : LangAS::Default;
5551  auto *Ret = GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(Name, Ty, AddrSpace, nullptr);
5552  setDSOLocal(cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Ret->stripPointerCasts()));
5553  return Ret;
5554 }
5555 
5556 void CodeGenModule::EmitTentativeDefinition(const VarDecl *D) {
5557  assert(!D->getInit() && "Cannot emit definite definitions here!");
5558 
5559  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(D);
5560  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
5561 
5562  // We already have a definition, not declaration, with the same mangled name.
5563  // Emitting of declaration is not required (and actually overwrites emitted
5564  // definition).
5565  if (GV && !GV->isDeclaration())
5566  return;
5567 
5568  // If we have not seen a reference to this variable yet, place it into the
5569  // deferred declarations table to be emitted if needed later.
5570  if (!MustBeEmitted(D) && !GV) {
5571  DeferredDecls[MangledName] = D;
5572  return;
5573  }
5574 
5575  // The tentative definition is the only definition.
5576  EmitGlobalVarDefinition(D);
5577 }
5578 
5579 void CodeGenModule::EmitExternalDeclaration(const VarDecl *D) {
5580  EmitExternalVarDeclaration(D);
5581 }
5582 
5583 CharUnits CodeGenModule::GetTargetTypeStoreSize(llvm::Type *Ty) const {
5584  return Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(
5585  getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSizeInBits(Ty));
5586 }
5587 
5588 LangAS CodeGenModule::GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(const VarDecl *D) {
5589  if (LangOpts.OpenCL) {
5590  LangAS AS = D ? D->getType().getAddressSpace() : LangAS::opencl_global;
5591  assert(AS == LangAS::opencl_global ||
5592  AS == LangAS::opencl_global_device ||
5593  AS == LangAS::opencl_global_host ||
5594  AS == LangAS::opencl_constant ||
5595  AS == LangAS::opencl_local ||
5596  AS >= LangAS::FirstTargetAddressSpace);
5597  return AS;
5598  }
5599 
5600  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && D) {
5601  auto *Scope = D->getAttr<SYCLScopeAttr>();
5602  if (Scope && Scope->isWorkGroup())
5603  return LangAS::sycl_local;
5604  }
5605 
5606  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice &&
5607  (!D || D->getType().getAddressSpace() == LangAS::Default))
5608  return LangAS::sycl_global;
5609 
5610  if (LangOpts.CUDA && LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice) {
5611  if (D) {
5612  if (D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>())
5613  return LangAS::cuda_constant;
5614  if (D->hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>())
5615  return LangAS::cuda_shared;
5616  if (D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>())
5617  return LangAS::cuda_device;
5618  if (D->getType().isConstQualified())
5619  return LangAS::cuda_constant;
5620  }
5621  return LangAS::cuda_device;
5622  }
5623 
5624  if (LangOpts.OpenMP) {
5625  LangAS AS;
5626  if (OpenMPRuntime->hasAllocateAttributeForGlobalVar(D, AS))
5627  return AS;
5628  }
5629  return getTargetCodeGenInfo().getGlobalVarAddressSpace(*this, D);
5630 }
5631 
5632 LangAS CodeGenModule::GetGlobalConstantAddressSpace() const {
5633  // OpenCL v1.2 s6.5.3: a string literal is in the constant address space.
5634  if (LangOpts.OpenCL)
5635  return LangAS::opencl_constant;
5636  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
5637  return LangAS::sycl_global;
5638  if (LangOpts.HIP && LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice && getTriple().isSPIRV())
5639  // For HIPSPV map literals to cuda_device (maps to CrossWorkGroup in SPIR-V)
5640  // instead of default AS (maps to Generic in SPIR-V). Otherwise, we end up
5641  // with OpVariable instructions with Generic storage class which is not
5642  // allowed (SPIR-V V1.6 s3.42.8). Also, mapping literals to SPIR-V
5643  // UniformConstant storage class is not viable as pointers to it may not be
5644  // casted to Generic pointers which are used to model HIP's "flat" pointers.
5645  return LangAS::cuda_device;
5646  if (auto AS = getTarget().getConstantAddressSpace())
5647  return *AS;
5648  return LangAS::Default;
5649 }
5650 
5651 // In address space agnostic languages, string literals are in default address
5652 // space in AST. However, certain targets (e.g. amdgcn) request them to be
5653 // emitted in constant address space in LLVM IR. To be consistent with other
5654 // parts of AST, string literal global variables in constant address space
5655 // need to be casted to default address space before being put into address
5656 // map and referenced by other part of CodeGen.
5657 // In OpenCL, string literals are in constant address space in AST, therefore
5658 // they should not be casted to default address space.
5659 static llvm::Constant *
5660 castStringLiteralToDefaultAddressSpace(CodeGenModule &CGM,
5661  llvm::GlobalVariable *GV) {
5662  llvm::Constant *Cast = GV;
5663  if (!CGM.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
5664  auto AS = CGM.GetGlobalConstantAddressSpace();
5665  if (AS != LangAS::Default)
5666  Cast = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().performAddrSpaceCast(
5667  CGM, GV, AS, LangAS::Default,
5668  llvm::PointerType::get(
5669  CGM.getLLVMContext(),
5670  CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default)));
5671  }
5672  return Cast;
5673 }
5674 
5675 template<typename SomeDecl>
5676 void CodeGenModule::MaybeHandleStaticInExternC(const SomeDecl *D,
5677  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
5678  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
5679  return;
5680 
5681  // Must have 'used' attribute, or else inline assembly can't rely on
5682  // the name existing.
5683  if (!D->template hasAttr<UsedAttr>())
5684  return;
5685 
5686  // Must have internal linkage and an ordinary name.
5687  if (!D->getIdentifier() || D->getFormalLinkage() != Linkage::Internal)
5688  return;
5689 
5690  // Must be in an extern "C" context. Entities declared directly within
5691  // a record are not extern "C" even if the record is in such a context.
5692  const SomeDecl *First = D->getFirstDecl();
5693  if (First->getDeclContext()->isRecord() || !First->isInExternCContext())
5694  return;
5695 
5696  // OK, this is an internal linkage entity inside an extern "C" linkage
5697  // specification. Make a note of that so we can give it the "expected"
5698  // mangled name if nothing else is using that name.
5699  std::pair<StaticExternCMap::iterator, bool> R =
5700  StaticExternCValues.insert(std::make_pair(D->getIdentifier(), GV));
5701 
5702  // If we have multiple internal linkage entities with the same name
5703  // in extern "C" regions, none of them gets that name.
5704  if (!R.second)
5705  R.first->second = nullptr;
5706 }
5707 
5708 static bool shouldBeInCOMDAT(CodeGenModule &CGM, const Decl &D) {
5709  if (!CGM.supportsCOMDAT())
5710  return false;
5711 
5712  if (D.hasAttr<SelectAnyAttr>())
5713  return true;
5714 
5715  GVALinkage Linkage;
5716  if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(&D))
5717  Linkage = CGM.getContext().GetGVALinkageForVariable(VD);
5718  else
5719  Linkage = CGM.getContext().GetGVALinkageForFunction(cast<FunctionDecl>(&D));
5720 
5721  switch (Linkage) {
5722  case GVA_Internal:
5723  case GVA_AvailableExternally:
5724  case GVA_StrongExternal:
5725  return false;
5726  case GVA_DiscardableODR:
5727  case GVA_StrongODR:
5728  return true;
5729  }
5730  llvm_unreachable("No such linkage");
5731 }
5732 
5733 bool CodeGenModule::supportsCOMDAT() const {
5734  return getTriple().supportsCOMDAT();
5735 }
5736 
5737 void CodeGenModule::maybeSetTrivialComdat(const Decl &D,
5738  llvm::GlobalObject &GO) {
5739  if (!shouldBeInCOMDAT(*this, D))
5740  return;
5741  GO.setComdat(TheModule.getOrInsertComdat(GO.getName()));
5742 }
