5744 void CodeGenModule::setAspectsEnumDecl(const EnumDecl *ED) {
5745  if (AspectsEnumDecl && AspectsEnumDecl != ED) {
5746  // Conflicting definitions of the aspect enum are not allowed.
5747  Error(ED->getLocation(), "redefinition of aspect enum");
5748  getDiags().Report(AspectsEnumDecl->getLocation(),
5749  diag::note_previous_definition);
5750  }
5751  AspectsEnumDecl = ED;
5752 }
5753 
5754 void CodeGenModule::generateIntelFPGAAnnotation(
5755  const Decl *D, llvm::SmallString<256> &AnnotStr) {
5756  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(AnnotStr);
5757  if (D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelRegisterAttr>())
5758  Out << "{register:1}";
5759  if (auto const *MA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMemoryAttr>()) {
5760  SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::MemoryKind Kind = MA->getKind();
5761  Out << "{memory:";
5762  switch (Kind) {
5763  case SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::MLAB:
5764  case SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::BlockRAM:
5765  Out << SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::ConvertMemoryKindToStr(Kind);
5766  break;
5767  case SYCLIntelMemoryAttr::Default:
5768  Out << "DEFAULT";
5769  break;
5770  }
5771  Out << '}';
5772  if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<DeclaratorDecl>(D)) {
5773  Out << "{sizeinfo:";
5774  // D can't be of type FunctionDecl (as no memory attribute can be applied
5775  // to a function)
5776  QualType ElementTy = DD->getType();
5777  QualType TmpTy = ElementTy->isArrayType()
5778  ? getContext().getBaseElementType(ElementTy)
5779  : ElementTy;
5780  Out << getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(TmpTy).getQuantity();
5781  // Add the dimension of the array to Out.
5782  while (const auto *AT = getContext().getAsArrayType(ElementTy)) {
5783  // Expecting only constant array types, assert otherwise.
5784  const auto *CAT = cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT);
5785  Out << "," << CAT->getSize();
5786  ElementTy = CAT->getElementType();
5787  }
5788  Out << '}';
5789  }
5790  }
5791  if (D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelSinglePumpAttr>())
5792  Out << "{pump:1}";
5793  if (D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelDoublePumpAttr>())
5794  Out << "{pump:2}";
5795  if (const auto *BWA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelBankWidthAttr>()) {
5796  llvm::APSInt BWAInt = BWA->getValue()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
5797  Out << '{' << BWA->getSpelling() << ':' << BWAInt << '}';
5798  }
5799  if (const auto *PCA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelPrivateCopiesAttr>()) {
5800  llvm::APSInt PCAInt = PCA->getValue()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
5801  Out << '{' << PCA->getSpelling() << ':' << PCAInt << '}';
5802  }
5803  if (const auto *NBA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelNumBanksAttr>()) {
5804  llvm::APSInt NBAInt = NBA->getValue()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
5805  Out << '{' << NBA->getSpelling() << ':' << NBAInt << '}';
5806  }
5807  if (const auto *BBA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelBankBitsAttr>()) {
5808  Out << '{' << BBA->getSpelling() << ':';
5809  for (SYCLIntelBankBitsAttr::args_iterator I = BBA->args_begin(),
5810  E = BBA->args_end();
5811  I != E; ++I) {
5812  if (I != BBA->args_begin())
5813  Out << ',';
5814  llvm::APSInt BBAInt = (*I)->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
5815  Out << BBAInt;
5816  }
5817  Out << '}';
5818  }
5819  if (const auto *MRA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMaxReplicatesAttr>()) {
5820  llvm::APSInt MRAInt = MRA->getValue()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
5821  Out << '{' << MRA->getSpelling() << ':' << MRAInt << '}';
5822  }
5823  if (const auto *MA = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelMergeAttr>()) {
5824  Out << '{' << MA->getSpelling() << ':' << MA->getName() << ':'
5825  << MA->getDirection() << '}';
5826  }
5827  if (D->hasAttr<SYCLIntelSimpleDualPortAttr>())
5828  Out << "{simple_dual_port:1}";
5829  if (const auto *FP2D = D->getAttr<SYCLIntelForcePow2DepthAttr>()) {
5830  llvm::APSInt FP2DInt =
5831  FP2D->getValue()->EvaluateKnownConstInt(getContext());
5832  Out << '{' << FP2D->getSpelling() << ':' << FP2DInt << '}';
5833  }
5834 }
5835 
5836 void CodeGenModule::addGlobalIntelFPGAAnnotation(const VarDecl *VD,
5837  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
5838  SmallString<256> AnnotStr;
5839  generateIntelFPGAAnnotation(VD, AnnotStr);
5840  if (!AnnotStr.empty()) {
5841  // Get the globals for file name, annotation, and the line number.
5842  llvm::Constant *AnnoGV = EmitAnnotationString(AnnotStr),
5843  *UnitGV = EmitAnnotationUnit(VD->getLocation()),
5844  *LineNoCst = EmitAnnotationLineNo(VD->getLocation());
5845 
5846  llvm::Constant *ASZeroGV = GV;
5847  if (GV->getAddressSpace() != 0)
5848  ASZeroGV = llvm::ConstantExpr::getAddrSpaceCast(
5849  GV, GV->getValueType()->getPointerTo(0));
5850 
5851  // Create the ConstantStruct for the global annotation.
5852  llvm::Constant *Fields[5] = {
5853  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(ASZeroGV, Int8PtrTy),
5854  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(AnnoGV, ConstGlobalsPtrTy),
5855  llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(UnitGV, ConstGlobalsPtrTy), LineNoCst,
5856  llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(ConstGlobalsPtrTy)};
5857  Annotations.push_back(llvm::ConstantStruct::getAnon(Fields));
5858  }
5859 }
5860 
5861 /// Pass IsTentative as true if you want to create a tentative definition.
5862 void CodeGenModule::EmitGlobalVarDefinition(const VarDecl *D,
5863  bool IsTentative) {
5864  // OpenCL global variables of sampler type are translated to function calls,
5865  // therefore no need to be translated.
5866  QualType ASTTy = D->getType();
5867  if (getLangOpts().OpenCL && ASTTy->isSamplerT())
5868  return;
5869 
5870  // If this is OpenMP device, check if it is legal to emit this global
5871  // normally.
5872  if (LangOpts.OpenMPIsTargetDevice && OpenMPRuntime &&
5873  OpenMPRuntime->emitTargetGlobalVariable(D))
5874  return;
5875 
5876  llvm::TrackingVH<llvm::Constant> Init;
5877  bool NeedsGlobalCtor = false;
5878  // Whether the definition of the variable is available externally.
5879  // If yes, we shouldn't emit the GloablCtor and GlobalDtor for the variable
5880  // since this is the job for its original source.
5881  bool IsDefinitionAvailableExternally =
5882  getContext().GetGVALinkageForVariable(D) == GVA_AvailableExternally;
5883  bool NeedsGlobalDtor =
5884  !IsDefinitionAvailableExternally &&
5885  D->needsDestruction(getContext()) == QualType::DK_cxx_destructor;
5886 
5887  const VarDecl *InitDecl;
5888  const Expr *InitExpr = D->getAnyInitializer(InitDecl);
5889 
5890  std::optional<ConstantEmitter> emitter;
5891 
5892  // CUDA E.2.4.1 "__shared__ variables cannot have an initialization
5893  // as part of their declaration." Sema has already checked for
5894  // error cases, so we just need to set Init to UndefValue.
5895  bool IsCUDASharedVar =
5896  getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice && D->hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>();
5897  // Shadows of initialized device-side global variables are also left
5898  // undefined.
5899  // Managed Variables should be initialized on both host side and device side.
5900  bool IsCUDAShadowVar =
5901  !getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice && !D->hasAttr<HIPManagedAttr>() &&
5902  (D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>() || D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() ||
5903  D->hasAttr<CUDASharedAttr>());
5904  bool IsCUDADeviceShadowVar =
5905  getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice && !D->hasAttr<HIPManagedAttr>() &&
5906  (D->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceType() ||
5907  D->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureType());
5908  if (getLangOpts().CUDA &&
5909  (IsCUDASharedVar || IsCUDAShadowVar || IsCUDADeviceShadowVar))
5910  Init = llvm::UndefValue::get(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ASTTy));
5911  else if (D->hasAttr<LoaderUninitializedAttr>())
5912  Init = llvm::UndefValue::get(getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(ASTTy));
5913  else if (!InitExpr) {
5914  // This is a tentative definition; tentative definitions are
5915  // implicitly initialized with { 0 }.
5916  //
5917  // Note that tentative definitions are only emitted at the end of
5918  // a translation unit, so they should never have incomplete
5919  // type. In addition, EmitTentativeDefinition makes sure that we
5920  // never attempt to emit a tentative definition if a real one
5921  // exists. A use may still exists, however, so we still may need
5922  // to do a RAUW.
5923  assert(!ASTTy->isIncompleteType() && "Unexpected incomplete type");
5924  Init = EmitNullConstant(D->getType());
5925  } else {
5926  initializedGlobalDecl = GlobalDecl(D);
5927  emitter.emplace(*this);
5928  llvm::Constant *Initializer = emitter->tryEmitForInitializer(*InitDecl);
5929  if (!Initializer) {
5930  QualType T = InitExpr->getType();
5931  if (D->getType()->isReferenceType())
5932  T = D->getType();
5933 
5934  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
5935  if (InitDecl->hasFlexibleArrayInit(getContext()))
5936  ErrorUnsupported(D, "flexible array initializer");
5937  Init = EmitNullConstant(T);
5938 
5939  if (!IsDefinitionAvailableExternally)
5940  NeedsGlobalCtor = true;
5941  } else {
5942  ErrorUnsupported(D, "static initializer");
5943  Init = llvm::UndefValue::get(getTypes().ConvertType(T));
5944  }
5945  } else {
5946  Init = Initializer;
5947  // We don't need an initializer, so remove the entry for the delayed
5948  // initializer position (just in case this entry was delayed) if we
5949  // also don't need to register a destructor.
5950  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && !NeedsGlobalDtor)
5951  DelayedCXXInitPosition.erase(D);
5952 
5953 #ifndef NDEBUG
5954  CharUnits VarSize = getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(ASTTy) +
5955  InitDecl->getFlexibleArrayInitChars(getContext());
5956  CharUnits CstSize = CharUnits::fromQuantity(
5957  getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Init->getType()));
5958  assert(VarSize == CstSize && "Emitted constant has unexpected size");
5959 #endif
5960  }
5961  }
5962 
5963  llvm::Type* InitType = Init->getType();
5964  llvm::Constant *Entry =
5965  GetAddrOfGlobalVar(D, InitType, ForDefinition_t(!IsTentative));
5966 
5967  // Strip off pointer casts if we got them.
5968  Entry = Entry->stripPointerCasts();
5969 
5970  // Entry is now either a Function or GlobalVariable.
5971  auto *GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(Entry);
5972 
5973  // We have a definition after a declaration with the wrong type.
5974  // We must make a new GlobalVariable* and update everything that used OldGV
5975  // (a declaration or tentative definition) with the new GlobalVariable*
5976  // (which will be a definition).
5977  //
5978  // This happens if there is a prototype for a global (e.g.
5979  // "extern int x[];") and then a definition of a different type (e.g.
5980  // "int x[10];"). This also happens when an initializer has a different type
5981  // from the type of the global (this happens with unions).
5982  if (!GV || GV->getValueType() != InitType ||
5983  GV->getType()->getAddressSpace() !=
5984  getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(D))) {
5985 
5986  // Move the old entry aside so that we'll create a new one.
5987  Entry->setName(StringRef());
5988 
5989  // Make a new global with the correct type, this is now guaranteed to work.
5990  GV = cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
5991  GetAddrOfGlobalVar(D, InitType, ForDefinition_t(!IsTentative))
5992  ->stripPointerCasts());
5993 
5994  // Replace all uses of the old global with the new global
5995  llvm::Constant *NewPtrForOldDecl =
5996  llvm::ConstantExpr::getPointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(GV,
5997  Entry->getType());
5998  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(NewPtrForOldDecl);
5999 
6000  // Erase the old global, since it is no longer used.
6001  cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Entry)->eraseFromParent();
6002  }
6003 
6004  MaybeHandleStaticInExternC(D, GV);
6005 
6006  if (D->hasAttr<AnnotateAttr>())
6007  AddGlobalAnnotations(D, GV);
6008 
6009  // Emit Intel FPGA attribute annotation for a file-scope static variable.
6010  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice)
6011  addGlobalIntelFPGAAnnotation(D, GV);
6012 
6013  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice) {
6014  const RecordDecl *RD = D->getType()->getAsRecordDecl();
6015 
6016  if (RD) {
6017  // Add IR attributes if add_ir_attribute_global_variable is attached to
6018  // type.
6019  if (RD->hasAttr<SYCLAddIRAttributesGlobalVariableAttr>())
6020  AddGlobalSYCLIRAttributes(GV, RD);
6021  // If VarDecl has a type decorated with SYCL device_global attribute
6022  // emit IR attribute 'sycl-unique-id'.
6023  if (RD->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>())
6024  addSYCLUniqueID(GV, D, Context);
6025  // If VarDecl type is SYCLTypeAttr::host_pipe, emit the IR attribute
6026  // 'sycl-unique-id'.
6027  if (const auto *Attr = RD->getAttr<SYCLTypeAttr>())
6028  if (Attr->getType() == SYCLTypeAttr::SYCLType::host_pipe)
6029  addSYCLUniqueID(GV, D, Context);
6030  }
6031  }
6032 
6033  if (D->getType().isRestrictQualified()) {
6034  llvm::LLVMContext &Context = getLLVMContext();
6035 
6036  // Common metadata nodes.
6037  llvm::NamedMDNode *GlobalsRestrict =
6038  getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata("globals.restrict");
6039  llvm::Metadata *Args[] = {llvm::ValueAsMetadata::get(GV)};
6040  llvm::MDNode *Node = llvm::MDNode::get(Context, Args);
6041  GlobalsRestrict->addOperand(Node);
6042  }
6043 
6044  // Set the llvm linkage type as appropriate.
6045  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(D);
6046 
6047  // CUDA B.2.1 "The __device__ qualifier declares a variable that resides on
6048  // the device. [...]"
6049  // CUDA B.2.2 "The __constant__ qualifier, optionally used together with
6050  // __device__, declares a variable that: [...]
6051  // Is accessible from all the threads within the grid and from the host
6052  // through the runtime library (cudaGetSymbolAddress() / cudaGetSymbolSize()
6053  // / cudaMemcpyToSymbol() / cudaMemcpyFromSymbol())."
6054  if (LangOpts.CUDA) {
6055  if (LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice) {
6056  if (Linkage != llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage &&
6057  (D->hasAttr<CUDADeviceAttr>() || D->hasAttr<CUDAConstantAttr>() ||
6058  D->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinSurfaceType() ||
6059  D->getType()->isCUDADeviceBuiltinTextureType()))
6060  GV->setExternallyInitialized(true);
6061  } else {
6062  getCUDARuntime().internalizeDeviceSideVar(D, Linkage);
6063  }
6064  getCUDARuntime().handleVarRegistration(D, *GV);
6065  }
6066 
6067  GV->setInitializer(Init);
6068  if (emitter)
6069  emitter->finalize(GV);
6070 
6071  // If it is safe to mark the global 'constant', do so now.
6072  GV->setConstant(!NeedsGlobalCtor && !NeedsGlobalDtor &&
6073  D->getType().isConstantStorage(getContext(), true, true));
6074 
6075  // If it is in a read-only section, mark it 'constant'.
6076  if (const SectionAttr *SA = D->getAttr<SectionAttr>()) {
6077  const ASTContext::SectionInfo &SI = Context.SectionInfos[SA->getName()];
6078  if ((SI.SectionFlags & ASTContext::PSF_Write) == 0)
6079  GV->setConstant(true);
6080  }
6081 
6082  CharUnits AlignVal = getContext().getDeclAlign(D);
6083  // Check for alignment specifed in an 'omp allocate' directive.
6084  if (std::optional<CharUnits> AlignValFromAllocate =
6085  getOMPAllocateAlignment(D))
6086  AlignVal = *AlignValFromAllocate;
6087  GV->setAlignment(AlignVal.getAsAlign());
6088 
6089  // On Darwin, unlike other Itanium C++ ABI platforms, the thread-wrapper
6090  // function is only defined alongside the variable, not also alongside
6091  // callers. Normally, all accesses to a thread_local go through the
6092  // thread-wrapper in order to ensure initialization has occurred, underlying
6093  // variable will never be used other than the thread-wrapper, so it can be
6094  // converted to internal linkage.
6095  //
6096  // However, if the variable has the 'constinit' attribute, it _can_ be
6097  // referenced directly, without calling the thread-wrapper, so the linkage
6098  // must not be changed.
6099  //
6100  // Additionally, if the variable isn't plain external linkage, e.g. if it's
6101  // weak or linkonce, the de-duplication semantics are important to preserve,
6102  // so we don't change the linkage.
6103  if (D->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic &&
6104  Linkage == llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage &&
6105  Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isOSDarwin() &&
6106  !D->hasAttr<ConstInitAttr>())
6107  Linkage = llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage;
6108 
6109  GV->setLinkage(Linkage);
6110  if (D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
6111  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalVariable::DLLImportStorageClass);
6112  else if (D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
6113  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalVariable::DLLExportStorageClass);
6114  else
6115  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalVariable::DefaultStorageClass);
6116 
6117  if (Linkage == llvm::GlobalVariable::CommonLinkage) {
6118  // common vars aren't constant even if declared const.
6119  GV->setConstant(false);
6120  // Tentative definition of global variables may be initialized with
6121  // non-zero null pointers. In this case they should have weak linkage
6122  // since common linkage must have zero initializer and must not have
6123  // explicit section therefore cannot have non-zero initial value.
6124  if (!GV->getInitializer()->isNullValue())
6125  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalVariable::WeakAnyLinkage);
6126  }
6127 
6128  setNonAliasAttributes(D, GV);
6129 
6130  if (D->getTLSKind() && !GV->isThreadLocal()) {
6131  if (D->getTLSKind() == VarDecl::TLS_Dynamic)
6132  CXXThreadLocals.push_back(D);
6133  setTLSMode(GV, *D);
6134  }
6135 
6136  maybeSetTrivialComdat(*D, *GV);
6137 
6138  // Emit the initializer function if necessary.
6139  if (NeedsGlobalCtor || NeedsGlobalDtor)
6140  EmitCXXGlobalVarDeclInitFunc(D, GV, NeedsGlobalCtor);
6141 
6142  SanitizerMD->reportGlobal(GV, *D, NeedsGlobalCtor);
6143 
6144  // Emit global variable debug information.
6145  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6146  if (getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
6147  DI->EmitGlobalVariable(GV, D);
6148 
6149  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
6150  maybeEmitPipeStorageMetadata(D, GV, *this);
6151  // Notify SYCL code generation infrastructure that a global variable is
6152  // being generated.
6153  getSYCLRuntime().actOnGlobalVarEmit(*this, *D, GV);
6154  }
6155 }
6156 
6157 void CodeGenModule::EmitExternalVarDeclaration(const VarDecl *D) {
6158  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6159  if (getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo()) {
6160  QualType ASTTy = D->getType();
6161  llvm::Type *Ty = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(D->getType());
6162  llvm::Constant *GV =
6163  GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(D->getName(), Ty, ASTTy.getAddressSpace(), D);
6164  DI->EmitExternalVariable(
6165  cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(GV->stripPointerCasts()), D);
6166  }
6167 }
6168 
6169 static bool isVarDeclStrongDefinition(const ASTContext &Context,
6170  CodeGenModule &CGM, const VarDecl *D,
6171  bool NoCommon) {
6172  // Don't give variables common linkage if -fno-common was specified unless it
6173  // was overridden by a NoCommon attribute.
6174  if ((NoCommon || D->hasAttr<NoCommonAttr>()) && !D->hasAttr<CommonAttr>())
6175  return true;
6176 
6177  // C11 6.9.2/2:
6178  // A declaration of an identifier for an object that has file scope without
6179  // an initializer, and without a storage-class specifier or with the
6180  // storage-class specifier static, constitutes a tentative definition.
6181  if (D->getInit() || D->hasExternalStorage())
6182  return true;
6183 
6184  // A variable cannot be both common and exist in a section.
6185  if (D->hasAttr<SectionAttr>())
6186  return true;
6187 
6188  // A variable cannot be both common and exist in a section.
6189  // We don't try to determine which is the right section in the front-end.
6190  // If no specialized section name is applicable, it will resort to default.
6191  if (D->hasAttr<PragmaClangBSSSectionAttr>() ||
6192  D->hasAttr<PragmaClangDataSectionAttr>() ||
6193  D->hasAttr<PragmaClangRelroSectionAttr>() ||
6194  D->hasAttr<PragmaClangRodataSectionAttr>())
6195  return true;
6196 
6197  // Thread local vars aren't considered common linkage.
6198  if (D->getTLSKind())
6199  return true;
6200 
6201  // Tentative definitions marked with WeakImportAttr are true definitions.
6202  if (D->hasAttr<WeakImportAttr>())
6203  return true;
6204 
6205  // A variable cannot be both common and exist in a comdat.
6206  if (shouldBeInCOMDAT(CGM, *D))
6207  return true;
6208 
6209  // Declarations with a required alignment do not have common linkage in MSVC
6210  // mode.
6211  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
6212  if (D->hasAttr<AlignedAttr>())
6213  return true;
6214  QualType VarType = D->getType();
6215  if (Context.isAlignmentRequired(VarType))
6216  return true;
6217 
6218  if (const auto *RT = VarType->getAs<RecordType>()) {
6219  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
6220  for (const FieldDecl *FD : RD->fields()) {
6221  if (FD->isBitField())
6222  continue;
6223  if (FD->hasAttr<AlignedAttr>())
6224  return true;
6225  if (Context.isAlignmentRequired(FD->getType()))
6226  return true;
6227  }
6228  }
6229  }
6230 
6231  // Microsoft's link.exe doesn't support alignments greater than 32 bytes for
6232  // common symbols, so symbols with greater alignment requirements cannot be
6233  // common.
6234  // Other COFF linkers (ld.bfd and LLD) support arbitrary power-of-two
6235  // alignments for common symbols via the aligncomm directive, so this
6236  // restriction only applies to MSVC environments.
6237  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple().isKnownWindowsMSVCEnvironment() &&
6238  Context.getTypeAlignIfKnown(D->getType()) >
6239  Context.toBits(CharUnits::fromQuantity(32)))
6240  return true;
6241 
6242  return false;
6243 }
6244 
6245 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes
6246 CodeGenModule::getLLVMLinkageForDeclarator(const DeclaratorDecl *D,
6247  GVALinkage Linkage) {
6248  if (Linkage == GVA_Internal)
6249  return llvm::Function::InternalLinkage;
6250 
6251  if (D->hasAttr<WeakAttr>())
6252  return llvm::GlobalVariable::WeakAnyLinkage;
6253 
6254  if (const auto *FD = D->getAsFunction())
6255  if (FD->isMultiVersion() && Linkage == GVA_AvailableExternally)
6256  return llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkOnceAnyLinkage;
6257 
6258  // We are guaranteed to have a strong definition somewhere else,
6259  // so we can use available_externally linkage.
6260  if (Linkage == GVA_AvailableExternally)
6261  return llvm::GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage;
6262 
6263  // SYCL: Device code is not generally limited to one translation unit, but
6264  // anything accessed from another translation unit is required to be annotated
6265  // with the SYCL_EXTERNAL macro. For any function or variable that does not
6266  // have this, linkonce_odr suffices. If -fno-sycl-rdc is passed, we know there
6267  // is only one translation unit and can so mark them internal.
6268  if (getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice && !D->hasAttr<SYCLKernelAttr>() &&
6269  !D->hasAttr<SYCLDeviceAttr>() &&
6270  !SemaSYCL::isTypeDecoratedWithDeclAttribute<SYCLDeviceGlobalAttr>(
6271  D->getType()))
6272  return getLangOpts().GPURelocatableDeviceCode
6273  ? llvm::Function::LinkOnceODRLinkage
6274  : llvm::Function::InternalLinkage;
6275 
6276  // Note that Apple's kernel linker doesn't support symbol
6277  // coalescing, so we need to avoid linkonce and weak linkages there.
6278  // Normally, this means we just map to internal, but for explicit
6279  // instantiations we'll map to external.
6280 
6281  // In C++, the compiler has to emit a definition in every translation unit
6282  // that references the function. We should use linkonce_odr because
6283  // a) if all references in this translation unit are optimized away, we
6284  // don't need to codegen it. b) if the function persists, it needs to be
6285  // merged with other definitions. c) C++ has the ODR, so we know the
6286  // definition is dependable.
6287  if (Linkage == GVA_DiscardableODR)
6288  return !Context.getLangOpts().AppleKext ? llvm::Function::LinkOnceODRLinkage
6289  : llvm::Function::InternalLinkage;
6290 
6291  // An explicit instantiation of a template has weak linkage, since
6292  // explicit instantiations can occur in multiple translation units
6293  // and must all be equivalent. However, we are not allowed to
6294  // throw away these explicit instantiations.
6295  //
6296  // CUDA/HIP: For -fno-gpu-rdc case, device code is limited to one TU,
6297  // so say that CUDA templates are either external (for kernels) or internal.
6298  // This lets llvm perform aggressive inter-procedural optimizations. For
6299  // -fgpu-rdc case, device function calls across multiple TU's are allowed,
6300  // therefore we need to follow the normal linkage paradigm.
6301  if (Linkage == GVA_StrongODR) {
6302  if (getLangOpts().AppleKext)
6303  return llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage;
6304  if (getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice &&
6305  !getLangOpts().GPURelocatableDeviceCode)
6306  return D->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>() ? llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage
6307  : llvm::Function::InternalLinkage;
6308  return llvm::Function::WeakODRLinkage;
6309  }
6310 
6311  // C++ doesn't have tentative definitions and thus cannot have common
6312  // linkage.
6313  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && isa<VarDecl>(D) &&
6314  !isVarDeclStrongDefinition(Context, *this, cast<VarDecl>(D),
6315  CodeGenOpts.NoCommon))
6316  return llvm::GlobalVariable::CommonLinkage;
6317 
6318  // selectany symbols are externally visible, so use weak instead of
6319  // linkonce. MSVC optimizes away references to const selectany globals, so
6320  // all definitions should be the same and ODR linkage should be used.
6321  // http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/5tkz6s71.aspx
6322  if (D->hasAttr<SelectAnyAttr>())
6323  return llvm::GlobalVariable::WeakODRLinkage;
6324 
6325  // Otherwise, we have strong external linkage.
6326  assert(Linkage == GVA_StrongExternal);
6327  return llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage;
6328 }
6329 
6330 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes
6331 CodeGenModule::getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(const VarDecl *VD) {
6332  GVALinkage Linkage = getContext().GetGVALinkageForVariable(VD);
6333  return getLLVMLinkageForDeclarator(VD, Linkage);
6334 }
6335 
6336 /// Replace the uses of a function that was declared with a non-proto type.
6337 /// We want to silently drop extra arguments from call sites
6338 static void replaceUsesOfNonProtoConstant(llvm::Constant *old,
6339  llvm::Function *newFn) {
6340  // Fast path.
6341  if (old->use_empty()) return;
6342 
6343  llvm::Type *newRetTy = newFn->getReturnType();
6344  SmallVector<llvm::Value*, 4> newArgs;
6345 
6346  for (llvm::Value::use_iterator ui = old->use_begin(), ue = old->use_end();
6347  ui != ue; ) {
6348  llvm::Value::use_iterator use = ui++; // Increment before the use is erased.
6349  llvm::User *user = use->getUser();
6350 
6351  // Recognize and replace uses of bitcasts. Most calls to
6352  // unprototyped functions will use bitcasts.
6353  if (auto *bitcast = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(user)) {
6354  if (bitcast->getOpcode() == llvm::Instruction::BitCast)
6355  replaceUsesOfNonProtoConstant(bitcast, newFn);
6356  continue;
6357  }
6358 
6359  // Recognize calls to the function.
6360  llvm::CallBase *callSite = dyn_cast<llvm::CallBase>(user);
6361  if (!callSite) continue;
6362  if (!callSite->isCallee(&*use))
6363  continue;
6364 
6365  // If the return types don't match exactly, then we can't
6366  // transform this call unless it's dead.
6367  if (callSite->getType() != newRetTy && !callSite->use_empty())
6368  continue;
6369 
6370  // Get the call site's attribute list.
6371  SmallVector<llvm::AttributeSet, 8> newArgAttrs;
6372  llvm::AttributeList oldAttrs = callSite->getAttributes();
6373 
6374  // If the function was passed too few arguments, don't transform.
6375  unsigned newNumArgs = newFn->arg_size();
6376  if (callSite->arg_size() < newNumArgs)
6377  continue;
6378 
6379  // If extra arguments were passed, we silently drop them.
6380  // If any of the types mismatch, we don't transform.
6381  unsigned argNo = 0;
6382  bool dontTransform = false;
6383  for (llvm::Argument &A : newFn->args()) {
6384  if (callSite->getArgOperand(argNo)->getType() != A.getType()) {
6385  dontTransform = true;
6386  break;
6387  }
6388 
6389  // Add any parameter attributes.
6390  newArgAttrs.push_back(oldAttrs.getParamAttrs(argNo));
6391  argNo++;
6392  }
6393  if (dontTransform)
6394  continue;
6395 
6396  // Okay, we can transform this. Create the new call instruction and copy
6397  // over the required information.
6398  newArgs.append(callSite->arg_begin(), callSite->arg_begin() + argNo);
6399 
6400  // Copy over any operand bundles.
6401  SmallVector<llvm::OperandBundleDef, 1> newBundles;
6402  callSite->getOperandBundlesAsDefs(newBundles);
6403 
6404  llvm::CallBase *newCall;
6405  if (isa<llvm::CallInst>(callSite)) {
6406  newCall =
6407  llvm::CallInst::Create(newFn, newArgs, newBundles, "", callSite);
6408  } else {
6409  auto *oldInvoke = cast<llvm::InvokeInst>(callSite);
6410  newCall = llvm::InvokeInst::Create(newFn, oldInvoke->getNormalDest(),
6411  oldInvoke->getUnwindDest(), newArgs,
6412  newBundles, "", callSite);
6413  }
6414  newArgs.clear(); // for the next iteration
6415 
6416  if (!newCall->getType()->isVoidTy())
6417  newCall->takeName(callSite);
6418  newCall->setAttributes(
6419  llvm::AttributeList::get(newFn->getContext(), oldAttrs.getFnAttrs(),
6420  oldAttrs.getRetAttrs(), newArgAttrs));
6421  newCall->setCallingConv(callSite->getCallingConv());
6422 
6423  // Finally, remove the old call, replacing any uses with the new one.
6424  if (!callSite->use_empty())
6425  callSite->replaceAllUsesWith(newCall);
6426 
6427  // Copy debug location attached to CI.
6428  if (callSite->getDebugLoc())
6429  newCall->setDebugLoc(callSite->getDebugLoc());
6430 
6431  callSite->eraseFromParent();
6432  }
6433 }
6434 
6435 /// ReplaceUsesOfNonProtoTypeWithRealFunction - This function is called when we
6436 /// implement a function with no prototype, e.g. "int foo() {}". If there are
6437 /// existing call uses of the old function in the module, this adjusts them to
6438 /// call the new function directly.
6439 ///
6440 /// This is not just a cleanup: the always_inline pass requires direct calls to
6441 /// functions to be able to inline them. If there is a bitcast in the way, it
6442 /// won't inline them. Instcombine normally deletes these calls, but it isn't
6443 /// run at -O0.
6444 static void ReplaceUsesOfNonProtoTypeWithRealFunction(llvm::GlobalValue *Old,
6445  llvm::Function *NewFn) {
6446  // If we're redefining a global as a function, don't transform it.
6447  if (!isa<llvm::Function>(Old)) return;
6448 
6449  replaceUsesOfNonProtoConstant(Old, NewFn);
6450 }
6451 
6452 void CodeGenModule::HandleCXXStaticMemberVarInstantiation(VarDecl *VD) {
6453  auto DK = VD->isThisDeclarationADefinition();
6454  if (DK == VarDecl::Definition && VD->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>())
6455  return;
6456 
6457  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK = VD->getTemplateSpecializationKind();
6458  // If we have a definition, this might be a deferred decl. If the
6459  // instantiation is explicit, make sure we emit it at the end.
6460  if (VD->getDefinition() && TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition)
6461  GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD);
6462 
6463  EmitTopLevelDecl(VD);
6464 }
6465 
6466 void CodeGenModule::EmitGlobalFunctionDefinition(GlobalDecl GD,
6467  llvm::GlobalValue *GV) {
6468  const auto *D = cast<FunctionDecl>(GD.getDecl());
6469 
6470  // Compute the function info and LLVM type.
6471  const CGFunctionInfo &FI = getTypes().arrangeGlobalDeclaration(GD);
6472  llvm::FunctionType *Ty = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FI);
6473 
6474  // Get or create the prototype for the function.
6475  if (!GV || (GV->getValueType() != Ty))
6476  GV = cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(GetAddrOfFunction(GD, Ty, /*ForVTable=*/false,
6477  /*DontDefer=*/true,
6478  ForDefinition));
6479 
6480  // Already emitted.
6481  if (!GV->isDeclaration())
6482  return;
6483 
6484  // We need to set linkage and visibility on the function before
6485  // generating code for it because various parts of IR generation
6486  // want to propagate this information down (e.g. to local static
6487  // declarations).
6488  auto *Fn = cast<llvm::Function>(GV);
6489  setFunctionLinkage(GD, Fn);
6490 
6491  // FIXME: this is redundant with part of setFunctionDefinitionAttributes
6492  setGVProperties(Fn, GD);
6493 
6494  MaybeHandleStaticInExternC(D, Fn);
6495 
6496  maybeSetTrivialComdat(*D, *Fn);
6497 
6498  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateCode(GD, Fn, FI);
6499 
6500  setNonAliasAttributes(GD, Fn);
6501  SetLLVMFunctionAttributesForDefinition(D, Fn);
6502 
6503  if (const ConstructorAttr *CA = D->getAttr<ConstructorAttr>())
6504  AddGlobalCtor(Fn, CA->getPriority());
6505  if (const DestructorAttr *DA = D->getAttr<DestructorAttr>())
6506  AddGlobalDtor(Fn, DA->getPriority(), true);
6507  if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && D->hasAttr<OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr>())
6508  getOpenMPRuntime().emitDeclareTargetFunction(D, GV);
6509 }
6510 
6511 void CodeGenModule::EmitAliasDefinition(GlobalDecl GD) {
6512  const auto *D = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
6513  const AliasAttr *AA = D->getAttr<AliasAttr>();
6514  assert(AA && "Not an alias?");
6515 
6516  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
6517 
6518  if (AA->getAliasee() == MangledName) {
6519  Diags.Report(AA->getLocation(), diag::err_cyclic_alias) << 0;
6520  return;
6521  }
6522 
6523  // If there is a definition in the module, then it wins over the alias.
6524  // This is dubious, but allow it to be safe. Just ignore the alias.
6525  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
6526  if (Entry && !Entry->isDeclaration())
6527  return;
6528 
6529  Aliases.push_back(GD);
6530 
6531  llvm::Type *DeclTy = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(D->getType());
6532 
6533  // Create a reference to the named value. This ensures that it is emitted
6534  // if a deferred decl.
6535  llvm::Constant *Aliasee;
6536  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes LT;
6537  unsigned AS;
6538  if (isa<llvm::FunctionType>(DeclTy)) {
6539  Aliasee = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(AA->getAliasee(), DeclTy, GD,
6540  /*ForVTable=*/false);
6541  LT = getFunctionLinkage(GD);
6542  AS = Aliasee->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
6543  } else {
6544  LangAS LAS = GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(dyn_cast<VarDecl>(GD.getDecl()));
6545  AS = ArgInfoAddressSpace(LAS);
6546  Aliasee = GetOrCreateLLVMGlobal(AA->getAliasee(), DeclTy, LAS,
6547  /*D=*/nullptr);
6548  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(GD.getDecl()))
6549  LT = getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD);
6550  else
6551  LT = getFunctionLinkage(GD);
6552  }
6553 
6554  // Create the new alias itself, but don't set a name yet.
6555  auto *GA =
6556  llvm::GlobalAlias::create(DeclTy, AS, LT, "", Aliasee, &getModule());
6557 
6558  if (Entry) {
6559  if (GA->getAliasee() == Entry) {
6560  Diags.Report(AA->getLocation(), diag::err_cyclic_alias) << 0;
6561  return;
6562  }
6563 
6564  assert(Entry->isDeclaration());
6565 
6566  // If there is a declaration in the module, then we had an extern followed
6567  // by the alias, as in:
6568  // extern int test6();
6569  // ...
6570  // int test6() __attribute__((alias("test7")));
6571  //
6572  // Remove it and replace uses of it with the alias.
6573  GA->takeName(Entry);
6574 
6575  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(GA);
6576  Entry->eraseFromParent();
6577  } else {
6578  GA->setName(MangledName);
6579  }
6580 
6581  // Set attributes which are particular to an alias; this is a
6582  // specialization of the attributes which may be set on a global
6583  // variable/function.
6584  if (D->hasAttr<WeakAttr>() || D->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>() ||
6585  D->isWeakImported()) {
6586  GA->setLinkage(llvm::Function::WeakAnyLinkage);
6587  }
6588 
6589  if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D))
6590  if (VD->getTLSKind())
6591  setTLSMode(GA, *VD);
6592 
6593  SetCommonAttributes(GD, GA);
6594 
6595  // Emit global alias debug information.
6596  if (isa<VarDecl>(D))
6597  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
6598  DI->EmitGlobalAlias(cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(GA->getAliasee()->stripPointerCasts()), GD);
6599 }
6600 
6601 void CodeGenModule::emitIFuncDefinition(GlobalDecl GD) {
6602  const auto *D = cast<ValueDecl>(GD.getDecl());
6603  const IFuncAttr *IFA = D->getAttr<IFuncAttr>();
6604  assert(IFA && "Not an ifunc?");
6605 
6606  StringRef MangledName = getMangledName(GD);
6607 
6608  if (IFA->getResolver() == MangledName) {
6609  Diags.Report(IFA->getLocation(), diag::err_cyclic_alias) << 1;
6610  return;
6611  }
6612 
6613  // Report an error if some definition overrides ifunc.
6614  llvm::GlobalValue *Entry = GetGlobalValue(MangledName);
6615  if (Entry && !Entry->isDeclaration()) {
6616  GlobalDecl OtherGD;
6617  if (lookupRepresentativeDecl(MangledName, OtherGD) &&
6618  DiagnosedConflictingDefinitions.insert(GD).second) {
6619  Diags.Report(D->getLocation(), diag::err_duplicate_mangled_name)
6620  << MangledName;
6621  Diags.Report(OtherGD.getDecl()->getLocation(),
6622  diag::note_previous_definition);
6623  }
6624  return;
6625  }
6626 
6627  Aliases.push_back(GD);
6628 
6629  llvm::Type *DeclTy = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(D->getType());
6630  llvm::Type *ResolverTy = llvm::GlobalIFunc::getResolverFunctionType(DeclTy);
6631  llvm::Constant *Resolver =
6632  GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(IFA->getResolver(), ResolverTy, {},
6633  /*ForVTable=*/false);
6634  llvm::GlobalIFunc *GIF =
6635  llvm::GlobalIFunc::create(DeclTy, 0, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
6636  "", Resolver, &getModule());
6637  if (Entry) {
6638  if (GIF->getResolver() == Entry) {
6639  Diags.Report(IFA->getLocation(), diag::err_cyclic_alias) << 1;
6640  return;
6641  }
6642  assert(Entry->isDeclaration());
6643 
6644  // If there is a declaration in the module, then we had an extern followed
6645  // by the ifunc, as in:
6646  // extern int test();
6647  // ...
6648  // int test() __attribute__((ifunc("resolver")));
6649  //
6650  // Remove it and replace uses of it with the ifunc.
6651  GIF->takeName(Entry);
6652 
6653  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(GIF);
6654  Entry->eraseFromParent();
6655  } else
6656  GIF->setName(MangledName);
6657  if (auto *F = dyn_cast<llvm::Function>(Resolver)) {
6658  F->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::DisableSanitizerInstrumentation);
6659  }
6660  SetCommonAttributes(GD, GIF);
6661 }
6662 
6663 llvm::Function *CodeGenModule::getIntrinsic(unsigned IID,
6664  ArrayRef<llvm::Type*> Tys) {
6665  return llvm::Intrinsic::getDeclaration(&getModule(), (llvm::Intrinsic::ID)IID,
6666  Tys);
6667 }
6668 
6669 static llvm::StringMapEntry<llvm::GlobalVariable *> &
6670 GetConstantCFStringEntry(llvm::StringMap<llvm::GlobalVariable *> &Map,
6671  const StringLiteral *Literal, bool TargetIsLSB,
6672  bool &IsUTF16, unsigned &StringLength) {
6673  StringRef String = Literal->getString();
6674  unsigned NumBytes = String.size();
6675 
6676  // Check for simple case.
6677  if (!Literal->containsNonAsciiOrNull()) {
6678  StringLength = NumBytes;
6679  return *Map.insert(std::make_pair(String, nullptr)).first;
6680  }
6681 
6682  // Otherwise, convert the UTF8 literals into a string of shorts.
6683  IsUTF16 = true;
6684 
6685  SmallVector<llvm::UTF16, 128> ToBuf(NumBytes + 1); // +1 for ending nulls.
6686  const llvm::UTF8 *FromPtr = (const llvm::UTF8 *)String.data();
6687  llvm::UTF16 *ToPtr = &ToBuf[0];
6688 
6689  (void)llvm::ConvertUTF8toUTF16(&FromPtr, FromPtr + NumBytes, &ToPtr,
6690  ToPtr + NumBytes, llvm::strictConversion);
6691 
6692  // ConvertUTF8toUTF16 returns the length in ToPtr.
6693  StringLength = ToPtr - &ToBuf[0];
6694 
6695  // Add an explicit null.
6696  *ToPtr = 0;
6697  return *Map.insert(std::make_pair(
6698  StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(ToBuf.data()),
6699  (StringLength + 1) * 2),
6700  nullptr)).first;
6701 }
6702 
6703 ConstantAddress
6704 CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfConstantCFString(const StringLiteral *Literal) {
6705  unsigned StringLength = 0;
6706  bool isUTF16 = false;
6707  llvm::StringMapEntry<llvm::GlobalVariable *> &Entry =
6708  GetConstantCFStringEntry(CFConstantStringMap, Literal,
6709  getDataLayout().isLittleEndian(), isUTF16,
6710  StringLength);
6711 
6712  if (auto *C = Entry.second)
6713  return ConstantAddress(
6714  C, C->getValueType(), CharUnits::fromQuantity(C->getAlignment()));
6715 
6716  llvm::Constant *Zero = llvm::Constant::getNullValue(Int32Ty);
6717  llvm::Constant *Zeros[] = { Zero, Zero };
6718 
6719  const ASTContext &Context = getContext();
6720  const llvm::Triple &Triple = getTriple();
6721 
6722  const auto CFRuntime = getLangOpts().CFRuntime;
6723  const bool IsSwiftABI =
6724  static_cast<unsigned>(CFRuntime) >=
6725  static_cast<unsigned>(LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift);
6726  const bool IsSwift4_1 = CFRuntime == LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_1;
6727 
6728  // If we don't already have it, get __CFConstantStringClassReference.
6729  if (!CFConstantStringClassRef) {
6730  const char *CFConstantStringClassName = "__CFConstantStringClassReference";
6731  llvm::Type *Ty = getTypes().ConvertType(getContext().IntTy);
6732  Ty = llvm::ArrayType::get(Ty, 0);
6733 
6734  switch (CFRuntime) {
6735  default: break;
6736  case LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift: [[fallthrough]];
6737  case LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift5_0:
6738  CFConstantStringClassName =
6739  Triple.isOSDarwin() ? "$s15SwiftFoundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN"
6740  : "$s10Foundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN";
6741  Ty = IntPtrTy;
6742  break;
6743  case LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_2:
6744  CFConstantStringClassName =
6745  Triple.isOSDarwin() ? "$S15SwiftFoundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN"
6746  : "$S10Foundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN";
6747  Ty = IntPtrTy;
6748  break;
6749  case LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_1:
6750  CFConstantStringClassName =
6751  Triple.isOSDarwin() ? "__T015SwiftFoundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN"
6752  : "__T010Foundation19_NSCFConstantStringCN";
6753  Ty = IntPtrTy;
6754  break;
6755  }
6756 
6757  llvm::Constant *C = CreateRuntimeVariable(Ty, CFConstantStringClassName);
6758 
6759  if (Triple.isOSBinFormatELF() || Triple.isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
6760  llvm::GlobalValue *GV = nullptr;
6761 
6762  if ((GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(C))) {
6763  IdentifierInfo &II = Context.Idents.get(GV->getName());
6764  TranslationUnitDecl *TUDecl = Context.getTranslationUnitDecl();
6765  DeclContext *DC = TranslationUnitDecl::castToDeclContext(TUDecl);
6766 
6767  const VarDecl *VD = nullptr;
6768  for (const auto *Result : DC->lookup(&II))
6769  if ((VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Result)))
6770  break;
6771 
6772  if (Triple.isOSBinFormatELF()) {
6773  if (!VD)
6774  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
6775  } else {
6776  GV->setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
6777  if (!VD || !VD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>())
6778  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLImportStorageClass);
6779  else
6780  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLExportStorageClass);
6781  }
6782 
6783  setDSOLocal(GV);
6784  }
6785  }
6786 
6787  // Decay array -> ptr
6788  CFConstantStringClassRef =
6789  IsSwiftABI ? llvm::ConstantExpr::getPtrToInt(C, Ty)
6790  : llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(Ty, C, Zeros);
6791  }
6792 
6793  QualType CFTy = Context.getCFConstantStringType();
6794 
6795  auto *STy = cast<llvm::StructType>(getTypes().ConvertType(CFTy));
6796 
6797  ConstantInitBuilder Builder(*this);
6798  auto Fields = Builder.beginStruct(STy);
6799 
6800  // Class pointer.
6801  Fields.add(cast<llvm::Constant>(CFConstantStringClassRef));
6802 
6803  // Flags.
6804  if (IsSwiftABI) {
6805  Fields.addInt(IntPtrTy, IsSwift4_1 ? 0x05 : 0x01);
6806  Fields.addInt(Int64Ty, isUTF16 ? 0x07d0 : 0x07c8);
6807  } else {
6808  Fields.addInt(IntTy, isUTF16 ? 0x07d0 : 0x07C8);
6809  }
6810 
6811  // String pointer.
6812  llvm::Constant *C = nullptr;
6813  if (isUTF16) {
6814  auto Arr = llvm::ArrayRef(
6815  reinterpret_cast<uint16_t *>(const_cast<char *>(Entry.first().data())),
6816  Entry.first().size() / 2);
6817  C = llvm::ConstantDataArray::get(VMContext, Arr);
6818  } else {
6819  C = llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(VMContext, Entry.first());
6820  }
6821 
6822  // Note: -fwritable-strings doesn't make the backing store strings of
6823  // CFStrings writable.
6824  auto *GV =
6825  new llvm::GlobalVariable(getModule(), C->getType(), /*isConstant=*/true,
6826  llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, C, ".str");
6827  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
6828  // Don't enforce the target's minimum global alignment, since the only use
6829  // of the string is via this class initializer.
6830  CharUnits Align = isUTF16 ? Context.getTypeAlignInChars(Context.ShortTy)
6831  : Context.getTypeAlignInChars(Context.CharTy);
6832  GV->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
6833 
6834  // FIXME: We set the section explicitly to avoid a bug in ld64 224.1.
6835  // Without it LLVM can merge the string with a non unnamed_addr one during
6836  // LTO. Doing that changes the section it ends in, which surprises ld64.
6837  if (Triple.isOSBinFormatMachO())
6838  GV->setSection(isUTF16 ? "__TEXT,__ustring"
6839  : "__TEXT,__cstring,cstring_literals");
6840  // Make sure the literal ends up in .rodata to allow for safe ICF and for
6841  // the static linker to adjust permissions to read-only later on.
6842  else if (Triple.isOSBinFormatELF())
6843  GV->setSection(".rodata");
6844 
6845  // String.
6846  llvm::Constant *Str =
6847  llvm::ConstantExpr::getGetElementPtr(GV->getValueType(), GV, Zeros);
6848 
6849  Fields.add(Str);
6850 
6851  // String length.
6852  llvm::IntegerType *LengthTy =
6853  llvm::IntegerType::get(getModule().getContext(),
6854  Context.getTargetInfo().getLongWidth());
6855  if (IsSwiftABI) {
6856  if (CFRuntime == LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_1 ||
6857  CFRuntime == LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_2)
6858  LengthTy = Int32Ty;
6859  else
6860  LengthTy = IntPtrTy;
6861  }
6862  Fields.addInt(LengthTy, StringLength);
6863 
6864  // Swift ABI requires 8-byte alignment to ensure that the _Atomic(uint64_t) is
6865  // properly aligned on 32-bit platforms.
6866  CharUnits Alignment =
6867  IsSwiftABI ? Context.toCharUnitsFromBits(64) : getPointerAlign();
6868 
6869  // The struct.
6870  GV = Fields.finishAndCreateGlobal("_unnamed_cfstring_", Alignment,
6871  /*isConstant=*/false,
6872  llvm::GlobalVariable::PrivateLinkage);
6873  GV->addAttribute("objc_arc_inert");
6874  switch (Triple.getObjectFormat()) {
6875  case llvm::Triple::UnknownObjectFormat:
6876  llvm_unreachable("unknown file format");
6877  case llvm::Triple::DXContainer:
6878  case llvm::Triple::GOFF:
6879  case llvm::Triple::SPIRV:
6880  case llvm::Triple::XCOFF:
6881  llvm_unreachable("unimplemented");
6882  case llvm::Triple::COFF:
6883  case llvm::Triple::ELF:
6884  case llvm::Triple::Wasm:
6885  GV->setSection("cfstring");
6886  break;
6887  case llvm::Triple::MachO:
6888  GV->setSection("__DATA,__cfstring");
6889  break;
6890  }
6891  Entry.second = GV;
6892 
6893  return ConstantAddress(GV, GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
6894 }
6895 
6896 bool CodeGenModule::getExpressionLocationsEnabled() const {
6897  return !CodeGenOpts.EmitCodeView || CodeGenOpts.DebugColumnInfo;
6898 }

6900 QualType CodeGenModule::getObjCFastEnumerationStateType() {
6901  if (ObjCFastEnumerationStateType.isNull()) {
6902  RecordDecl *D = Context.buildImplicitRecord("__objcFastEnumerationState");
6903  D->startDefinition();
6904 
6905  QualType FieldTypes[] = {
6906  Context.UnsignedLongTy, Context.getPointerType(Context.getObjCIdType()),
6907  Context.getPointerType(Context.UnsignedLongTy),
6908  Context.getConstantArrayType(Context.UnsignedLongTy, llvm::APInt(32, 5),
6909  nullptr, ArraySizeModifier::Normal, 0)};
6910 
6911  for (size_t i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
6912  FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(Context,
6913  D,
6914  SourceLocation(),
6915  SourceLocation(), nullptr,
6916  FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
6917  /*BitWidth=*/nullptr,
6918  /*Mutable=*/false,
6919  ICIS_NoInit);
6920  Field->setAccess(AS_public);
6921  D->addDecl(Field);
6922  }
6923 
6924  D->completeDefinition();
6925  ObjCFastEnumerationStateType = Context.getTagDeclType(D);
6926  }
6927 
6928  return ObjCFastEnumerationStateType;
6929 }
6930 
6931 llvm::Constant *
6932 CodeGenModule::GetConstantArrayFromStringLiteral(const StringLiteral *E) {
6933  assert(!E->getType()->isPointerType() && "Strings are always arrays");
6934 
6935  // Don't emit it as the address of the string, emit the string data itself
6936  // as an inline array.
6937  if (E->getCharByteWidth() == 1) {
6938  SmallString<64> Str(E->getString());
6939 
6940  // Resize the string to the right size, which is indicated by its type.
6941  const ConstantArrayType *CAT = Context.getAsConstantArrayType(E->getType());
6942  assert(CAT && "String literal not of constant array type!");
6943  Str.resize(CAT->getZExtSize());
6944  return llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(VMContext, Str, false);
6945  }
6946 
6947  auto *AType = cast<llvm::ArrayType>(getTypes().ConvertType(E->getType()));
6948  llvm::Type *ElemTy = AType->getElementType();
6949  unsigned NumElements = AType->getNumElements();
6950 
6951  // Wide strings have either 2-byte or 4-byte elements.
6952  if (ElemTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == 16) {
6953  SmallVector<uint16_t, 32> Elements;
6954  Elements.reserve(NumElements);
6955 
6956  for(unsigned i = 0, e = E->getLength(); i != e; ++i)
6957  Elements.push_back(E->getCodeUnit(i));
6958  Elements.resize(NumElements);
6959  return llvm::ConstantDataArray::get(VMContext, Elements);
6960  }
6961 
6962  assert(ElemTy->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() == 32);
6963  SmallVector<uint32_t, 32> Elements;
6964  Elements.reserve(NumElements);
6965 
6966  for(unsigned i = 0, e = E->getLength(); i != e; ++i)
6967  Elements.push_back(E->getCodeUnit(i));
6968  Elements.resize(NumElements);
6969  return llvm::ConstantDataArray::get(VMContext, Elements);
6970 }
6971 
6972 static llvm::GlobalVariable *
6973 GenerateStringLiteral(llvm::Constant *C, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes LT,
6974  CodeGenModule &CGM, StringRef GlobalName,
6975  CharUnits Alignment) {
6976  unsigned AddrSpace = CGM.getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(
6977  CGM.GetGlobalConstantAddressSpace());
6978 
6979  llvm::Module &M = CGM.getModule();
6980  // Create a global variable for this string
6981  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
6982  M, C->getType(), !CGM.getLangOpts().WritableStrings, LT, C, GlobalName,
6983  nullptr, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal, AddrSpace);
6984  GV->setAlignment(Alignment.getAsAlign());
6985  GV->setUnnamedAddr(llvm::GlobalValue::UnnamedAddr::Global);
6986  if (GV->isWeakForLinker()) {
6987  assert(CGM.supportsCOMDAT() && "Only COFF uses weak string literals");
6988  GV->setComdat(M.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
6989  }
6990  CGM.setDSOLocal(GV);
6991 
6992  return GV;
6993 }
6994 
6995 /// GetAddrOfConstantStringFromLiteral - Return a pointer to a
6996 /// constant array for the given string literal.
6997 ConstantAddress
6998 CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfConstantStringFromLiteral(const StringLiteral *S,
6999  StringRef Name) {
7000  CharUnits Alignment =
7001  getContext().getAlignOfGlobalVarInChars(S->getType(), /*VD=*/nullptr);
7002 
7003  llvm::Constant *C = GetConstantArrayFromStringLiteral(S);
7004  llvm::GlobalVariable **Entry = nullptr;
7005  if (!LangOpts.WritableStrings) {
7006  Entry = &ConstantStringMap[C];
7007  if (auto GV = *Entry) {
7008  if (uint64_t(Alignment.getQuantity()) > GV->getAlignment())
7009  GV->setAlignment(Alignment.getAsAlign());
7010  return ConstantAddress(castStringLiteralToDefaultAddressSpace(*this, GV),
7011  GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
7012  }
7013  }
7014 
7015  SmallString<256> MangledNameBuffer;
7016  StringRef GlobalVariableName;
7017  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes LT;
7018 
7019  // Mangle the string literal if that's how the ABI merges duplicate strings.
7020  // Don't do it if they are writable, since we don't want writes in one TU to
7021  // affect strings in another.
7022  if (getCXXABI().getMangleContext().shouldMangleStringLiteral(S) &&
7023  !LangOpts.WritableStrings) {
7024  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(MangledNameBuffer);
7025  getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleStringLiteral(S, Out);
7026  LT = llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
7027  GlobalVariableName = MangledNameBuffer;
7028  } else {
7029  LT = llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage;
7030  GlobalVariableName = Name;
7031  }
7032 
7033  auto GV = GenerateStringLiteral(C, LT, *this, GlobalVariableName, Alignment);
7034 
7035  CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo();
7036  if (DI && getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
7037  DI->AddStringLiteralDebugInfo(GV, S);
7038 
7039  if (Entry)
7040  *Entry = GV;
7041 
7042  SanitizerMD->reportGlobal(GV, S->getStrTokenLoc(0), "<string literal>");
7043 
7044  return ConstantAddress(castStringLiteralToDefaultAddressSpace(*this, GV),
7045  GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
7046 }

7048 /// GetAddrOfConstantStringFromObjCEncode - Return a pointer to a constant
7049 /// array for the given ObjCEncodeExpr node.
7050 ConstantAddress
7051 CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfConstantStringFromObjCEncode(const ObjCEncodeExpr *E) {
7052  std::string Str;
7053  getContext().getObjCEncodingForType(E->getEncodedType(), Str);
7054

7056 }
