7058 /// GetAddrOfConstantCString - Returns a pointer to a character array containing
7059 /// the literal and a terminating '\0' character.
7060 /// The result has pointer to array type.
7061 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfConstantCString(
7062  const std::string &Str, const char *GlobalName) {
7063  StringRef StrWithNull(Str.c_str(), Str.size() + 1);
7064  CharUnits Alignment = getContext().getAlignOfGlobalVarInChars(
7065  getContext().CharTy, /*VD=*/nullptr);
7066 
7067  llvm::Constant *C =
7068  llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(getLLVMContext(), StrWithNull, false);
7069 
7070  // Don't share any string literals if strings aren't constant.
7071  llvm::GlobalVariable **Entry = nullptr;
7072  if (!LangOpts.WritableStrings) {
7073  Entry = &ConstantStringMap[C];
7074  if (auto GV = *Entry) {
7075  if (uint64_t(Alignment.getQuantity()) > GV->getAlignment())
7076  GV->setAlignment(Alignment.getAsAlign());
7077  return ConstantAddress(castStringLiteralToDefaultAddressSpace(*this, GV),
7078  GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
7079  }
7080  }
7081 
7082  // Get the default prefix if a name wasn't specified.
7083  if (!GlobalName)
7084  GlobalName = ".str";
7085  // Create a global variable for this.
7086  auto GV = GenerateStringLiteral(C, llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage, *this,
7087  GlobalName, Alignment);
7088  if (Entry)
7089  *Entry = GV;
7090 
7091  return ConstantAddress(castStringLiteralToDefaultAddressSpace(*this, GV),
7092  GV->getValueType(), Alignment);
7093 }
7094 
7095 ConstantAddress CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfGlobalTemporary(
7096  const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *E, const Expr *Init) {
7097  assert((E->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static ||
7098  E->getStorageDuration() == SD_Thread) && "not a global temporary");
7099  const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(E->getExtendingDecl());
7100 
7101  // If we're not materializing a subobject of the temporary, keep the
7102  // cv-qualifiers from the type of the MaterializeTemporaryExpr.
7103  QualType MaterializedType = Init->getType();
7104  if (Init == E->getSubExpr())
7105  MaterializedType = E->getType();
7106 
7107  CharUnits Align = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(MaterializedType);
7108 
7109  auto InsertResult = MaterializedGlobalTemporaryMap.insert({E, nullptr});
7110  if (!InsertResult.second) {
7111  // We've seen this before: either we already created it or we're in the
7112  // process of doing so.
7113  if (!InsertResult.first->second) {
7114  // We recursively re-entered this function, probably during emission of
7115  // the initializer. Create a placeholder. We'll clean this up in the
7116  // outer call, at the end of this function.
7117  llvm::Type *Type = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(MaterializedType);
7118  InsertResult.first->second = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
7119  getModule(), Type, false, llvm::GlobalVariable::InternalLinkage,
7120  nullptr);
7121  }
7122  return ConstantAddress(InsertResult.first->second,
7123  llvm::cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(
7124  InsertResult.first->second->stripPointerCasts())
7125  ->getValueType(),
7126  Align);
7127  }
7128 
7129  // FIXME: If an externally-visible declaration extends multiple temporaries,
7130  // we need to give each temporary the same name in every translation unit (and
7131  // we also need to make the temporaries externally-visible).
7132  SmallString<256> Name;
7133  llvm::raw_svector_ostream Out(Name);
7134  getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleReferenceTemporary(
7135  VD, E->getManglingNumber(), Out);
7136 
7137  APValue *Value = nullptr;
7138  if (E->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static && VD->evaluateValue()) {
7139  // If the initializer of the extending declaration is a constant
7140  // initializer, we should have a cached constant initializer for this
7141  // temporary. Note that this might have a different value from the value
7142  // computed by evaluating the initializer if the surrounding constant
7143  // expression modifies the temporary.
7144  Value = E->getOrCreateValue(false);
7145  }
7146 
7147  // Try evaluating it now, it might have a constant initializer.
7148  Expr::EvalResult EvalResult;
7149  if (!Value && Init->EvaluateAsRValue(EvalResult, getContext()) &&
7150  !EvalResult.hasSideEffects())
7151  Value = &EvalResult.Val;
7152 
7153  LangAS AddrSpace = GetGlobalVarAddressSpace(VD);
7154 
7155  std::optional<ConstantEmitter> emitter;
7156  llvm::Constant *InitialValue = nullptr;
7157  bool Constant = false;
7158  llvm::Type *Type;
7159  if (Value) {
7160  // The temporary has a constant initializer, use it.
7161  emitter.emplace(*this);
7162  InitialValue = emitter->emitForInitializer(*Value, AddrSpace,
7163  MaterializedType);
7164  Constant =
7165  MaterializedType.isConstantStorage(getContext(), /*ExcludeCtor*/ Value,
7166  /*ExcludeDtor*/ false);
7167  Type = InitialValue->getType();
7168  } else {
7169  // No initializer, the initialization will be provided when we
7170  // initialize the declaration which performed lifetime extension.
7171  Type = getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(MaterializedType);
7172  }
7173 
7174  // Create a global variable for this lifetime-extended temporary.
7175  llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = getLLVMLinkageVarDefinition(VD);
7176  if (Linkage == llvm::GlobalVariable::ExternalLinkage) {
7177  const VarDecl *InitVD;
7178  if (VD->isStaticDataMember() && VD->getAnyInitializer(InitVD) &&
7179  isa<CXXRecordDecl>(InitVD->getLexicalDeclContext())) {
7180  // Temporaries defined inside a class get linkonce_odr linkage because the
7181  // class can be defined in multiple translation units.
7182  Linkage = llvm::GlobalVariable::LinkOnceODRLinkage;
7183  } else {
7184  // There is no need for this temporary to have external linkage if the
7185  // VarDecl has external linkage.
7186  Linkage = llvm::GlobalVariable::InternalLinkage;
7187  }
7188  }
7189  auto TargetAS = getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(AddrSpace);
7190  auto *GV = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
7191  getModule(), Type, Constant, Linkage, InitialValue, Name.c_str(),
7192  /*InsertBefore=*/nullptr, llvm::GlobalVariable::NotThreadLocal, TargetAS);
7193  if (emitter) emitter->finalize(GV);
7194  // Don't assign dllimport or dllexport to local linkage globals.
7195  if (!llvm::GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(Linkage)) {
7196  setGVProperties(GV, VD);
7197  if (GV->getDLLStorageClass() == llvm::GlobalVariable::DLLExportStorageClass)
7198  // The reference temporary should never be dllexport.
7199  GV->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalVariable::DefaultStorageClass);
7200  }
7201  GV->setAlignment(Align.getAsAlign());
7202  if (supportsCOMDAT() && GV->isWeakForLinker())
7203  GV->setComdat(TheModule.getOrInsertComdat(GV->getName()));
7204  if (VD->getTLSKind())
7205  setTLSMode(GV, *VD);
7206  llvm::Constant *CV = GV;
7207  if (AddrSpace != LangAS::Default)
7208  CV = getTargetCodeGenInfo().performAddrSpaceCast(
7209  *this, GV, AddrSpace, LangAS::Default,
7210  llvm::PointerType::get(
7211  getLLVMContext(),
7212  getContext().getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::Default)));
7213 
7214  // Update the map with the new temporary. If we created a placeholder above,
7215  // replace it with the new global now.
7216  llvm::Constant *&Entry = MaterializedGlobalTemporaryMap[E];
7217  if (Entry) {
7218  Entry->replaceAllUsesWith(CV);
7219  llvm::cast<llvm::GlobalVariable>(Entry)->eraseFromParent();
7220  }
7221  Entry = CV;
7222 
7223  return ConstantAddress(CV, Type, Align);
7224 }
7225 
7226 /// EmitObjCPropertyImplementations - Emit information for synthesized
7227 /// properties for an implementation.
7228 void CodeGenModule::EmitObjCPropertyImplementations(const
7229  ObjCImplementationDecl *D) {
7230  for (const auto *PID : D->property_impls()) {
7231  // Dynamic is just for type-checking.
7232  if (PID->getPropertyImplementation() == ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Synthesize) {
7233  ObjCPropertyDecl *PD = PID->getPropertyDecl();
7234 
7235  // Determine which methods need to be implemented, some may have
7236  // been overridden. Note that ::isPropertyAccessor is not the method
7237  // we want, that just indicates if the decl came from a
7238  // property. What we want to know is if the method is defined in
7239  // this implementation.
7240  auto *Getter = PID->getGetterMethodDecl();
7241  if (!Getter || Getter->isSynthesizedAccessorStub())
7242  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateObjCGetter(
7243  const_cast<ObjCImplementationDecl *>(D), PID);
7244  auto *Setter = PID->getSetterMethodDecl();
7245  if (!PD->isReadOnly() && (!Setter || Setter->isSynthesizedAccessorStub()))
7246  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateObjCSetter(
7247  const_cast<ObjCImplementationDecl *>(D), PID);
7248  }
7249  }
7250 }
7251 
7252 static bool needsDestructMethod(ObjCImplementationDecl *impl) {
7253  const ObjCInterfaceDecl *iface = impl->getClassInterface();
7254  for (const ObjCIvarDecl *ivar = iface->all_declared_ivar_begin();
7255  ivar; ivar = ivar->getNextIvar())
7256  if (ivar->getType().isDestructedType())
7257  return true;
7258 
7259  return false;
7260 }
7261 
7262 static bool AllTrivialInitializers(CodeGenModule &CGM,
7263  ObjCImplementationDecl *D) {
7264  CodeGenFunction CGF(CGM);
7265  for (ObjCImplementationDecl::init_iterator B = D->init_begin(),
7266  E = D->init_end(); B != E; ++B) {
7267  CXXCtorInitializer *CtorInitExp = *B;
7268  Expr *Init = CtorInitExp->getInit();
7269  if (!CGF.isTrivialInitializer(Init))
7270  return false;
7271  }
7272  return true;
7273 }
7274 
7275 /// EmitObjCIvarInitializations - Emit information for ivar initialization
7276 /// for an implementation.
7277 void CodeGenModule::EmitObjCIvarInitializations(ObjCImplementationDecl *D) {
7278  // We might need a .cxx_destruct even if we don't have any ivar initializers.
7279  if (needsDestructMethod(D)) {
7280  const IdentifierInfo *II = &getContext().Idents.get(".cxx_destruct");
7281  Selector cxxSelector = getContext().Selectors.getSelector(0, &II);
7282  ObjCMethodDecl *DTORMethod = ObjCMethodDecl::Create(
7283  getContext(), D->getLocation(), D->getLocation(), cxxSelector,
7284  getContext().VoidTy, nullptr, D,
7285  /*isInstance=*/true, /*isVariadic=*/false,
7286  /*isPropertyAccessor=*/true, /*isSynthesizedAccessorStub=*/false,
7287  /*isImplicitlyDeclared=*/true,
7288  /*isDefined=*/false, ObjCImplementationControl::Required);
7289  D->addInstanceMethod(DTORMethod);
7290  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateObjCCtorDtorMethod(D, DTORMethod, false);
7291  D->setHasDestructors(true);
7292  }
7293 
7294  // If the implementation doesn't have any ivar initializers, we don't need
7295  // a .cxx_construct.
7296  if (D->getNumIvarInitializers() == 0 ||
7297  AllTrivialInitializers(*this, D))
7298  return;
7299 
7300  const IdentifierInfo *II = &getContext().Idents.get(".cxx_construct");
7301  Selector cxxSelector = getContext().Selectors.getSelector(0, &II);
7302  // The constructor returns 'self'.
7303  ObjCMethodDecl *CTORMethod = ObjCMethodDecl::Create(
7304  getContext(), D->getLocation(), D->getLocation(), cxxSelector,
7305  getContext().getObjCIdType(), nullptr, D, /*isInstance=*/true,
7306  /*isVariadic=*/false,
7307  /*isPropertyAccessor=*/true, /*isSynthesizedAccessorStub=*/false,
7308  /*isImplicitlyDeclared=*/true,
7309  /*isDefined=*/false, ObjCImplementationControl::Required);
7310  D->addInstanceMethod(CTORMethod);
7311  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateObjCCtorDtorMethod(D, CTORMethod, true);
7312  D->setHasNonZeroConstructors(true);
7313 }
7314 
7315 // EmitLinkageSpec - Emit all declarations in a linkage spec.
7316 void CodeGenModule::EmitLinkageSpec(const LinkageSpecDecl *LSD) {
7317  if (LSD->getLanguage() != LinkageSpecLanguageIDs::C &&
7318  LSD->getLanguage() != LinkageSpecLanguageIDs::CXX) {
7319  ErrorUnsupported(LSD, "linkage spec");
7320  return;
7321  }
7322 
7323  EmitDeclContext(LSD);
7324 }
7325 
7326 void CodeGenModule::EmitTopLevelStmt(const TopLevelStmtDecl *D) {
7327  // Device code should not be at top level.
7328  if (LangOpts.CUDA && LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice)
7329  return;
7330 
7331  std::unique_ptr<CodeGenFunction> &CurCGF =
7332  GlobalTopLevelStmtBlockInFlight.first;
7333 
7334  // We emitted a top-level stmt but after it there is initialization.
7335  // Stop squashing the top-level stmts into a single function.
7336  if (CurCGF && CXXGlobalInits.back() != CurCGF->CurFn) {
7337  CurCGF->FinishFunction(D->getEndLoc());
7338  CurCGF = nullptr;
7339  }
7340 
7341  if (!CurCGF) {
7342  // void __stmts__N(void)
7343  // FIXME: Ask the ABI name mangler to pick a name.
7344  std::string Name = "__stmts__" + llvm::utostr(CXXGlobalInits.size());
7345  FunctionArgList Args;
7346  QualType RetTy = getContext().VoidTy;
7347  const CGFunctionInfo &FnInfo =
7348  getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionDeclaration(RetTy, Args);
7349  llvm::FunctionType *FnTy = getTypes().GetFunctionType(FnInfo);
7350  llvm::Function *Fn = llvm::Function::Create(
7351  FnTy, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, Name, &getModule());
7352 
7353  CurCGF.reset(new CodeGenFunction(*this));
7354  GlobalTopLevelStmtBlockInFlight.second = D;
7355  CurCGF->StartFunction(GlobalDecl(), RetTy, Fn, FnInfo, Args,
7356  D->getBeginLoc(), D->getBeginLoc());
7357  CXXGlobalInits.push_back(Fn);
7358  }
7359 
7360  CurCGF->EmitStmt(D->getStmt());
7361 }
7362 
7363 void CodeGenModule::EmitDeclContext(const DeclContext *DC) {
7364  for (auto *I : DC->decls()) {
7365  // Unlike other DeclContexts, the contents of an ObjCImplDecl at TU scope
7366  // are themselves considered "top-level", so EmitTopLevelDecl on an
7367  // ObjCImplDecl does not recursively visit them. We need to do that in
7368  // case they're nested inside another construct (LinkageSpecDecl /
7369  // ExportDecl) that does stop them from being considered "top-level".
7370  if (auto *OID = dyn_cast<ObjCImplDecl>(I)) {
7371  for (auto *M : OID->methods())
7372  EmitTopLevelDecl(M);
7373  }
7374 
7375  EmitTopLevelDecl(I);
7376  }
7377 }
7378 
7379 /// EmitTopLevelDecl - Emit code for a single top level declaration.
7380 void CodeGenModule::EmitTopLevelDecl(Decl *D) {
7381  // Ignore dependent declarations.
7382  if (D->isTemplated())
7383  return;
7384 
7385  // Consteval function shouldn't be emitted.
7386  if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D); FD && FD->isImmediateFunction())
7387  return;
7388 
7389  switch (D->getKind()) {
7390  case Decl::CXXConversion:
7391  case Decl::CXXMethod:
7392  case Decl::Function:
7393  EmitGlobal(cast<FunctionDecl>(D));
7394  // Always provide some coverage mapping
7395  // even for the functions that aren't emitted.
7396  AddDeferredUnusedCoverageMapping(D);
7397  break;
7398 
7399  case Decl::CXXDeductionGuide:
7400  // Function-like, but does not result in code emission.
7401  break;
7402 
7403  case Decl::Var:
7404  case Decl::Decomposition:
7405  case Decl::VarTemplateSpecialization:
7406  EmitGlobal(cast<VarDecl>(D));
7407  if (auto *DD = dyn_cast<DecompositionDecl>(D))
7408  for (auto *B : DD->bindings())
7409  if (auto *HD = B->getHoldingVar())
7410  EmitGlobal(HD);
7411  break;
7412 
7413  // Indirect fields from global anonymous structs and unions can be
7414  // ignored; only the actual variable requires IR gen support.
7415  case Decl::IndirectField:
7416  break;
7417 
7418  // C++ Decls
7419  case Decl::Namespace:
7420  EmitDeclContext(cast<NamespaceDecl>(D));
7421  break;
7422  case Decl::ClassTemplateSpecialization: {
7423  const auto *Spec = cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(D);
7424  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
7425  if (Spec->getSpecializationKind() ==
7426  TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition &&
7427  Spec->hasDefinition())
7428  DI->completeTemplateDefinition(*Spec);
7429  } [[fallthrough]];
7430  case Decl::CXXRecord: {
7431  CXXRecordDecl *CRD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
7432  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo()) {
7433  if (CRD->hasDefinition())
7434  DI->EmitAndRetainType(getContext().getRecordType(cast<RecordDecl>(D)));
7435  if (auto *ES = D->getASTContext().getExternalSource())
7436  if (ES->hasExternalDefinitions(D) == ExternalASTSource::EK_Never)
7437  DI->completeUnusedClass(*CRD);
7438  }
7439  // Emit any static data members, they may be definitions.
7440  for (auto *I : CRD->decls())
7441  if (isa<VarDecl>(I) || isa<CXXRecordDecl>(I))
7442  EmitTopLevelDecl(I);
7443  break;
7444  }
7445  // No code generation needed.
7446  case Decl::UsingShadow:
7447  case Decl::ClassTemplate:
7448  case Decl::VarTemplate:
7449  case Decl::Concept:
7450  case Decl::VarTemplatePartialSpecialization:
7451  case Decl::FunctionTemplate:
7452  case Decl::TypeAliasTemplate:
7453  case Decl::Block:
7454  case Decl::Empty:
7455  case Decl::Binding:
7456  break;
7457  case Decl::Using: // using X; [C++]
7458  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
7459  DI->EmitUsingDecl(cast<UsingDecl>(*D));
7460  break;
7461  case Decl::UsingEnum: // using enum X; [C++]
7462  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
7463  DI->EmitUsingEnumDecl(cast<UsingEnumDecl>(*D));
7464  break;
7465  case Decl::NamespaceAlias:
7466  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
7467  DI->EmitNamespaceAlias(cast<NamespaceAliasDecl>(*D));
7468  break;
7469  case Decl::UsingDirective: // using namespace X; [C++]
7470  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
7471  DI->EmitUsingDirective(cast<UsingDirectiveDecl>(*D));
7472  break;
7473  case Decl::CXXConstructor:
7474  getCXXABI().EmitCXXConstructors(cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(D));
7475  break;
7476  case Decl::CXXDestructor:
7477  getCXXABI().EmitCXXDestructors(cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D));
7478  break;
7479 
7480  case Decl::StaticAssert:
7481  // Nothing to do.
7482  break;
7483 
7484  // Objective-C Decls
7485 
7486  // Forward declarations, no (immediate) code generation.
7487  case Decl::ObjCInterface:
7488  case Decl::ObjCCategory:
7489  break;
7490 
7491  case Decl::ObjCProtocol: {
7492  auto *Proto = cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(D);
7493  if (Proto->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
7494  ObjCRuntime->GenerateProtocol(Proto);
7495  break;
7496  }
7497 
7498  case Decl::ObjCCategoryImpl:
7499  // Categories have properties but don't support synthesize so we
7500  // can ignore them here.
7501  ObjCRuntime->GenerateCategory(cast<ObjCCategoryImplDecl>(D));
7502  break;
7503 
7504  case Decl::ObjCImplementation: {
7505  auto *OMD = cast<ObjCImplementationDecl>(D);
7506  EmitObjCPropertyImplementations(OMD);
7507  EmitObjCIvarInitializations(OMD);
7508  ObjCRuntime->GenerateClass(OMD);
7509  // Emit global variable debug information.
7510  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
7511  if (getCodeGenOpts().hasReducedDebugInfo())
7512  DI->getOrCreateInterfaceType(getContext().getObjCInterfaceType(
7513  OMD->getClassInterface()), OMD->getLocation());
7514  break;
7515  }
7516  case Decl::ObjCMethod: {
7517  auto *OMD = cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
7518  // If this is not a prototype, emit the body.
7519  if (OMD->getBody())
7520  CodeGenFunction(*this).GenerateObjCMethod(OMD);
7521  break;
7522  }
7523  case Decl::ObjCCompatibleAlias:
7524  ObjCRuntime->RegisterAlias(cast<ObjCCompatibleAliasDecl>(D));
7525  break;
7526 
7527  case Decl::PragmaComment: {
7528  const auto *PCD = cast<PragmaCommentDecl>(D);
7529  switch (PCD->getCommentKind()) {
7530  case PCK_Unknown:
7531  llvm_unreachable("unexpected pragma comment kind");
7532  case PCK_Linker:
7533  AppendLinkerOptions(PCD->getArg());
7534  break;
7535  case PCK_Lib:
7536  AddDependentLib(PCD->getArg());
7537  break;
7538  case PCK_Compiler:
7539  case PCK_ExeStr:
7540  case PCK_User:
7541  break; // We ignore all of these.
7542  }
7543  break;
7544  }
7545 
7546  case Decl::PragmaDetectMismatch: {
7547  const auto *PDMD = cast<PragmaDetectMismatchDecl>(D);
7548  AddDetectMismatch(PDMD->getName(), PDMD->getValue());
7549  break;
7550  }
7551 
7552  case Decl::LinkageSpec:
7553  EmitLinkageSpec(cast<LinkageSpecDecl>(D));
7554  break;
7555 
7556  case Decl::FileScopeAsm: {
7557  // File-scope asm is ignored during device-side CUDA compilation.
7558  if (LangOpts.CUDA && LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice)
7559  break;
7560  // File-scope asm is ignored during device-side OpenMP compilation.
7561  if (LangOpts.OpenMPIsTargetDevice)
7562  break;
7563  // File-scope asm is ignored during device-side SYCL compilation.
7564  if (LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice)
7565  break;
7566  auto *AD = cast<FileScopeAsmDecl>(D);
7567  getModule().appendModuleInlineAsm(AD->getAsmString()->getString());
7568  break;
7569  }
7570 
7571  case Decl::TopLevelStmt:
7572  EmitTopLevelStmt(cast<TopLevelStmtDecl>(D));
7573  break;
7574 
7575  case Decl::Import: {
7576  auto *Import = cast<ImportDecl>(D);
7577 
7578  // If we've already imported this module, we're done.
7579  if (!ImportedModules.insert(Import->getImportedModule()))
7580  break;
7581 
7582  // Emit debug information for direct imports.
7583  if (!Import->getImportedOwningModule()) {
7584  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
7585  DI->EmitImportDecl(*Import);
7586  }
7587 
7588  // For C++ standard modules we are done - we will call the module
7589  // initializer for imported modules, and that will likewise call those for
7590  // any imports it has.
7591  if (CXX20ModuleInits && Import->getImportedOwningModule() &&
7592  !Import->getImportedOwningModule()->isModuleMapModule())
7593  break;
7594 
7595  // For clang C++ module map modules the initializers for sub-modules are
7596  // emitted here.
7597 
7598  // Find all of the submodules and emit the module initializers.
7599  llvm::SmallPtrSet<clang::Module *, 16> Visited;
7600  SmallVector<clang::Module *, 16> Stack;
7601  Visited.insert(Import->getImportedModule());
7602  Stack.push_back(Import->getImportedModule());
7603 
7604  while (!Stack.empty()) {
7605  clang::Module *Mod = Stack.pop_back_val();
7606  if (!EmittedModuleInitializers.insert(Mod).second)
7607  continue;
7608 
7609  for (auto *D : Context.getModuleInitializers(Mod))
7610  EmitTopLevelDecl(D);
7611 
7612  // Visit the submodules of this module.
7613  for (auto *Submodule : Mod->submodules()) {
7614  // Skip explicit children; they need to be explicitly imported to emit
7615  // the initializers.
7616  if (Submodule->IsExplicit)
7617  continue;
7618 
7619  if (Visited.insert(Submodule).second)
7620  Stack.push_back(Submodule);
7621  }
7622  }
7623  break;
7624  }
7625 
7626  case Decl::Export:
7627  EmitDeclContext(cast<ExportDecl>(D));
7628  break;
7629 
7630  case Decl::OMPThreadPrivate:
7631  EmitOMPThreadPrivateDecl(cast<OMPThreadPrivateDecl>(D));
7632  break;
7633 
7634  case Decl::OMPAllocate:
7635  EmitOMPAllocateDecl(cast<OMPAllocateDecl>(D));
7636  break;
7637 
7638  case Decl::OMPDeclareReduction:
7639  EmitOMPDeclareReduction(cast<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(D));
7640  break;
7641 
7642  case Decl::OMPDeclareMapper:
7643  EmitOMPDeclareMapper(cast<OMPDeclareMapperDecl>(D));
7644  break;
7645 
7646  case Decl::OMPRequires:
7647  EmitOMPRequiresDecl(cast<OMPRequiresDecl>(D));
7648  break;
7649 
7650  case Decl::Typedef:
7651  case Decl::TypeAlias: // using foo = bar; [C++11]
7652  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
7653  DI->EmitAndRetainType(
7654  getContext().getTypedefType(cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)));
7655  break;
7656 
7657  case Decl::Record:
7658  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
7659  if (cast<RecordDecl>(D)->getDefinition())
7660  DI->EmitAndRetainType(getContext().getRecordType(cast<RecordDecl>(D)));
7661  break;
7662 
7663  case Decl::Enum:
7664  if (CGDebugInfo *DI = getModuleDebugInfo())
7665  if (cast<EnumDecl>(D)->getDefinition())
7666  DI->EmitAndRetainType(getContext().getEnumType(cast<EnumDecl>(D)));
7667  break;
7668 
7669  case Decl::HLSLBuffer:
7670  getHLSLRuntime().addBuffer(cast<HLSLBufferDecl>(D));
7671  break;
7672 
7673  default:
7674  // Make sure we handled everything we should, every other kind is a
7675  // non-top-level decl. FIXME: Would be nice to have an isTopLevelDeclKind
7676  // function. Need to recode Decl::Kind to do that easily.
7677  assert(isa<TypeDecl>(D) && "Unsupported decl kind");
7678  break;
7679  }
7680 }
7681 
7682 void CodeGenModule::AddDeferredUnusedCoverageMapping(Decl *D) {
7683  // Do we need to generate coverage mapping?
7684  if (!CodeGenOpts.CoverageMapping)
7685  return;
7686  switch (D->getKind()) {
7687  case Decl::CXXConversion:
7688  case Decl::CXXMethod:
7689  case Decl::Function:
7690  case Decl::ObjCMethod:
7691  case Decl::CXXConstructor:
7692  case Decl::CXXDestructor: {
7693  if (!cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody())
7694  break;
7695  SourceManager &SM = getContext().getSourceManager();
7696  if (LimitedCoverage && SM.getMainFileID() != SM.getFileID(D->getBeginLoc()))
7697  break;
7698  DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls.try_emplace(D, true);
7699  break;
7700  }
7701  default:
7702  break;
7703  };
7704 }
7705 
7706 void CodeGenModule::ClearUnusedCoverageMapping(const Decl *D) {
7707  // Do we need to generate coverage mapping?
7708  if (!CodeGenOpts.CoverageMapping)
7709  return;
7710  if (const auto *Fn = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
7711  if (Fn->isTemplateInstantiation())
7712  ClearUnusedCoverageMapping(Fn->getTemplateInstantiationPattern());
7713  }
7714  DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls.insert_or_assign(D, false);
7715 }
7716 
7717 void CodeGenModule::EmitDeferredUnusedCoverageMappings() {
7718  // We call takeVector() here to avoid use-after-free.
7719  // FIXME: DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls is getting mutated because
7720  // we deserialize function bodies to emit coverage info for them, and that
7721  // deserializes more declarations. How should we handle that case?
7722  for (const auto &Entry : DeferredEmptyCoverageMappingDecls.takeVector()) {
7723  if (!Entry.second)
7724  continue;
7725  const Decl *D = Entry.first;
7726  switch (D->getKind()) {
7727  case Decl::CXXConversion:
7728  case Decl::CXXMethod:
7729  case Decl::Function:
7730  case Decl::ObjCMethod: {
7731  CodeGenPGO PGO(*this);
7732  GlobalDecl GD(cast<FunctionDecl>(D));
7733  PGO.emitEmptyCounterMapping(D, getMangledName(GD),
7734  getFunctionLinkage(GD));
7735  break;
7736  }
7737  case Decl::CXXConstructor: {
7738  CodeGenPGO PGO(*this);
7739  GlobalDecl GD(cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(D), Ctor_Base);
7740  PGO.emitEmptyCounterMapping(D, getMangledName(GD),
7741  getFunctionLinkage(GD));
7742  break;
7743  }
7744  case Decl::CXXDestructor: {
7745  CodeGenPGO PGO(*this);
7746  GlobalDecl GD(cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D), Dtor_Base);
7747  PGO.emitEmptyCounterMapping(D, getMangledName(GD),
7748  getFunctionLinkage(GD));
7749  break;
7750  }
7751  default:
7752  break;
7753  };
7754  }
7755 }
7756 
7757 void CodeGenModule::EmitMainVoidAlias() {
7758  // In order to transition away from "__original_main" gracefully, emit an
7759  // alias for "main" in the no-argument case so that libc can detect when
7760  // new-style no-argument main is in used.
7761  if (llvm::Function *F = getModule().getFunction("main")) {
7762  if (!F->isDeclaration() && F->arg_size() == 0 && !F->isVarArg() &&
7763  F->getReturnType()->isIntegerTy(Context.getTargetInfo().getIntWidth())) {
7764  auto *GA = llvm::GlobalAlias::create("__main_void", F);
7765  GA->setVisibility(llvm::GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility);
7766  }
7767  }
7768 }
7769 
7770 /// Turns the given pointer into a constant.
7771 static llvm::Constant *GetPointerConstant(llvm::LLVMContext &Context,
7772  const void *Ptr) {
7773  uintptr_t PtrInt = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(Ptr);
7774  llvm::Type *i64 = llvm::Type::getInt64Ty(Context);
7775  return llvm::ConstantInt::get(i64, PtrInt);
7776 }
7777 
7778 static void EmitGlobalDeclMetadata(CodeGenModule &CGM,
7779  llvm::NamedMDNode *&GlobalMetadata,
7780  GlobalDecl D,
7781  llvm::GlobalValue *Addr) {
7782  if (!GlobalMetadata)
7783  GlobalMetadata =
7784  CGM.getModule().getOrInsertNamedMetadata("clang.global.decl.ptrs");
7785 
7786  // TODO: should we report variant information for ctors/dtors?
7787  llvm::Metadata *Ops[] = {llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(Addr),
7788  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(GetPointerConstant(
7789  CGM.getLLVMContext(), D.getDecl()))};
7790  GlobalMetadata->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(CGM.getLLVMContext(), Ops));
7791 }
7792 
7793 bool CodeGenModule::CheckAndReplaceExternCIFuncs(llvm::GlobalValue *Elem,
7794  llvm::GlobalValue *CppFunc) {
7795  // Store the list of ifuncs we need to replace uses in.
7796  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::GlobalIFunc *> IFuncs;
7797  // List of ConstantExprs that we should be able to delete when we're done
7798  // here.
7799  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::ConstantExpr *> CEs;
7800 
7801  // It isn't valid to replace the extern-C ifuncs if all we find is itself!
7802  if (Elem == CppFunc)
7803  return false;
7804 
7805  // First make sure that all users of this are ifuncs (or ifuncs via a
7806  // bitcast), and collect the list of ifuncs and CEs so we can work on them
7807  // later.
7808  for (llvm::User *User : Elem->users()) {
7809  // Users can either be a bitcast ConstExpr that is used by the ifuncs, OR an
7810  // ifunc directly. In any other case, just give up, as we don't know what we
7811  // could break by changing those.
7812  if (auto *ConstExpr = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantExpr>(User)) {
7813  if (ConstExpr->getOpcode() != llvm::Instruction::BitCast)
7814  return false;
7815 
7816  for (llvm::User *CEUser : ConstExpr->users()) {
7817  if (auto *IFunc = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(CEUser)) {
7818  IFuncs.push_back(IFunc);
7819  } else {
7820  return false;
7821  }
7822  }
7823  CEs.push_back(ConstExpr);
7824  } else if (auto *IFunc = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalIFunc>(User)) {
7825  IFuncs.push_back(IFunc);
7826  } else {
7827  // This user is one we don't know how to handle, so fail redirection. This
7828  // will result in an ifunc retaining a resolver name that will ultimately
7829  // fail to be resolved to a defined function.
7830  return false;
7831  }
7832  }
7833 
7834  // Now we know this is a valid case where we can do this alias replacement, we
7835  // need to remove all of the references to Elem (and the bitcasts!) so we can
7836  // delete it.
7837  for (llvm::GlobalIFunc *IFunc : IFuncs)
7838  IFunc->setResolver(nullptr);
7839  for (llvm::ConstantExpr *ConstExpr : CEs)
7840  ConstExpr->destroyConstant();
7841 
7842  // We should now be out of uses for the 'old' version of this function, so we
7843  // can erase it as well.
7844  Elem->eraseFromParent();
7845 
7846  for (llvm::GlobalIFunc *IFunc : IFuncs) {
7847  // The type of the resolver is always just a function-type that returns the
7848  // type of the IFunc, so create that here. If the type of the actual
7849  // resolver doesn't match, it just gets bitcast to the right thing.
7850  auto *ResolverTy =
7851  llvm::FunctionType::get(IFunc->getType(), /*isVarArg*/ false);
7852  llvm::Constant *Resolver = GetOrCreateLLVMFunction(
7853  CppFunc->getName(), ResolverTy, {}, /*ForVTable*/ false);
7854  IFunc->setResolver(Resolver);
7855  }
7856  return true;
7857 }
7858 
7859 /// For each function which is declared within an extern "C" region and marked
7860 /// as 'used', but has internal linkage, create an alias from the unmangled
7861 /// name to the mangled name if possible. People expect to be able to refer
7862 /// to such functions with an unmangled name from inline assembly within the
7863 /// same translation unit.
7864 void CodeGenModule::EmitStaticExternCAliases() {
7865  if (!getTargetCodeGenInfo().shouldEmitStaticExternCAliases())
7866  return;
7867  for (auto &I : StaticExternCValues) {
7868  const IdentifierInfo *Name = I.first;
7869  llvm::GlobalValue *Val = I.second;
7870 
7871  // If Val is null, that implies there were multiple declarations that each
7872  // had a claim to the unmangled name. In this case, generation of the alias
7873  // is suppressed. See CodeGenModule::MaybeHandleStaticInExternC.
7874  if (!Val)
7875  break;
7876 
7877  llvm::GlobalValue *ExistingElem =
7878  getModule().getNamedValue(Name->getName());
7879 
7880  // If there is either not something already by this name, or we were able to
7881  // replace all uses from IFuncs, create the alias.
7882  if (!ExistingElem || CheckAndReplaceExternCIFuncs(ExistingElem, Val))
7883  addCompilerUsedGlobal(llvm::GlobalAlias::create(Name->getName(), Val));
7884  }
7885 }
7886 
7887 bool CodeGenModule::lookupRepresentativeDecl(StringRef MangledName,
7888  GlobalDecl &Result) const {
7889  auto Res = Manglings.find(MangledName);
7890  if (Res == Manglings.end())
7891  return false;
7892  Result = Res->getValue();
7893  return true;
7894 }
7895 
7896 /// Emits metadata nodes associating all the global values in the
7897 /// current module with the Decls they came from. This is useful for
7898 /// projects using IR gen as a subroutine.
7899 ///
7900 /// Since there's currently no way to associate an MDNode directly
7901 /// with an llvm::GlobalValue, we create a global named metadata
7902 /// with the name 'clang.global.decl.ptrs'.
7903 void CodeGenModule::EmitDeclMetadata() {
7904  llvm::NamedMDNode *GlobalMetadata = nullptr;
7905 
7906  for (auto &I : MangledDeclNames) {
7907  llvm::GlobalValue *Addr = getModule().getNamedValue(I.second);
7908  // Some mangled names don't necessarily have an associated GlobalValue
7909  // in this module, e.g. if we mangled it for DebugInfo.
7910  if (Addr)
7911  EmitGlobalDeclMetadata(*this, GlobalMetadata, I.first, Addr);
7912  }
7913 }
7914 
7915 /// Emits metadata nodes for all the local variables in the current
7916 /// function.
7917 void CodeGenFunction::EmitDeclMetadata() {
7918  if (LocalDeclMap.empty()) return;
7919 
7920  llvm::LLVMContext &Context = getLLVMContext();
7921 
7922  // Find the unique metadata ID for this name.
7923  unsigned DeclPtrKind = Context.getMDKindID("clang.decl.ptr");
7924 
7925  llvm::NamedMDNode *GlobalMetadata = nullptr;
7926 
7927  for (auto &I : LocalDeclMap) {
7928  const Decl *D = I.first;
7929  llvm::Value *Addr = I.second.emitRawPointer(*this);
7930  if (auto *Alloca = dyn_cast<llvm::AllocaInst>(Addr)) {
7931  llvm::Value *DAddr = GetPointerConstant(getLLVMContext(), D);
7932  Alloca->setMetadata(
7933  DeclPtrKind, llvm::MDNode::get(
7934  Context, llvm::ValueAsMetadata::getConstant(DAddr)));
7935  } else if (auto *GV = dyn_cast<llvm::GlobalValue>(Addr)) {
7936  GlobalDecl GD = GlobalDecl(cast<VarDecl>(D));
7937  EmitGlobalDeclMetadata(CGM, GlobalMetadata, GD, GV);
7938  }
7939  }
7940 }

7962 void CodeGenModule::EmitCoverageFile() {
7963  llvm::NamedMDNode *CUNode = TheModule.getNamedMetadata("llvm.dbg.cu");
7964  if (!CUNode)
7965  return;
7966 
7967  llvm::NamedMDNode *GCov = TheModule.getOrInsertNamedMetadata("llvm.gcov");
7968  llvm::LLVMContext &Ctx = TheModule.getContext();
7969  auto *CoverageDataFile =
7970  llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, getCodeGenOpts().CoverageDataFile);
7971  auto *CoverageNotesFile =
7972  llvm::MDString::get(Ctx, getCodeGenOpts().CoverageNotesFile);
7973  for (int i = 0, e = CUNode->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
7974  llvm::MDNode *CU = CUNode->getOperand(i);
7975  llvm::Metadata *Elts[] = {CoverageNotesFile, CoverageDataFile, CU};
7976  GCov->addOperand(llvm::MDNode::get(Ctx, Elts));
7977  }
7978 }

7980 llvm::Constant *CodeGenModule::GetAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(QualType Ty,
7981  bool ForEH) {
7982  // Return a bogus pointer if RTTI is disabled, unless it's for EH.
7983  // FIXME: should we even be calling this method if RTTI is disabled
7984  // and it's not for EH?
7985  if (!shouldEmitRTTI(ForEH))
7986  return llvm::Constant::getNullValue(GlobalsInt8PtrTy);
7987 
7988  if (ForEH && Ty->isObjCObjectPointerType() &&
7989  LangOpts.ObjCRuntime.isGNUFamily())
7990  return ObjCRuntime->GetEHType(Ty);
7991 
7992  return getCXXABI().getAddrOfRTTIDescriptor(Ty);
7993 }
7994 
7995 void CodeGenModule::EmitOMPThreadPrivateDecl(const OMPThreadPrivateDecl *D) {
7996  // Do not emit threadprivates in simd-only mode.
7997  if (LangOpts.OpenMP && LangOpts.OpenMPSimd)
7998  return;
7999  for (auto RefExpr : D->varlists()) {
8000  auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(RefExpr)->getDecl());
8001  bool PerformInit =
8002  VD->getAnyInitializer() &&
8003  !VD->getAnyInitializer()->isConstantInitializer(getContext(),
8004  /*ForRef=*/false);
8005 
8006  Address Addr(GetAddrOfGlobalVar(VD),
8007  getTypes().ConvertTypeForMem(VD->getType()),
8008  getContext().getDeclAlign(VD));
8009  if (auto InitFunction = getOpenMPRuntime().emitThreadPrivateVarDefinition(
8010  VD, Addr, RefExpr->getBeginLoc(), PerformInit))
8011  CXXGlobalInits.push_back(InitFunction);
8012  }
8013 }

8015 llvm::Metadata *
8016 CodeGenModule::CreateMetadataIdentifierImpl(QualType T, MetadataTypeMap &Map,
8017  StringRef Suffix) {
8018  if (auto *FnType = T->getAs<FunctionProtoType>())
8019  T = getContext().getFunctionType(
8020  FnType->getReturnType(), FnType->getParamTypes(),
8021  FnType->getExtProtoInfo().withExceptionSpec(EST_None));
8022 
8023  llvm::Metadata *&InternalId = Map[T.getCanonicalType()];
8024  if (InternalId)
8025  return InternalId;
8026 
8027  if (isExternallyVisible(T->getLinkage())) {
8028  std::string OutName;
8029  llvm::raw_string_ostream Out(OutName);
8030  getCXXABI().getMangleContext().mangleCanonicalTypeName(
8031  T, Out, getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiICallNormalizeIntegers);
8032 
8033  if (getCodeGenOpts().SanitizeCfiICallNormalizeIntegers)
8034  Out << ".normalized";
8035 
8036  Out << Suffix;
8037 
8038  InternalId = llvm::MDString::get(getLLVMContext(), Out.str());
8039  } else {
8040  InternalId = llvm::MDNode::getDistinct(getLLVMContext(),
8041  llvm::ArrayRef<llvm::Metadata *>());
8042  }
8043 
8044  return InternalId;
8045 }
8046 
8047 llvm::Metadata *CodeGenModule::CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(QualType T) {
8048  return CreateMetadataIdentifierImpl(T, MetadataIdMap, "");
8049 }
8050 
8051 llvm::Metadata *
8052 CodeGenModule::CreateMetadataIdentifierForVirtualMemPtrType(QualType T) {
8053  return CreateMetadataIdentifierImpl(T, VirtualMetadataIdMap, ".virtual");
8054 }
8055 
8056 // Generalize pointer types to a void pointer with the qualifiers of the
8057 // originally pointed-to type, e.g. 'const char *' and 'char * const *'
8058 // generalize to 'const void *' while 'char *' and 'const char **' generalize to
8059 // 'void *'.
8060 static QualType GeneralizeType(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType Ty) {
8061  if (!Ty->isPointerType())
8062  return Ty;
8063 
8064  return Ctx.getPointerType(
8065  QualType(Ctx.VoidTy).withCVRQualifiers(
8066  Ty->getPointeeType().getCVRQualifiers()));
8067 }
8068 
8069 // Apply type generalization to a FunctionType's return and argument types
8070 static QualType GeneralizeFunctionType(ASTContext &Ctx, QualType Ty) {
8071  if (auto *FnType = Ty->getAs<FunctionProtoType>()) {
8072  SmallVector<QualType, 8> GeneralizedParams;
8073  for (auto &Param : FnType->param_types())
8074  GeneralizedParams.push_back(GeneralizeType(Ctx, Param));
8075 
8076  return Ctx.getFunctionType(
8077  GeneralizeType(Ctx, FnType->getReturnType()),
8078  GeneralizedParams, FnType->getExtProtoInfo());
8079  }
8080 
8081  if (auto *FnType = Ty->getAs<FunctionNoProtoType>())
8082  return Ctx.getFunctionNoProtoType(
8083  GeneralizeType(Ctx, FnType->getReturnType()));
8084 
8085  llvm_unreachable("Encountered unknown FunctionType");
8086 }
8087 
8088 llvm::Metadata *CodeGenModule::CreateMetadataIdentifierGeneralized(QualType T) {
8089  return CreateMetadataIdentifierImpl(GeneralizeFunctionType(getContext(), T),
8090  GeneralizedMetadataIdMap, ".generalized");
8091 }

8093 /// Returns whether this module needs the "all-vtables" type identifier.
8094 bool CodeGenModule::NeedAllVtablesTypeId() const {
8095  // Returns true if at least one of vtable-based CFI checkers is enabled and
8096  // is not in the trapping mode.
8097  return ((LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFIVCall) &&
8098  !CodeGenOpts.SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFIVCall)) ||
8099  (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFINVCall) &&
8100  !CodeGenOpts.SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFINVCall)) ||
8101  (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast) &&
8102  !CodeGenOpts.SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFIDerivedCast)) ||
8103  (LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast) &&
8104  !CodeGenOpts.SanitizeTrap.has(SanitizerKind::CFIUnrelatedCast)));
8105 }

8107 void CodeGenModule::AddVTableTypeMetadata(llvm::GlobalVariable *VTable,
8108  CharUnits Offset,
8109  const CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
8110  llvm::Metadata *MD =
8111  CreateMetadataIdentifierForType(QualType(RD->getTypeForDecl(), 0));
8112  VTable->addTypeMetadata(Offset.getQuantity(), MD);
8113 
8114  if (CodeGenOpts.SanitizeCfiCrossDso)
8115  if (auto CrossDsoTypeId = CreateCrossDsoCfiTypeId(MD))
8116  VTable->addTypeMetadata(Offset.getQuantity(),
8117  llvm::ConstantAsMetadata::get(CrossDsoTypeId));
8118 
8119  if (NeedAllVtablesTypeId()) {
8120  llvm::Metadata *MD = llvm::MDString::get(getLLVMContext(), "all-vtables");
8121  VTable->addTypeMetadata(Offset.getQuantity(), MD);
8122  }
8123 }

8132 llvm::Value *
8133 CodeGenModule::createOpenCLIntToSamplerConversion(const Expr *E,
8134  CodeGenFunction &CGF) {
8135  llvm::Constant *C = ConstantEmitter(CGF).emitAbstract(E, E->getType());
8136  auto *SamplerT = getOpenCLRuntime().getSamplerType(E->getType().getTypePtr());
8137  auto *FTy = llvm::FunctionType::get(SamplerT, {C->getType()}, false);
8138  auto *Call = CGF.EmitRuntimeCall(

8143 CharUnits CodeGenModule::getNaturalPointeeTypeAlignment(
8144  QualType T, LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo, TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo) {
8145  return getNaturalTypeAlignment(T->getPointeeType(), BaseInfo, TBAAInfo,
8146  /* forPointeeType= */ true);
8147 }
8148 
8149 CharUnits CodeGenModule::getNaturalTypeAlignment(QualType T,
8150  LValueBaseInfo *BaseInfo,
8151  TBAAAccessInfo *TBAAInfo,
8152  bool forPointeeType) {
8153  if (TBAAInfo)
8154  *TBAAInfo = getTBAAAccessInfo(T);
8155 
8156  // FIXME: This duplicates logic in ASTContext::getTypeAlignIfKnown. But
8157  // that doesn't return the information we need to compute BaseInfo.
8158 
8159  // Honor alignment typedef attributes even on incomplete types.
8160  // We also honor them straight for C++ class types, even as pointees;
8161  // there's an expressivity gap here.
8162  if (auto TT = T->getAs<TypedefType>()) {
8163  if (auto Align = TT->getDecl()->getMaxAlignment()) {
8164  if (BaseInfo)
8165  *BaseInfo = LValueBaseInfo(AlignmentSource::AttributedType);
8166  return getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(Align);
8167  }
8168  }
8169 
8170  bool AlignForArray = T->isArrayType();
8171 
8172  // Analyze the base element type, so we don't get confused by incomplete
8173  // array types.
8174  T = getContext().getBaseElementType(T);
8175 
8176  if (T->isIncompleteType()) {
8177  // We could try to replicate the logic from
8178  // ASTContext::getTypeAlignIfKnown, but nothing uses the alignment if the
8179  // type is incomplete, so it's impossible to test. We could try to reuse
8180  // getTypeAlignIfKnown, but that doesn't return the information we need
8181  // to set BaseInfo. So just ignore the possibility that the alignment is
8182  // greater than one.
8183  if (BaseInfo)
8184  *BaseInfo = LValueBaseInfo(AlignmentSource::Type);
8185  return CharUnits::One();
8186  }
8187 
8188  if (BaseInfo)
8189  *BaseInfo = LValueBaseInfo(AlignmentSource::Type);
8190 
8191  CharUnits Alignment;
8192  const CXXRecordDecl *RD;
8193  if (T.getQualifiers().hasUnaligned()) {
8194  Alignment = CharUnits::One();
8195  } else if (forPointeeType && !AlignForArray &&
8196  (RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl())) {
8197  // For C++ class pointees, we don't know whether we're pointing at a
8198  // base or a complete object, so we generally need to use the
8199  // non-virtual alignment.
8200  Alignment = getClassPointerAlignment(RD);
8201  } else {
8202  Alignment = getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(T);
8203  }
8204 
8205  // Cap to the global maximum type alignment unless the alignment
8206  // was somehow explicit on the type.
8207  if (unsigned MaxAlign = getLangOpts().MaxTypeAlign) {
8208  if (Alignment.getQuantity() > MaxAlign &&
8209  !getContext().isAlignmentRequired(T))
8210  Alignment = CharUnits::fromQuantity(MaxAlign);
8211  }
8212  return Alignment;
8213 }
8214 
8215 bool CodeGenModule::stopAutoInit() {
8216  unsigned StopAfter = getContext().getLangOpts().TrivialAutoVarInitStopAfter;
8217  if (StopAfter) {
8218  // This number is positive only when -ftrivial-auto-var-init-stop-after=* is
8219  // used
8220  if (NumAutoVarInit >= StopAfter) {
8221  return true;
8222  }
8223  if (!NumAutoVarInit) {
8224  unsigned DiagID = getDiags().getCustomDiagID(
8225  DiagnosticsEngine::Warning,
8226  "-ftrivial-auto-var-init-stop-after=%0 has been enabled to limit the "
8227  "number of times ftrivial-auto-var-init=%1 gets applied.");
8228  getDiags().Report(DiagID)
8229  << StopAfter
8230  << (getContext().getLangOpts().getTrivialAutoVarInit() ==
8231  LangOptions::TrivialAutoVarInitKind::Zero
8232  ? "zero"
8233  : "pattern");
8234  }
8235  ++NumAutoVarInit;
8236  }
8237  return false;
8238 }
8239 
8240 void CodeGenModule::printPostfixForExternalizedDecl(llvm::raw_ostream &OS,
8241  const Decl *D) const {
8242  // ptxas does not allow '.' in symbol names. On the other hand, HIP prefers
8243  // postfix beginning with '.' since the symbol name can be demangled.
8244  if (LangOpts.HIP)
8245  OS << (isa<VarDecl>(D) ? ".static." : ".intern.");
8246  else
8247  OS << (isa<VarDecl>(D) ? "__static__" : "__intern__");
8248 
8249  // If the CUID is not specified we try to generate a unique postfix.
8250  if (getLangOpts().CUID.empty()) {
8251  SourceManager &SM = getContext().getSourceManager();
8252  PresumedLoc PLoc = SM.getPresumedLoc(D->getLocation());
8253  assert(PLoc.isValid() && "Source location is expected to be valid.");
8254 
8255  // Get the hash of the user defined macros.
8256  llvm::MD5 Hash;
8257  llvm::MD5::MD5Result Result;
8258  for (const auto &Arg : PreprocessorOpts.Macros)
8259  Hash.update(Arg.first);
8260  Hash.final(Result);
8261 
8262  // Get the UniqueID for the file containing the decl.
8263  llvm::sys::fs::UniqueID ID;
8264  if (llvm::sys::fs::getUniqueID(PLoc.getFilename(), ID)) {
8265  PLoc = SM.getPresumedLoc(D->getLocation(), /*UseLineDirectives=*/false);
8266  assert(PLoc.isValid() && "Source location is expected to be valid.");
8267  if (auto EC = llvm::sys::fs::getUniqueID(PLoc.getFilename(), ID))
8268  SM.getDiagnostics().Report(diag::err_cannot_open_file)
8269  << PLoc.getFilename() << EC.message();
8270  }
8271  OS << llvm::format("%x", ID.getFile()) << llvm::format("%x", ID.getDevice())
8272  << "_" << llvm::utohexstr(Result.low(), /*LowerCase=*/true, /*Width=*/8);
8273  } else {
8274  OS << getContext().getCUIDHash();
8275  }
8276 }

8280  "Should have emitted all decls deferred to emit.");

8282  "Newly created module should not have deferred decls");

8285  "Still have (unmerged) EmittedDeferredDecls deferred decls");
8286 
8287  assert(NewBuilder->DeferredVTables.empty() &&

8290

8292  "Newly created module should not have mangled decl names");

8294  "Newly created module should not have manglings");
